New Year is always an invite to stablish goals for the next 365 days.
There are some areas there I'm pleased like improving my knowledge on idioms, writing, speaking, presenting scientific articles.
There are also areas that I should improve like statistics, IA, algorithms and how to present a work I developed.
So I need to have some strategies for achieving goals.
1 - Improving a new language: I need to study, daily, at least little time like 15 minutes.
And this study includes writing, reading a lot.
2 - Presenting scientific articles: It's important to search inovative findings, read, study and try to disseminate these new ideas.
When I suppose to be a presenter I need to stydy a lot.
3 - Improve my knowledge on statistics: a challenge, but not impossible.
Like previous goals I'll need to study sistematically and never give up.
4 - Understanding algorithms - a new knowledge and very difficult to understanding for whom is not an specialty on this area but I think that if I'll be persistent I will learn.
So much challenge but if I meet all my goals it will contribute to my happiness, of course.
