What's the future of travel?
Nowadays people can travel around a world almost without any limits.
During the last 100 years people change the waythey travel.
Even our grand parents spent days or weeks for traveling between continents.
Ships were the fastest mode of traveling.
Than airlines started offer their services and nowa we can fligh in 24 hours around the glob.
People trying to deleoped new way of transport to minimise lengh of travel.
On the other hand we are looking beyond the horizon of the glob, we are intresting for travel into space.
There are two companies which work for making traveling in space more accesible.
It is a big chance that in a short future people will start traveling in to a space.
At the beginning it could cost a fortune for ordinary people but it will change when more companies will developed their technology and services.
It will still remains we will move from one place to another but we will use diferent mode of transport, maybe we will sleep during the trip to minimise the cause of traveling in space becasue we still don't know the impact on our body and mind when traveling on space.
First, I would like to say thank you for letting me write this request in this amazing magazine.
As you already know, I will write about "The School Of The Future."
I will especially write about in what ways do you think schools will be different in the future and in what ways might they still be the same.
I think schools will be different in the future by accepting ICT ecuipments such as projectors, sound boxes and so on.
I think by using these exuipments, it will be so efficient and both students and teachers will be able to facilitate their classes very smoothly in the future.
On the other hand, schools will still be the same by offering school lunches.
I believe that we need school lunch dietitian to insure students' individual health.
Plus, school lunch time should be fun!
I like schools today, but I hope that future schools will also be nice by having a great balance between accepting a new technology and mainting an old schools' tradition.
