"Television entertains, but can it also educate?,"
if I would answer this question, I would say "Yes.."
I have a reason to support this statement.
Firstly, I of course agree that television entertains by showing audiences variety shows, quiz shows, comedy shows and so on.
Usually, this kind of TV shows are very popular among kids and teenagers.
In fact, I also enjoy watching these types of TV shows.
Moreover, TV can also educate by broadcasting about recent news, science, social studies and so on.
Of course, learning something in school and learning something from workbooks are important, but I think TV shows will also be part of education.
On TV, you can learn things that can't be taught in school, and they can sometimes be very educational for kids like us.
in conclusion, I think that we should live well with mass media like television, and I think that will lead us to a better life in the future.
