In this century, Mobile phone has become indispensable part of our personal and professional life.
We use it to connect and communicate with our love one, clients, boss and other people around us.
And with smartphone, some people use it for business purpose.
Young millionaires have been using mobile phone to creat customer engagement and sell products worth more than millions.
Many employees also use it as a main tool for working remotely.
Banning mobile phone usage in public space will interupt a main channel for communication respectively and cuase a massive inconvenience.
However, using mobile phone in public space can trigger several joint problems.
In some spaces like library and movie theater, mobile phone ringtone and blue light can disturb people nearby and ruin the serenity environment of the space.
Having long and loud conversations via mobiles on public transportation disrupt the peace of the journey and distract other concentration.
And the loud noise can spread the negative emotion.
Another drawback of using mobile phone in public spaces especially government service and hospital is that it annoy professional officers who are focusing and doing their job.
In my opinion, Instead of imposing bans, town concil shoud allow people to use moblie phone with some restriction and encourage people to use mobile phones and other electronic equipment with consideration for others.
