Its a debatable issue whether one needs a still and steady life or intense life which is full of excitement and challenges.
I personally believe that life should be challenging and deep enough so that we can be remembered by all other people till the time life exist on this universe.
To embark with, intense life has its certain benefits.
The one most common one is that such a life teach you new and different skills required to solve issues further boosting your confidence level and making you famous.
To illustrate this, the famous scientist Einstin belonging to a small village accept the challenge and invented the bulb which further made him a famous scientist and still remembered by all of us.
Secondly, such life reduces stress and makes the life more happening and lively to live whereas calm and steady life is good for initial time but after sometime you easily gets bored with such a life and you are follwoing the same routine from many years.
For example, recent survey conducted by The Times newspaper shows that people living in hilly area those who are doing same kind of work does not have any excitement for life as compared to city people.
To sum up, it's only the intense quality of life which helps an individual to learn new methods and techniques, further boosting their confidence level to except new challenges of life and making them famous personalities.
