Books and technology I am a music teacher.
I work at a small school.
All my students get the nots in paper form.
But the newest trend is to work with a tablet.
We do not need paper and for the enviroment is this good.
At the moment is my biggest work to scan all my music nots that I need.
My tablet is very good but I have to learn to need it.
The biggest question is:"What is the easyest form to find the nots on the computer?"
Ore only I have a computer the students do not have them.
Also a problem is, that not all schools have wireless to send a message to print what I need.
At the moment is this for me the future.
The primary schools have the facility and the students learn early to work with a computer.
I see the problem not in the school but at home!
The children are often alone at home and they do not only work for the school on the computer the temptation is to surf in the internet.
We all know what happens next.
