It is often said that health is wealth so people should consider health before money.
I agree with the statement because healthy people can live independently.
However, I believe that money is equally important to live a healthy life.
Some people believe that healthy people are less dependent on their family.
Because they can learn new things quicker by concentrating for long time on their work.
Nowdays, employeers prefer people with new skills and are highly paid which is enough for them to surive on their own.
In this they can work till the time they want to get reitreed.
For intsance, a report from 2012 at oxford university found that the healthier people learn 5 times faster than the people who are not able to concentrate.
Therefore, health must be taken seriously.
On the other hand, I think that, nowdays, money play a vital role in keeping you healthy.
Rich people can stay away from disease by eating organic food which is very difficult to aford for normal people.
In this way people are less prone to get the diseases and they can stay healthy for longer time as compared to people with less income.
For example, a survey in india found that 90% of the rich people have their own farms for growing organic vegeatbles.
To sum up, It is undeniable that health should be given the highest importance as compared to other urgent items.
it is also true that money should not be ignored.
