A new year started, here in Liceo Classico.
We are all coming back from our vacations, and it's now time to focus on the goal we want to reach this year.
I am really interested in greek.
This year we will start studying greek poetries and I can't wait to do so.
Saffo's words have always enchanted my mind and now I am really excited to learn something more about her stile and her living.
However, I am not interested only about greek.
I know this year we will start to study english literature too, so I know it is a really great opportunity to improve my english.
I would really like to be able to get the english certification this year or maybe the next.
To achieve my goals I will work hard, because I know that nothing comes from nothing.
I want to built my future day after day, learning as much as it is possibile.
Every new skill I get it is a bigger possibility to get what i want in life.
I really like to travel around the world, especially with my boyfriend.
For the moment we go for low cost vacations, we don't really have much money.
We've gone to Kracow two years ago and we've stayed there for a week.
Althoug Poland became part of the European Union, they still don't have the Euro.
For this reason it is really convenient for us European people to spend a period there: one Euro values four of their Zloty.
Moreover, Krakow is rich of history: we've seen lots of interesting buildings, from Synagogues to castles.
In Krakow there is a strong hebraic culture, they have seven Synagogues, all set in the same district.
In the older Synagogue there's now a museum, but other ones are still used to pray and to celebrate religious functions.
The Kupa Synagogue, so small but so colourful, is one of the most beautiful monument I ever visited.
One hour and an half by bus from Krakow there are Birkeanau and Auschwitz Lagers, two of the saddly famous german Lager in where Nazists imprisoned Hebras during Nazist Regyme.
I strongly reconmend everyone to visit this places, to realize how human being can be cruel and not to forget.
