My favorite subject is math.
I never tired of it even though I have been studying it for ten hours every day.
Thinking math problem renders me nothing but pleased.
But I have some troubles.
I can solve difficult problems if I have a lot of time, but the exam I'm going to take is time-limited one.
This is because I want to reduce the amount of time I need to come up with the solution for problems.
On top of that, I'd like to improve my arithmetic ability, which also reduces time loss.
To achieve this, I will do problem solving exercise every week.
In this exercise, I must solve six problems within 150 minutes, as I do in the exam.
Then, I will analyze causes of time loss, and consider feasible measures for them.
And, I also make it a rule not to give up calculation in the middle.
--- Should computers and tablets completely replace books in schools and universities? ---
If I have to answer this question, I would say, "Yes.."
I have a reason to support this opinion.
I know that traditional books, such as textbooks or workbooks are very good for both students and teacher' learning and teaching method, but, recenly, there is a movement that supports the use of technological textbooks or workbooks.
 (So called "e-textbooks or e-workbooks.) 
I totally support this movement because by using 'e-textbooks' or 'e-workbooks', I believe that there will be a lot of benefits.
For example, I believe that e-textbooks can help visualize some complicated things, such as chemical compounds or body mecanism, and e-workbooks will be able able to do answer checks automatically.
Plus, by accepting this method, I believe that there will be less burden to both of students and teachers and they will be able to focus on some other things.
I think that's good!
For these reasons, I think there is a high possibility that school textbooks and workbooks will be replaced into technological ones.
My reasons for learning English Learning English is almost necessary nowadays.
When you speak English, many things are opened to you, such as jobs, studies, or even friends !
For example, I personally spend a lot of time surfing on the web, and during all of this time, I sometimes met new people from all around the world.
Have learned English the way I did allowed me to talk to those people and to discuss with them !
To be interested in new cultures, new ways of thinking and countries.
But that's not it, learning English is also important to me for my studies.
I would love to be accepted in a prestigious High School with anglophone students.
Maybe I'm too ambitious, but it's important to have dreams and to follow them !
Moreover, I just love learning languages, specially English.
I don't know why is it so special to me, but I don't always need a reason to do something, right ?
Just go for it, and have fun !
The school of the future An excitement assumption: school of the future.
There's something that always put me in questions.
Why schools have the same profile since I was a child?
They try to update the schedule, try to improve qualifications of teachers but the time are always the same.
Today, parents, specially mothers need to work not only at house.
So they need to leave their children in a safe place where they know their children will have many education activities.
But the time taht schools offer are rarely in accord to timetable's parents.
If they supply this necessity, they are very expensive.
So it's important to readapt schools.
They should be fexible with hours.
They will need to offer activities related to informatic technologies.
If they don't students will be boring and not interested in classes.
Some professions will be replaced by modern ones.
So, we will need courses to qualify workers to these new tendencies.
