MODERN SCHOOLS The older we are getting, the more technological progess we can see.
We are creating flying cars in our heads thinking about future.
But how about schools?
What will they look like in next hundred years?
When you turn back a hundred years, you see how many changes became from that time.
We already learn from different devices in school, teachers are showing information not only on blackboards, but also electric boards, on which they can fluently turn next topics.
So whats next?
It is believed that in the future robots will replace humans work.
So this is how I see it...
Teachers will be replaced by robots, but they still would look like real human beings.
That would solve the problem of teachers deficit and eldery average age.
I also think that in future students will have to give their fingerprint to prevent burglaries.
But I suppose sitting in the wooden chairs in front of a desk will never change, because it is the only way teaching can be made.
Dear mayor, I\u2019m writing you regarding the issue with the use of portable devices such a mobile phone on public spaces.
Recent researches indicate that the number of users in the last years is rapidly increasing.
Especially the newer generations want to have all the mod cons to hold a \u201Cstep with the time\u201D.
On the one hand, during the usage from mobile phones in the public places people are showing an unrespect for the community.
On the other hand, for many people the mobile phones are a necessarily due to work or a private matter.
That\u2019s means they must use their mobile phones for example in a restaurant.
There is no doubt in my mind that there is a need of taking measures regarding this matter.
The burden of responsibility lies in the hand of any of us.
As regards the most appropriate response to this situation, one suggestion would be to start a campaign to show the nation the disadvantages of overusing their mobile phones on public places.
In my opinion it would be wrong to take the law into your own hands and completely prohibit using cell phones.
It would be great put all factors in perspective before concluding.
The world surely be a better place to live if we all have respect for each other.
After all, we are only humans but have all the time in our hands to make a better tomorrow for our children.
