People have been always told that honesty is one the most important virtues since they were little, which means they should always avoid lying to others.
Even though no specific reasons were given at that time, teachers prefer to tell children moral stories.
When someone looks back his childhood through photo albums, these memories might be reminiscent of how necessary it is to be honest as their teacher once told them.
That is, people will have to face several consequence if they are found being deceitful.
There is a really simple fact about lying to others, and they will choose not listening to you next time.
It is common fact as it looks like. However, if our society has fraudulent criminals disguised as charitable helpers all over the place, it would have a devastating impact to people's faith about giving a hand to those in needs in the long run.
When it is becoming harder and harder for them to receive any help, it could one of most despair thing can happen to the society.
Also, bragging yourself, as a form of lying, always makes your feelings hollow eventually.
Not to mention trying to cover up these lies with other lies, and it will end up out of hand.
Last but not least, lying will make you blind to where you can improve to be a better person in overall.
Not knowing their short-comings, some people create a false impression of themselves by lying to others.
Those are my thoughts about how unacceptible it is to tell a lie.
