Nowadays, it is a fact that the vast majority of children like to spend their time playing video games.
I think that is a good way of entertaining but only if it is done with control.
Firstly, it is understandable that parents do not like video games, because it can bring about several problems to their kids, for example, it can made them more violent, antisocial, addicted....
On the other hand, I believe that this hobbie can help young people because it can bring some benefits too, such as improving their creativity, developing their imagination, helping them to make friends...
A further point is that the most important facts when deciding if video games are good or bad, are how many time you spend and what tipe of video game you are playing.
In conclusion, from my point of view, video games are not such a negative thing like most of parents think, but it all depends on how much control you have when you are playing them.
