In my opinion, animals belong in nature, but I am not against zoos.
Pleas don't confuse my words.
I think zoos are important.
Zoos allow people to learn about animals, their environment and what they eat.
Furthermore, the zoos are a family spaces where children could enjoy the nature with out the wild life risk.
Also, the most important zoos in the world have helped to conserve some animals species which are disappearing.
For example, many animals in danger of extinction have reproduced in zoos.
In the other hands, I don't agree with people who have wild animals locked in cages.
In my country there are many homes where are exotic birds in cages.
Others have squirrels and turtles as a pet.
In my opinion, that is animal cruelty.
The ordinary people don't know about wild animals health care.
Also, the people don't supply suitable food to the animals.
This animals couldn't reproduce in captivity because at most time they don't have a couple.
