In this day and age, most of the time young people feel that the educational system is not suited for them.
Some students can learn things very easily and find that they are not using their capacities as its fullest or the opposite, being this the students who cannot have good grades regardless what they study, as they do not have the hability to make the most of it.
If a school is considering this when giving the title of graduation to their students, they ought to be aware of the opportunities in the surroundings to better facilitate the connection between the both sides.
Youngsters sometimes have low self-esteem which makes it difficult for them to decide what to do, fearing the approach they have with others.
As for adults, they should stymulate criativity, giving them tools to develop their integration, helping them and incentivate the demonstration of their points of view.
With all the certain this type o work will help youn people to engage in the society, develp their mindset, learn by doing, build intergenerational tights and get everyone closer to each other as there is always opportunity to find solutions for problems, with solidarity. Bearing this in mind, volunteering could create a space for alternative means of community support, it could also help the economic system, raise humanitarian values as there is no technical obligation would only require respect between one another.
