At this time of inequality world, a big round of applause must be given to front-line volunters who have been battaling poverty and heath issues for underpriveledge people.
We are in dasperate need for more volunteers in order to continue the flight and win this poverty war.
Forcing high schools to complete the volunteer work might increase number of volunteers in the short run, however, it is not sustainable in the long run.
This requirement can impose students to take the positive action for their community, but it can not highlight their concern over the struggling of the underpriviledge in their community to cope with the worsen air polution, drought and hungry.
Forcing students without educating them about volunteer work can mark a new point of conflict.
They will solve the problem without emphasize the beneficial living condition.
I suggest the school to initiate the volunteer course.
This course will make the students believed and interested in the volunteers work story given out by the guest teachers who has adopted the volunteer work in their routine life.
This course will mention about possible way to start easily volunteer work.
If the students are educated, it will be easy for convincing them to take the small steps in action.
To make the volunteer work contagious, the school need a wisely communication campaign and intriguing reward.
The school might offer the certificated for those who have finished this volunteer coures.
This purpose of this course is to mitigate the damage from misunderstanding action.
Enlighting the value of volunteers work instead of imposing school requirement seem to be an effective and sustainable approach to ensure every students access to a set of knowledge before taking the meaningful work for others.
