How employees feel at work is becoming a main focus nowdays.
Managers admitted that workers are more effective when they feel confortable at work, and for the last recent years have wondered how to make it happen.
In order to make workers confortable, a lot have ideas has seen the light.
New work organisations appeared as: homeworking, open spaces, relax rooms, and many more.
In my opinion all of these arragement are an excellent thing.
The new open spaces, one of the best ideas of these new organisations.
First, open spaces broad to the cowokers the chance to communicate much more.
They are now able to exchange informations much more quiclky than before.
In cubicles people had to phone their coworkes or go to their desk in order to give a information.
Also, open spaces is a good way to reenforce the team building, and to create a team spirit even stronger.
When people are in enclosed workstations, they easy can forget they are a teamp.
With open spaces relationship between coworkers are stronger.
Of course, open spaces can offer some difficulties toward some employees.
Some people find it too noisy and are having trouble to concatrate on their work.
Other people will regret their intimacy, and might feel unconfortable in a space with no walls.
For the first difficulty, employees can use headphones to reduce the noise, and not be disturb for a time period.
For the second difficulty, it's up to every employee to decorate their desk with photos, or souvenirs to make it more intimate.
Regarding this different points, i believe open spaces are a great new way to organize the work place and should be encourage.
