Nowadays, people who live in the affluent countries are getting older .
Therefore the demand to the medical access is increasing swiftly.
However there are a less medical doctors in the rural areas compared with cities.
There are varius reasons that a medical doctor prefers to work in a city than a rural area accoridng different reaserchs that is executed by different European medical hospitals.
First of all, a research that is conducted by Erasmuc MC in the Netherlands shows that the medical doctors prefer to work in cities because of the family.
Both their wives and children are against to live a small cities, therefore the doctors have to make a diffucult dicisions.
Moreover, it turns out that the partner of the medical doctor a work has that is settled in a city.
Secondly, the medical doctors walk problems that is associated with transport if they want to in work a rural areas.
The road in a lot of wealthy countries is getting bussier, so the the trafic jam is increasing rapidly.
This problems daunted the medical doctors to work in rural areas. Many medical doctors shows that they are willing to work in a rural areas, however they avoid this areas due to the trafic jams.
On the other hand, the research indicite that thare are medical doctors who avoid rural areas because the care demand in a rural area is lower than a city.
In a big cities there a lot of people , therefore the demand to care activites is higher than a rural areas.
To summarize a medical doctor would earn more money if he or she works in a city than a rural area.
To solve this problem the government has to stimulate the use of public transport.
If the people who work other sectors use more in public transport instead of cars, the trafic jam would decrease.
This will make easier for the medical doctors to travel from a city to a rural areas.
Another solutation would be that the health insurance companies more paid to those work in a rural areas to stimulate the medical doctors to work in a rural area.
INTRODUCTION Telling the truth has been an issue always argued for centuries, and all men have always wandered the importance of it.
Poets, phylosophers, musicians and more generally every kind of artists have posed the question.
However, I think that neither themselves nor their audience can be give en exhausted answer.
WHAT IS THAT?
In accordance with some of the most prestigiuos phylosophical theories, we cannot find a precise statement to sum up what truth is , in other words they argue that truth does not exist.
To be more precise they assume that there is not only a single truth, but thousands or billiards examples of it.
Everyone of us knows what is real for him and the underlying reasons that lead him to believe in something.
EXAMPLES As I see it, not always telling the truth is the best thing to do, in same cases a lies is a way to protect people especially our dearest and nearest.
On the other hand, everyone of us should be intuitive enough to know when is the moment to lie or telling the truth, and above all recognising who is ready to accept a difficult and harmful truth even when it could convey a big sorrow.
Some examples can be related to relationships or deseases where your doubts do not let you to decide what is better for others.
CONCLUSIONS As I said before, we are required a big quantity of braveness, but also a sharp spirit of observation to decide when is the moment to speak clearly.
