There have been an ongoing debate around enclosed workstations versus open design.
Open offices tend to enable collaboration while enclosed spaces tend to encourage more focus.
However, every spaces have been designed for specific purpose like our house where living room is an open space for familiy gathering while our bedroom is an enclosed space for private activity.
Office should be designed in the same direction.
Employees have been doing many activities in the office.
Clearly not all of these activities are effectively done in a single type of a space.
This is the main reason I support the company to make a multi purpose working spaces.
Meeting and training might need open space for enhancing collaboration and discussion.
On the other hand, cubicles will be a peaceful space for doing a complicated work which need deeply focus.
Divesify the enviroment of working space will give the employees the choice to choose the space for completing their specific task in productive way.
Well design working space can increase creativity, innovation and proficiency in the company.
In my opinion, I would suggest to combine the cubicles and open spaces because every employees has their own preference.
Let's them choose their working environment for delivering highly productive task.
Many innovative offices make a radical change by offering their employee with non-fixed seat.
Employees can freely choose to work at quiet room, garden, kitchen, co-working space or any spaces that they feel comfortable to work.
Unbelievable, the various of working space can provoke employees' productivity.
Especially, when the office was designed based on collective of data.
Schooling is a big part of someone's life.
There you meet a lot of people: teachers, friends, supervisers and more.
Some will come into your life and will never leave, while others will follow their own path.
In this journey, some people will have the same teacher for several year while other will have new teachers each year.
In my opinion having different teachers each year is the best way to collect new skills, and to learn from different places.
Every one is unique, and every teachers also are.
Having a new teacher each year will give you new skills, and will help you to develop yourself in different maners.
Also having a new teacher each year is the best way to confront students with real life.
When you will go to work, you will meet a lot of different people, and different attitudes.
Having autorities figure changing when you are studying is a very good way to prevent the futre.
Another main point is: adaptation.
Changing teachers will help young ones to be adaptative in different situations.
I might be 100% sure it is better for students, I also understand the disadvantages of changing teachers each year.
First, some children need time to get use to someone.
And for this kind of people changing each year is very challenging.
They might even suffer from this turn-over, and see it as if they were abandonned by their teachers.
Also, for students that have been developping a trustfull relationship with their teachers they could be more motivated within their work if they have the same teacher each year.
Anyway, there are a lot of sensibilities, and my opinion is not a sure thing, even if I believe in my reasons.
