Learning can be difficult if we don't use appropriate tools.
For example, learning English with many tools at the same time will make learner confused since different tool has different unique feature.
This text is a suggestion to learn English using a web-based tool namely Write and Improve.
Write and Improve is an English learning tool developed by Cambridge University.
It has many features which allow a learner take most benefit of the tool.
At first, it invites the learner to write in English on broad topics within different level, from beginner to business level.
It also offers a preparation for IELTS test, a test that is used for University entrance in some Commonwealth countries.
Apart from that, the learners can create their own workbook or join other workbooks.
This feature also can be used for an English teachers to share the homeworks to their students and to make online assessment.
Let's take a more detail example.
When learners entering an Writing and Improve workbooks, for instance beginner level, they are asked to choose a topic and write an article (can be review, summary, or argumentation) for that topic.
Writing and Improve (W&I) requires minimum word numbers to qualify that a task is done.
When learners accomplish this requirement, they can submit their works by clicking "Check" button.
W&I will assest that works and give feedbacks.
The learners can revise their writing based on the given feedbacks and submit it again to obtain such improvements.
W&I will show the score of writing sequentially.
