In my opinion offices in seperate rooms are more comfortable than offices, where most employees are in one room.
Indeed, it is easier to help each other, but if an amount of your colleagues have to call important partners of the company the whole time, it can be really disturbing.
Therefore, employees are not able to focus and concentrate on their own work and that is very inconvenient.
Due the fact that the most people are working slower and more carelessly while they are being disturbed, not only the company suffers from it, but also the staff themselves.
For instance, my dad is a clerk in a company, where all employees work in one room and he describes the situation as very uncomfortable and annoying, because his colleagues are on the phone the whole day.
It takes him twice as long to finish his projects now.
To put the main in a nutshell, an office with a open design is not quite right for employees, who have to focus on their own work.
I think tehat it is better to have walls to separete offices of different employees.
First of all, it can be very destructive if there is no walls betweeen different offices.
There are employees who prefer to wrok a calm environment.
It is very important to protect those employees and give them right so that they can work a suitable environment.
Furthermore not all employees in a company conduct the same work, so it is illogical to put all employees in a open office.
