Some high schools have a requirement that student must complete a certain amout of volunteer work in order to graduate.
Volunteer work can offer a large range of diversity.
It can be to help homeless people, to teach a language to foreigners, or to pick up trashes on the beach.
They don't need to be in a large non-gouvernmental organisation to discover what volunteer work is.
Students will encounter many opportunities, and can choose a realm where they feel comfortable in.
High school is a period where childs become adults and are questioning their believes and opinions.
In my opinion that's an excellent idea for many reasons.
Volunteer work presents many advantages for students.
First, it's a work experience.
And as any work experience it will help students to develope new skills and to build a professional network.
Secondly, some teenagers might discover a new interest while working as a volunteer, and find out their path.
Finally, volunteer work will confront young adults to people in need and will make them realise in which society they are living in.
It will open their mind, and their believes, and it will help them to become more responsible adults.
Eventhough I believe that's a great initiative, I think it might be difficult for young adults to manage their time.
High shcool is already very demanding in therm of homeworks, adding volunteer work can lead them in some difficulties.
The lack of free time can be very stressful for some teenagers.
High schools requiring a certain amout of volunteer work in order to graduate must keep in mind these difficulties.
Nevertheless, I am convicted that's a great idea.
Whether people should always tell the truth in any situations remains a highly continuous public discourse.
Although it is undeniable that honesty is of great importance, I strongly believe that in some circumstances, not revealing the truth is an effective choice to protect both speakers and listeners.
In the one hand, honesty is a valuable personality that everyone should have in order to archive a better life.
In the contemporary society, people are likely to broaden their horizons and develop their soft skills by working with people.
The fact has demonstrated that people can only co-operate one another through trust and honesty, which play an essential role in building a long term relationship.
Honest people will never flatter another and make the progress by their own qualification.
Moreover, telling the truth is considered as one of the most effective ways to not only increase understanding and sympathy among people but also help people respect and appreciate differences of others.
Therefore, many companies today choose employees, who are both qualified and reliable because they believe that these people will become powerful workforces for development of society.
