My opinion is that it is good to study abroad for a time during high school or university.
There are 2 advantages.
First you can learn something abroad which people live in Japan cannot experience.
You have some different experience so that you have your own strong point and you can be succuessful in the future.
Those who can think original idea are always needed for every fields.
Second you can learn another language.
It is defficult to learn language uncounciously as we get older.
No matter whatever language you may study, it must be your strong point if you can master it.
And if you can speak some language, you can communicate with many people.
You can improve your personality with this experience.
Otherwise there are also 2 disadvantages.
First no one can know whether you can suit the environment where you will go.
The risk to leave your hometown is more bigger than you expect.
It is not big problems that you can check some imformation in advance like diseases or a culture.
But you cannot check what the locals are like and how the weather and the humid influence on you.
These are serious problems.
Next if you think you will be successful as an elite in Japan, I don't recommend you to studying abroad.
It may be not good as your career. Because the Japanese culture is so unique. And Many Japanese come to be conservative as they get older.
You don't need to take an additional risk.
You'd better enter a high school and an university in Japan.
Anyway I approve of the opinion that students study abroad in his young days.
The experience you got there is your tresure.
To bo honest I think that video games are dangerous.
It rewards you with too much dopamin for too easy tasks.
Everything else is so hard in compare to games.
Children do not want to do something useful because the dopamin rush produced by video games is so high.
Everything else seems too boring and it decrease their productivity and development.
One of the biggest problems is that video games can result in increasing violent behavior.
Soldiers are learning huge responsibility with their weapons.
It is strictly regulated when they can use violent and they know all the consequences.
But in video games children are receiving good points for killing virtual enemy with no punishment for killing inocent people.
They are used to killing.
They are nurturing to kill without consequences.
Another thing is that the video games do not reflect reality.
You can drive virtual car at speed 200 mph and there is no danger of doing it.
So why shuld you drive responsibly in real life if you do not know any better?
I don't think zoos are good places at all.
Never liked, all that animal abuse make me sad.
But thanks to new technologies, like Internet and virtual reality, people can learn about animals differently nowdays.
For example, in Japan they've ceated a 7D Holographic Projection Display Zoo where you can get close to animals safely both for the animal and for visitors.
With this technology reality feels close because uses different dimensions to capture an object (7 Dimension).
Reality has 3D space, we know that, but the reason why we are talking about so many dimensions here is because the hologram is captured from a large number of positions and each position described in 3D space.
And, each captures a variety of viewing directions in 2D space.
Plus, two additional parameters are captured for each direction: image intensity and time.
In other words, a 7D technology is like having a bounch of photographers sorrounding an object.
This technology is fascinating and can help us to get into the wild and learn about it whitout animal abuse.
Maybe in the past zoos were important for us, helps us to see nature in a fantastic way time has change and we need to catch up to the chanching times.
