The future of travel Nowadays everybody uses a way of travelling.
Whether it is by a personal car or taking the public transport people need to go to their job because the majority of them don't work near their homes.
However, I think that in the future travel will be different.
Technology is developed everyday in order to help humans with their lives, so why creating new ways of travelling wouldn't be possible?
I think that travel will change dramatically in the future.
The trams might be suspended above the streets and descend where people need to get down.
The cars' engine will work on more ecologic fuel like compost or solar energy instead of gas.
There will also exist more express trains which will travel all the way around a continent offering, in this way, the opportunity to see the world to more ordinary people.
Whatever the future might bring, one thing that, I think, will not be changed for a good amount of time is the way in which airplanes work and look.
These are already quite developed and I don't see what changes might be brought to them.
The truth is that nobody can surely know what inventions will be brought to live in the future.
But the thing I am sure of is that these will surprise us.
