I agree with the opinions that video games can have a negative impact on children.
They have many negative points and few positive points.
To begin with, I'll show you two negative points.
Firstly, thier violental situation.
Children cannot get to recognize the difference between real and virtual.
Secondly, thier time.
Children may spend much time on playing games.
As a result they don't make time to study, which is the duty of children.
Well, don't we have a compromise plan?
Yes, we have.
It is intellectual games.
I think this is the only positive point the video games have.
Playing intellectual games, for example stuying games or puzzle games, children can activate their brain.
It is very useful to improve their structure thinking.
In conclusion, I almost agree with the opinions that video games can have a negative impact on children, however I also have a compromise plan that intellectual games can be valuable for children.
