As every grown person in the 21st century ought to know, not evey human being looks, feel and desire the same from one other.
Due to these facts, in order to respect each individual's personality, a considerable amount of freedoom should be given to each person.
Among the concept of freedoom, free choice is an essential issue.
On the one hand, despite I might sound quite idealistical. I have to say that I strongly respect and understand the importance of rules, without them our society would be an anarchism and daily life would be like putting an elephant into a car.
However, as it regards to volunteer work I have a completely solid point of view and I will wholeheartedly deffend it.
The reason why I am so concerned about this topys is that I absolutely believe that there are certain things that come out from the deepest part of our soul, and forcing those feelings and emotions result in an awful ending.
Volunteer work is not for everyone, those courangerous people who dare to volunteer have some kind of magical atittude inside themselves.
Therefore, Incluiding this activity as compulstory at school couldn't be more useless.
Nevertheless, there are endless activities to do in order to teach solidarity and empaty such as playing a team sport or planting trees.
In conclusion, considering all things carefully mentioned above, as far as I am concerned, only those who hugely desire to volunteer should do so.
It does not mean they are better people, they just have something special to give to those people who absolutely need their help
