People use mobile phones everywhere, home, park, street, public transports, cafe, and restaurants.
They used it to make calls, use social medias, or just listen musics.
This practive is growth form year to year. In public transport for example, we almost see no one use their mobile phones.
These people habits often disturb comfort of using public facilites including public transports.
To reduce or avoid thid practice, banning the use of mobile phones should be implemented.
Among all activities using mobile phones, the use of of mobile phones to make calls, including video calls, should be strictly prohibited.
This policy will prohibit people for overuse the mobile phones.
Other activities like listening musics, including watching video; read books or articles, and other activities which do not make any noise should be allowed.
This rule should be clearly written in every pubic facility including public transports.
The implementation of the rule could be different among public facilities.
For instance, we prohibit making calls in public transport and restaurant, but we allow it in train station buildings.
There is should be an exception in which all people are allowed to make emergency calls wherever they are.
Furthermore, the exact rules should be discussed among different kinds of people: worker, civil servant, and students.
By implementing the banning of mobile phones usage, the convenience of using public facilites like public transport and restaurant, should be improved.
