Some people believe that zoos are good places to learning about animals, but belonging in nature is good way.
From my view point, they both have their own benefits and drawbacks.
To begin with, if the government provide the zoos, people will have more chance to keep in touch with animals, which their living style and transformation.
Even though you are not zologists, you can also learn about their life cycle and their strengths and weaknesses.
For example, monkey are almost like human which are 99.2% same with humans.
If the zoos are not opened, yet people have never chance to study their behaviors and features.
On the other hand, animals should not be kept in cave which can effect their life cycle, reproduction and even dead.
For instance, crocodile, you can see their life changing in nature and their transforming in zoos are thoroughly different.
In nature, they have more strengths and wilder than in cave.
The another example, keeping in the cave can effect reproductive system due to the fact that the place is tiny and monotonous partnerships.
I believe that if you want to research their life styles or life cycles, why do not we go to see their inhabitants?
You can see through not only their changes but also landscape of the nature views and also can take a selfie.
For instance, in Singapore, they occupy people under ground water tunnel which was built cinder the Pacific Ocean from there you can see any kinds of sea animals such as whales, sea cucumbers and jellyfishs etc.
In conclusion, keeping in the zoos also have advantageous and disadvantageous, hence, I do prefer to keep them in free.
