Working makes part of our lives, when we reach the adult age we need to get a job, in order to earn money to survive.
Only if you have your own company you wouldn\u00B4t start being just a simple employee.
By being an simple employee you have to submit yourself to the conditions the company you work for, gaves you.
In some companies you work in enclosed workstations or cubicles in other offices you have a more open design, in which there are no walls separating employees from their coworkers.
These two different models of offices have pros and cons: the first example gaves you more privacy, silence and concentration; whereas the second type of offices can provide you more interaction with your partners, it\u00B4s easy to dialogue with the others and you never feel alone.
To sum up if it where me I would prefer to work in a cubicle as I would be more concentrated and if I need help I would go to the next office and ask for an opinion.
