The majority of people are made for socialcontact and interaction.
The walls of cubicle offices rob jou from making these connection with your colleagues.
You do get same additional own space and privacy with walls, but this comes with a social cost.
When you open up your officen, a couple of thinks will happen.
People will be able to see one another.
This means that you will not be able to slag anymore.
You could get away with this in a cubicle.
At the same time, you will be able to see your collegaus at work what can give you the motivation to keep working.
And when you need some help you can easaly ask.
The feeling at the office will be different.
It will not only be everybody for himself but more a feeling of working in a group.
This will al create a more colleague friendly environment.
People in general do not prefer small and tight spaces.
We come from ancester who roamed around over open fields.
Having the ability to overlook you direct space, gives the feeling of safety and peace.
You create this feeling by opening op your office.
But it is importend to do it in the correct manner.
So give everybody his own space and do not place people direct infront or next to eachother.
Otherwise, the treshold to get distrected will be lowered.
Natural light is something that is importand for a lot of people.
Walls of cubicles are light barriers that lead to tl lighting.
This is different in an open workspace.
There are secundary school were you first need to spent a certain amount of time on charity work before earning your degree.
This can for example mean that students help by giving Englisch to refugees or maybe work at a homeless shelter.
There are a lot of lessons students are able to learn from doing these type of work.
Volunteer work teaches children to not only think about their own situation, but also about the situations of people less fortunate than them self.
Not everybody has the same opportunities in life.
A little help can make a lot of differance for somebody in need.
Because volunteer work is made part of your graduation progres, , it will force people that would normally not do charity work to try it.
These students are pushed out of their comfort space.
You never know, maybe it will even change their opinion about it.
It can broaden their view.
Starting volunteer work at a younger age will make it feel more normal.
It will also increase the chance that students will do more volunteer work in the future.
We need new volunteers every year.
Inspiring young people to step up can make a difference in maintaining a steady stream of voluntaisr.
