I have been using write and improve for several weeks and wrote many articles.
I can now say about the things that i liked and disliked.
Write and improve provides huge number of topics and all are divided into three categories beginner, intermediate, and advance.
Users as per their convience choose the topic and write up to 300 words.
They have also provided business category in that topics are related to business activity.
This is useful for professional people who want to improve their business english.
The topics in this category are few and limited in subject.
Write and improve must include more variety of topics so that over all practice related to business english can be performed.
One more feature, they have included that is test zone.
This category is for people who is preparing for IELTS.
Here, the topics are listed similar to what comes in IELTS exam.
Sadly, this category is chargeable, and after one review they continuely ask for subscription.
Now, the most important part of this portal is feedback and progress.
Here, they check, mark the mistakes, and give suggestion for correction.
The over all review system is good but lack in details like highlighted part does not mention the mistake detail and also do not suggest the better way of writing.
However, it shows the proficieny and CEFR level.
To summarise, this is a best website I have found where topics and proofread both are available.
I reccommond write and improve to include more business topics and provide more detailed review system.
