When I was a child video games were already quite diffused, but with time their amount is grown.
This is dued to several factors: from one side the technological progress, by the other side parents who are always busier every day and don't have time - neither patience - to stay with their children.
I've often seen exhausted parents who gave their children their mobile phone so that those children would have stayed quiete for - at least - the following thirty minutes.
And I've also seen children who didn't care going out with their friends, preferring instead to play with their xbox console.
This is a serious problem and Governs should try to solve it, basing on the very usefull help of childood psychologists and schools.
I think children should be encouraged to spend time outside, playing, running, going on the roaller, byking.
They need to understand what it means to stay in the nature, they need to have time to explore what they are surraunded from.
Moreover, stay in the nature helps to develop stronger anticorps, which are always usefull.
Video games, if abused, can bring a child to believe what happens it them is real: so that maybe they can learn to believe that social relationship should be based only on social media interations or that it's fair and consented by the law to kill, bit or invest by car someone.
Children should play video games for a limited period of their day also to preserve their view.
Video games are however a good option to spend some time in the day, maybe one our or a little more, to socialize with friends if it's raining and it's not possible to go outside and to develop confidence with technological istruments since the youngest age, because learning havin fun is always a good thing.
