Zoo are places where animals in different circunstances live.
There are a lot of zoos around the world with different priorities and charactersitics.
Nowadays, most of zoos work with endangered creatures or abuse animals from circuses or contraband, but there are also a few zoos who work as an entertaiment place specifically and thats why people often argue about animals being enclosed in unnatural habitats called zoos.
They say that species who are separate from their freedom have several consequences like stress, mentally ills or even suicides.
Animals protectors also debate about the space where animals live.
They argue even if the zoos have the "adequate" space and conditions to stay animals, they still are in captivity.
However, zoos in opposite say that they do an important work to preserve wildlife.
Zoos say that their breeds and rescue programmes help to preserve endangered animals or study different illness and their treatments.
Even, they do an important work teaching children about the value of biodiversity giving them a real experince with animals and wildlife to create ambient awareness.
As I see,zoos have pros and against for wildlife.
These kind of places many times help animals who has been abused or need be rehabilitated to be insert into their natural enviromnent.
Even though zoos help a lot to preserve wildlife they still stay animals captive that's why I strongly believe that it should be an agreement between zoos and hunters to respect wildlife.
I mean that people should help and treat vulnerable creatures and try to re-insert them into their natural enviromnets as soon as possible using zoos as a tool to preserve and help vulnerable animals.
