studying in another country recently has a growing trend among students in different degrees.
Although this experience has some positive effects on the student's life, its drawbacks could not be denied.
On the one hand, for studying abroad, students have to learn a new language and overcome the language barrier in the new country, which is a very valuable experience.
Besides, they will be in touch with a new culture and new people and this would help them to improve their interpersonal skills.
Also, the experience of studying in another country could be a bright spot in the student's resume and enhance their employment chance.
On the other hand, being away from family can be a difficult aspect of this matter for some of the students.
Furthermore, when they feel the lack of family support, they may feel homesickness and depression which affect their performance in the university or college.
