Always more students choos to study abroad and in a larger part they have always great experiences.
Here in Italy we call theese kind of experiences "Erasmus" or "cultural exchanges."
They usually last at least three months, but most times students study abroad for circa six months.
Some of htem, the most motivated ones, stays outside from Italy for one year.
There are a lot of advantages for those who choose to study in a foreign country: firs of all learning another language and getting to know another culture.
Indeed learning a language living in a country where this language is not spoken could become quite difficult, because people haven't the chance to practise in real life.
Moreover, facing with the people of place and with their customs is realy helpful to hunderstand the culture and allows to come closer with the language too.
Go away from home means getting older too: guys start to organize their days, to clean their rooms, to pay light, rubbish, gas and water.
They eventually learn to live as adults, out of the cup of glass in which they have lived for all their lives.
Erasmus is a good option also to know new people, which maybe will help in an eventual future job.
Studying abroad can however have disadvantages because we Italian people are really close to our families and the missing of them sometimes is too much intense that someone can feel alone and suffer solitude.
In some cases moreover going away from home could become an excuse to run away from responsabilities and duties or to get a life out of rules.
A lot of student thinks that what happens in Erasmus remains in Erasmus and they use that period just to have fun and not to study.
Study abroad could be the greates of the experiences with the fair behaviour.
