In this essay, I am going to outline two main problems about all of doctors desire to working in urban areas where can make money rolling in, but in rural region there are not enough doctors.
Based on my knowledge, I am going to demonstrate about the different between urban and rural region .
The First thing is money due to the fact that in city center where can give you a lot of money especially a month more than $50000 dollars or more.
Nevertheless, in rural areas, money is lay income, so they can not spend too much on medical health.
The Second one is convenient, if she works at city center, she could rely on the public transportation such as taxi, subway and city-bike.
However, in the outskirts, they only can trust on the tuktuk or motorbike, which are taking an ages to commute one district to another districts.
And also, the motorcycle is the most dengerous things in transportation because every year in rural areas people are died by motorbike accidents.
On the one hand, working hours, in downtown, it takes only six to eight hours a day to takes duty and in hospitals where have so many sections such as morning, middle-day, night.
On the other hand, in the countrysides, it is so strange consequently, it is only a doctor with two or one nurses to struggle 3 months or 6 months shift which pretty hard to control it.
From my point of view, the government or each medical universities / colleges responsible to branch each states.
For instance, if she lives in suburb, she has better to work in suburb region hospitals.
Do not give them choice.
And second one, controlling amounts of salaries which can separate crowded doctors in city center.
If nurse who has two years experience, she might get $20000 dollars a year.
The third one, fixing the roads and providing subway or round district bus in countryside that kind of things could fix not only long hours commute but also long hours duty.
