All of us know how young people are interested in music, but what they likely miss, is a general tuition in history of the music and a better knowledge about some of the most famous and important compositors.
An always more increasing number of shools have already decided to give lectures where students can choose what fields of the music to study.
The experiments seems to work and students not only are getting high scores, but they also read up on the subjects they are more interested in.
