The importance of zoos are focus in several talks when enviromental workers are together.
To the people who suport the zoos in the cities, this place have a big importance to aware the human beings about their impact in the nature, because only when you know about something you can pretect it.
When the zoos attract people into that, a lot of activities can happen whatever the age of the public.
To the other hand, a lot of people think that the animmals must live free.
In this conception, the zoos are bad places for the animmals, because there are jails very small there and it don't provide an enough interaction with other species, as would happen in their natural habitats.
However, I think the best way to make people become more aware about their role as a being belonging in the nature is provide fair conditions to the animmals live with freedom.
For example, in the South Africa, the savanna's animmals can live free and the human beings pay to visit it in its natural habitat.
This practice is called "safari" and it has been seen like a positive way to improve the human awareness about the enviroment.
When I was an university student I was living with my parents.
I don't think it was the better choice.
My parents' house is located outside the city.
