Education life is an essential part of everyone's life who normally start their student life since three or four years old. During those years kids usually have the same teacher since kindergarden to primary school who teaches them the basic subjects and spend most part of the day with them, opposite to that in high schools, preparatories and colleges people have different teachers for each subject as a resource to teach students get used to learn no matter the teacher style to teach.
This process of teaching in high schools are good to students because they learn to learn indistinctivily to the person who teach and they just focus on the subject and knowledge behind it .
To me, having different teachers each year has more benefits than having one teacher for several years because students have the opportunity to experiment with different styles of teaching during their educative process.
They can also develop abilities to make investigation projects due to each teacher will ask for homework or papers with specifically points to be scored in order that each student should develop those homework with those specifications and investigate the best way to present their works with the correct toppic and framework.
That's why I consider better have different teachers trhough the years instead of one teacher with the same style and the same way to work, something that many times become tedious to students.
