Different teachers have different methods and style to teach concepts, so because of these defferences beween the teachers, some people think that, it can be more useful for students to change their teacher every year, and try deifferent methods, but some others believe that it is not a reliable way to learn, because students will get used to their teacher's behavior and changing the teachers, constantly can be cause to irreparable harmness.
By considering all the main points about this title, we should mention that both of these thoughts have some strengths and weakness which we interfere them in continue.
In the terms of learning issues we shoud consider behavior of both, teachers and students, On one hand, it can be helpful for some students to have different teachers because it will help them to have varies perspective about concepts and it end up with better understanding,for example when a student want to learn verbs, a teacher may tell him/her some words that not make sense for him/her but another teacher may say this concept by a better way.
On the other hand, some students are not adaptable and changing their teacher can not be helpful becuase coordinating with a new method and behavior will be stiff for them, so they are not going to make a great progress. In conclusion, many different elemen have role- depends on personality and age- which people find the best way to learn concepts therefore, the main point is try to find best way without any prejudge.
