I think computers and tablets should completely replace books in schools and universities.
I have four reasons to support my opinion.
Firstly, it is cheaper with long-term view.
Once we get a device, it doesn't spend much money to add a new literature than a paper book.
Secondly, it keeps up the tidy condition as it is new.
Books are going bad, but devices doesn't get old.
We don't need to re-buy them.
We may spend more for initial cost, but not for running cost.
Thirdly, it doesn't need a space because it's portable.
We waste lots of spaces with stacked books.
It's unuseful and dangerous.
We can substitute this space for something other with a device.
Lastly, it's easier to look up literatures.
Wherever and whenever you are, you can do that.
It's very useful On the other hand, I think it is better for novels to read with paper books.
It is one of the precious time to go around book shelves to find an attracting book.
If you have decided which book you read, devices are better, but not, paper is valuable.
