Most medical doctors prefer to work in cities rather than in countrysides.
There are few reasons for such a situation.
Firstly, working in an urban area brings more chances for career development.
Secondly, hospitals located in cities are far better equiped than those in rural ares, which gives medics possibility to fully use their aptitudes and abilities.
Lastly, being a doctor in a city is undoubtedly more beneficial than in a countryside.
However this generates a predicament of not sufficient number of medics in rural areas and under such circumstances lifes of people living in those places are endangered.
One obvious solution to this problem could be an increment of doctor's salaries, who work in those regions.
It might convince some medics to change their workplace.
Another thing could be supply hospitals with larger number of ambulances and mainly with helicopters, which in theory could guarantee greater accessibility to medical healthcare for people whose lifes are at risk.
