After high-school graduation, students have to make choices about their studies.
They need to decide what and where, they want to sutdy.
In the process other choices have to be made such as: should I stay living at home while I am studying, or should I move away and live on my own ?
For some, the choices is simple as their university is not close to their homes so they have to take their own appartement.
Others have to decide wether or not they will move out from their parents.
When students can decide they are few interogations that need to be taken in account.
First: how will you pay your rent ?
There are two options.
Your parents will fund you, or you will have to take a part time job to pay it.
In the second scenario, students need to be aware that they will have less free time, and less time for their homework.
Secondly: will I feel comfortable living on my own ?
Indeed, some young students would'nt feel able to live by their own, and still need the support of their parents.
And last but not least: will it be a benefit for my studies ?
It is important to know if living on my own will be a true benefit or contreversily if it will bring difficulties.
In my opinion, moving away to study can be a great opportunity, and young students will become more independant living by their own if they can manage it.
Nevertheless it is important to be aware that it won't fit for all students, and everyone is different.
I do not have a yes or no answer to this question.
