My reasons for learning English I have studied English since I was at the kindergarden.
Twice a week there was a class in which a theacher taught us animals and colours.
However, I do not know if I remember these from then.
When I started school, my parents wanted me to learn English even though I did not like it.
They used to say that it would help me later but at what?
They did not say.
Later on, I started to like English classes because of a teacher who made these seem funny.
Only then I thought about why I should learn English.
First of all, since I was a little child I wanted to travel the world so I realised that if it would ever happen I should be ready to communicate with the local people.
But how could I do it if I do not know any worlwide language?
That is the main reason why I decided to learn English.
Another reason for learning English is the perspective of a well-paid job.
Nowadays almost every employer ask you to know at least one foreign language.
So it doesn't matter if you are very good at doing something if you don't know one more language besides your mother tongue.
Moreover, I would love to have the chance to study abroad and that's why I must learn English.
All in all, one can never know what life brings so it is better to be prepared for any opportunity one might receive.
