Nowadays studying abroad has become popular among students from different levels and this kind of opportunities have pros and cons to considerate.
In my opinion, I agree with the idea of studying abroad because there are more pros than cons.
Some of the most important cons about studying abroad are: more options to study; international students have the opportunity to progress in their studies and more job opportunities with enhanced CVs, students also make more friends, becoming more independents and learning new languages and cultures, that is why abroad study trips or scholarships are good chances to students.
On the other hand, students also have to deal with difficulties and cons during their abroad journeys, some of the problems are scholar places cost, culture shock, not fluency in language even some students have issues in the return to their country and their studies there.
To sum up, studying abroad is a wonderful experience in each person, but, people also consider some things before they decide to go with this kind of study adventure.
My favourite season of the year By: Carla Parr I like both seasons in my country, but, if I have to choose one definitively winter season will be the chosen.
To me, winter season is the best seasons ever because during this season I can snuggle with a mug of hot chocolate and watching movies.
I also can share with friends on a camping trip making smores.
In general, I can do different activities with people that I love.
Some advantages of the winter season are holidays.
During winter season Christmas and New Year eve come.
These holidays give us a great opportunity to share with family and friends, spending time together or doing funny activities such as an invisible friend, special dinners, or small trips near to my town.
In conclusion, winter is my favourite season ever because is the perfect opportunity to share and create moments with relatives and fellows I love; some of the people who I am not able to see frequently, that is why this is my favourite season.
