Living away on your own during school is a good way to get to know new possibilities and overcome challenges.
Some students prefer to live at home with their family while they are at school, that is why they can save money and it is more confortable having your parents around to support you.
However, I can say from my own experience that live away is the best option, if you are open for new challenges.
I will explore below.
I got to an university far from my hometown.
Firstly, I took a bus in Vinhedo to go to Sao Paulo where my university is located.
I watched the classes and then I took the bus back to Vinhedo.
During this period I lived with mom and It was good having my mom's support.
Nevertheless, it was a long trip everyday.
I spend around three hours in a bus and I was getting tired.
After a few months, I decided to move to Sao Paulo to live on my own.
That was the best decision I ever made!
I saved time, I learned how to cook, how to take of my house.
And this was a learning that I took for the rest of my life.
In conclusion, despite all the facilities of living with our parents. Living on your own is an amazing experience which brings you personal development.
