MEDICIN FOR EVERYONE It is widely known that, when it comes to rural spaces, the vast majority of doctors do not desire developing their career in such places.
The reasons why it all happen are going to be pointed out a continuation.
Despite the fact that living in the countryside could be seen as a dream come true to many people, it may not be the case for someone whose career ambitions are unlimited.
The thing is, living in a rural area, gives people sometimes the impression of being trapped in a small space.
Besides, technology and progress do not normally arrive on time at these places.
Another issue to have under consideration, is the fact that the economic resources of people who live in rural areas, are far less substantial than the ones of those who live in big cities.
Nevertheless, the importance of an equal and balanced medical system for everyone is beyond doubt.
Having said that, the primary focus of any kind of goberment, should be based on developing the medical and care system of the harmest areas, by investing more money on them and turning those places into more atractive ones.
Last but by no means least, improvements in rural facilities, in general, should be something to take stock of.
Rural life is a luxury that must be preserved.
