In my opinion, experiencing volunteer work is a great requirement for students who want to graduate.
I think that would help students in several ways.
Firstly, from the philanthropy aspect, the youngsters will learn how to help others and raise their collaboration spirit without expecting any payment.
Secondly, the volunteer work experience can be a bright spot in the students' CV, which can be an effective thing in their college or university acceptance.
Moreover, this type of work makes them be in contact with more people with different beliefs, which will teach them to behave in different situations and in my opinion this experience is not easily achievable.
On the other hand, maybe students see it as a burden on their shoulders before graduation but they will find its value when they finish it.
In conclusion, maybe expecting a volunteer activity as a requirement from the students before graduation is a little unfair for a person who needs graduate soon, but this adventure will benefit them in their future life and career.
