The impact of the exercise in a healthy living is a common discussion topic in our times.
The long work journeys and the stressful pace of life don\u00B4t allow us to dedicate more time to our body, but, are there things more important than physical condition?
My answer is yes.
I think mental health is more important than physical condition.
What happens is both are linked.
There are several aspects to cover if we want to mantain our mind in a good condition. Family, food, salary, work-life balance and of course our body.
Getting some excersice is not the only way to mantain our body healthy, we have to care other things too.
To conclude I would like to mention again the importance of the proper balance.
Healthy life is a combination of a training body, peaceful mind, funny and interesting job and stable family life.
If we work in all these dimensions we will enjoy a healthier life!
Nowadays more and more people choose to study English through self-study.
This may be a real challenge, the experience being beyong compare to the classical form of learing, in a classroom with a teacher.
The Writing part was never my strength as I often find it difficult to write a pure genuine text, but I can tell that since I have discovered the free writing tool offered by Cambrige, Write and Improve, my life radically changed!
The thing about this educational website is that it is very handy, offering instant feedback of your writing.
It suggests possible changes in order to get the best out of your work.
Just think that you select your level in English and you are at a click distance from thousands of exam tasks.
How handy is that?
Undoubtedly, you are never alone.
Or at least, you can choose not to be.
If you sign up for a workbook, you are eligible to feedback from other participle and that is how learning becomes collective!
Sharing is caring, isn't it?
Write and Improve is more appealing, more interactive than any other learing platform, as it uses artificial intelligence in the favour of education, which I think that is a tremendous opportunity to challenge young learners to practice more and to get familiar with the exam tasks.
I feel a negative impression about children playing video games.
Children are addicted to the games and cannot manage their times.
I often see the children who are playing games when they stay at school for study, when they have dinner with their family, and so on.
They play games during midnight and they cannot get enough sleep, which may affect to their health.
They need to stare at the screen to play it, therefore their vision become worse.
They play with their friends via video games, and they don't communicate together in the actual world.
I'm afraid that they can't get the communication skill through play.
Some video games are so attractive that children cannot stop playing it.
They may continue to play it for a long time and get a harm effect to their physical and mental health.
If they manage their time and stop to play games in a short time, it doesn't make a tremendous damage, but it is difficult especially for immature people.
Adults have to manage it besides their children.
