I think it is wrong to keep animals in zoos.
If we go to zoos, we can observe the lives of many species of animals directly.
It's an amazing experience for young children and it may make them to notice the importance of living animals.
Some children may choose biology or veterinary medicine as their speciality in the future.
But the lives in zoos are virtual in a way.
Animals in zoos don't get foods, water, and living places themselves.
They eat and drink what they are given and sleep in concrete buildings.
They don't search their spouses and they don't take care of their children themselves.
Human make and take care of their family.
Human keep their health at zoos.
It isn't a natural way for animals.
If we want to see the real animal life, we have to jump into nature, but it takes enormous time and money.
Otherwise, we can feel the essense of animal life in a movie or TV video program.
I think it is a better way to know the real animal life than going to zoos.
