I think the advantages are much more than the disadvantages of studying abroad.
The advantage of studying abroad is that students can have many experiences in foreign countries which they cannot experience in their own country.
They may feel culture gap between these countries.
They notice that there are various types of people and society around the world.
They will know the importance of diversity, and they will respect each other even if each of them has a different philosophy, religion, customs, and culture.
Understanding each other is quite difficult, but young people can adopt the specific situation more easily than old people do.
I think the younger, the better.
The disadvantage of studying abroad is the cost of it.
They need much money for their study and living there.
In addition, they have to leave their home and live themselves apart from their family members.
It may cause some mental problems.
I think that threre are two advantages and one disadvantage of sutudents studying abroad during high school or university.
The first advantage is that you can see several perspectives by studying abroad instead of studying in your country in your early ages.
It would definitely broaden your insight and the way of thinking.
The second one is that having experiences might be beneficial for your career.
For instance, if you wanted to tell your experiences to people who was eager to study abroad, it would be really helpful for you to recognize the difference of education between your country and the country you study.
Whereas, the only disadvantage of studying abroad is that the security.
If you live in a secure place such as Japan, something dangerous might happen during your stay abroad.
So you should be more careful and try to be alart to protect yourself in other country.
