The best holiday for me was a trip to Guam in Feburary, 2013, which our boss brought all employees there as the 10th anniversary since the company established in 2003.
Actually, I was a little nervous before leaving Japan because it was my first trip abroad.
Moreover, I am afraid of heights so it was like a nightmare during a four-hour-flight from Narita Airport to Guam.
However, as soon as getting to the airport there, my best journey got started.
All I could see there such as the Pacific Ocean, beautiful palms, local food, clean and organized hotel rooms, and kind and nice people, was amazing.
I went shopping to buy something for my family and friends, hung around the island, and went to some places where Japanese soldiers were dead during World War II.
I prayed for them.
Anyways, these experiences were so memorable for me, I stayed there for only three days though.
If my English got much better, I would definetely like to visit Guam again and communicate with local people.
Controversy over the incorporating volunteer work in requirements of enrolling in the high schools has been continued over the past years.
Some laud its benefits while others do not.
In this essay I intend to argue about the subject and interefere the advantages and disadvantages.
Due to the research recently has done, teenagares who are used to working volunteer in different fields have more responsibility to accept their role in the society.
As they devote some of hours in a week for sacrificing stuff therefore their understanding of difficult situation are increased and they have more potential to make decision on the crises.
On the other hand, some families prefer to enroll their teenagers in different classes and endow the most advantages of teenagers free times,they think young people should be learn variuos skills for having more option in the future to choose.
By way of conclusion I believe that, as the personalitity of teenagers can be entirely different, parents and school authorities should consider their behavior as the determiner key to help them to improve theirselves and volunteer work although is a sign of a sacrifing soul but must not be a requirement for registration in the high school.
