I think there are mostly three reasons why doctores are few in rural areas.
Firstly, it is difficult to install enough equipments.
I mean it's difficult to distinguish which is installed or not because predicting the patients' character is hard.
Secondly, it is difficult to hire nurses and receptionists.
There are not many expertised nurces and receptionists in the countryside as well as doctors.
Doctors cannot open thier clinic alone.
Thirdly, it is difficult to gather patients.
Many are elderlies in the countryside.
Since they tend to have chronic diseases, they go to a big hospital at city center.
That is why they have a family doctor there, it is hard to gather patients to a town clinic.
Well, I think we can solve it now.
We need to develop online medical care.
Wherever the patients are, they can see a doctor in a city.
It is beneficial for not only the elderlies in the countryside but also everyone who has sick.
These are the all of my opinions.
I hope everyone who needs medical care can get enough treatment.
