Since I have experienced both situations, I can say that living away from my family for a while, has developed my personality and it was a valuable experience for me.
When I was a student in high school, I was living with my family.
On that time, I was not worried about my food or my expenses at all, I knew that when I arrive home, everything is ready for me.
The only thing which was expected for me was only studying.
Furthermore, when I got sick, My parents were taking care of me, and I healed very soon.
But when I decide to get out of my comfort zone and choose to live away from my family, I know that would be an awkward situation but it will help me to become independent.
I have lived 6 years away from my family, and I have learned to manage my expenses and take care of my health and build a strong personality without my parents' help.
However, I am not suggesting this way to all of the students, because it depends on the person's personality and characteristic.
In conclusion, may the experience of living alone during the studying in university is hard, but I think It has this ability to pull out one person's ability and be helpful to be a more independent and responsible person.
