You just graduated and now the evry next part of your life is to begin: university.
But when it coms to the housing situation during this time, the opinions differ.
Some negotiate living at home with your family is the best option, whereas others argue living on your own is the best choice possibly taken.
Actualy both options have their positiv and negative aspects.
On the one hand living on your own obviously helps becoming more confident and reliable but simultaneously responsobility increases a lot.
You have to buy your own groceries, do your lawndry, tidy up, pay your bills and cook for yourself.
Meanwhile you have the opportunity to do whatever you want - if it is not illegal though - and make experiences with being dependent on your own.
On the other hand those responsibilities need a lot of your time, which is less while living with your family.
Your mother might be very gentle and do your lawndry, cook dinner for you and iron your blouses, whereas throwing a party with your new friends could not amaze here the same way as you.
As a conclusion it is important to mention, that everyone prefers different ways of living and there is nothing wrong with it at all.
