There are both positive and negative effects from video games to children.
The benefit of video games is training eye-and-hand coordination which is the basis of many works in children's life.
Moreover, children who play video games have a faster problem solving skill as they expose to new puzzles along the games.
However, the disadventage of video games is much more than the adventage one.
Most families suffer from their children's inappropriate behavior copying from a violent situation in fighting video games which are the most popular type of game.
Many crimes are caused by game players who imitate a character's brutal action.
Another negative effect of video game which mostly affects on preschool children is a language problem causing from limited interpersonal interaction and one-way communication between children and a video screen.
It is normal to see a toddler watching Youtube clips or playing mobile phone games by himself while his parents are also using their phones separately.
Moreover, it causes a long-term health problem, such as near eyesight, muscle sore and constipation, and social problem.
In conclusion, even though video games give children some learning skill, their disadventages affect children's life severely.
Thus, parents must limit their children's playing time to balance benefits and disbenefits causing by playng games.
