Office design Nowadays, due to the lively changes into the office workingenvironment, more and more employers get to crowd all their employees into a large room and their activity is supposed to be accomplished due to a very efficient teamwork.
I believe that all this is nonesense, that this is just a myth that would cover the economy that the employer is making in renting a much cheaper space that will maximize the company's earning.
I truly believe that the emplyees are in their right to benefit from a personal workplace, that will provide them with a quiet and private work experence that will allow them to focus better and be even more productive.
Employers should take notice to the fact that a shared workplace cannot be propely aired and so respiratorical issues appear.
If the place they work in was not jeopardizing their health, the expoyees would work longer and will be beneficial in the long run for te company they work for.
Moreover, working separately will prevent diseases from being spread, as the workers will get less in contact with each other especially during the cold season when the flu is viral.
The less people breathe the same air the better.
In addition, claustrofobic people will feel more safe and their affection will not encounter with their work.
It is proven that a better organisation brings a consistent increase in productivity.
To sum up, each and every emplyee should be provided with his own place in order to focus on his work and to not jeopardize his health and the others'.
