Zoo is where animals from around the world are keeped to display to people.
Animals are shown in a cage which is built imitating a normal habitat of those animals to reduce their stress however it cannot entirely replace the real habitat in nature.
In my opinion, people should not study about animals keeped in zoos with these reasons.
First, when animals are raised in zoos, they change their behaviour to adjust to the new environment.
They would normally hunt their preys or hide themselves in nature but zoos provide them enough foods and safe places to live in comfort.
For example, penguins are waiting to be fed by a zookeeper, and tigers would not hunt anymore.
Moreover, zoos divide each animal separately depended on its specie.
Therefore, there is no interaction between different species.
In nature, animals each species would form a foodchain to control each other's population which cannot be form in zoo's environment.
In conclusion, it is the best to have animals roming free in nature.
Zoo is not a proper place for learning about animals.
Studying abroad have both good and bad points.
Many students choose their school in a foreign country to get more opportunity to improve their knowledge and language.
Furthermore, students who have graduated from high school tend to be accepted into that country's university more.
They can adapt to their new environment and friends easier than students who never study abroad.
On the other hand, study abroad requires more budget for living and school expense even if students get a scholarship.
Moreover, some university does not accept a foreign student in the same course as its country's local student because of a language barrier.
So, when students come back to their home country, some of them don't meet a job's knowledge requirement or are lack of experience in working in a local company.
Therefore, every student should think carefully before they apply to a university abroad so that they would get more good experience than a disadvantage.
