Medical doctors' workplace After some tough years of studying in order to become a reputable doctor that not only are they make in order to achieve a better statute, but also to acomplish one's wish to live a comfortable life it is unlikely that a medical school graduate to have prospects about working in a deprived area.
First and foremost, if the salary was equal for each and every health professional no matter the place he choose to work in, there would be more willing to jeopardize their social life in order to work in much havier conditions and with people poorly educated.
A respectable wage is a great motivation to balance this statistic.
In addition to the forementioned, the government should be looking deeply into introducing more priviledges to those heroes.
Some of the doctors are urged to get to people who are further isolated, which makes a real challenge especially during cold seasons.
Those doctors should get provided transport in order to move around freely and also more furlough that will be beneficial to their mental and physical health.
Moreover, they should get the best accomodation possible during their stay in the rural area in order to show how much we appreciate their daily efforts.
To sum up, the sacrifices the doctors make being apart their families and an active social life should be compensated with a more attractice wage and a generous place to stay.
