There is no accuse about how exercise is important to our lives.
Human's body needs energy and enough activity to burn it out to maintain a normal physiology.
However, exercise is not the most important thing for our health.
In fact, human needs the 4 most important factor to survive, that are foods, shelters, clothes and medications.
Also, our wellness is varied due to the difference of these factors.
We need food and water to build up energy and prevent a disease.
Many kinds of food are considered as a medicine to reduce an inflammation or improve an immunity.
There is a trend, nowadays, of eating 'clean food' believed to prevent a disease as well as a trend of daily exercise.
Some food is put into a 'junk food' categorie which means it damages a health of a person who consumes it.
In conclusion, exercise is important to our health but there are many things that are more important than it.
Therefore, we need to focus not only on exercising but also other things to maintain our good health, too.
