The majority of people consider that doing exercises is important for their health and they are not wrong.
However, there are other things which are as or more important than exercising.
Firstly, you should eat a healthy diet.
This means eating a variety of food poor in fats and sugar.
Someone's diet is very important if they want to live healthy.
Although a little junk food, rich in fats and sugar, from time to time does not hurt anybody, it should be eaten as rarely as possible because the carbohydrates affect the good working of the human body.
Secondly, it is also important to have an organised lifestyle, with eight hours of sleep and eating regularly.
More organised someone's life is, healthier he is because, with a routine, the body get used with working normal and efficient.
Moreover, it has been scientifically proved that emotions have a lot to do with people's health.
For example, stress affects someone's liver while sadness affects humans' lungs and so on.
So being happy and think positively also contributes to people's health.
That is why it is important to be pleased with the things you do.
In my view, exercise is important for our health but it is not the most important thing.
If you are too busy or tired after a day at work it is not necessarily to exhaust yourself exercising, instead you could something that relax you and makes you happy.
