Write and Improve is an English site in the internet where everyone can practice and improve their writing skills.
I have first heard of this site from my English teacher when she was trying to convice me and my classmates to write with more confidence in English.
I must admit that I was not sure about it at first.
All of this because I didn't considered myself very keen on writing, especially in another language than \u00EEn my native one.
Although I was sceptic about this, I decided to give it a try.
At first I was surprised by the variety of types of exercises which I could find on Write and Improve.
I hadn't expected it.
It was not difficult to choose a task which inspired me to write.
I was fascinated.
Once I had started I could not stop but I had to owing to the limited number of words because this site also helps you to decide how much you should write for every task.
Moreover, after you finished you can press on the Check button and the site will automatically verify and mark your work.
All considered, I would certainly recommend Write and Improve not only to anyone who wants to improve their writing skills but also to those who write only for fun.
The site is well structured and offers a variety of tasks from which to choose which inspires you most.
Studying music Nowadays music is everywhere around us.
Music not only drives people a pleasant vibe, but it also takes part in inducing concentration.
Music used to be very well apreciated in the aristocratic society and if the children mastered a musical instrument it brought a distinctive honour to the family, being a trace of a high-chosen education and wealth.
Why shouldn't it still be a mandatory subject at school?
Music is a very fine science, as it develops the cognitive abilities.
Children will develop an inner intelligence and a stronger sense of responsability.
It is proven that if a child takes up a musical instrument at an early age, he will get more shots at a tremendous grow.
Studying music tenders an auspicious behaviour and elegance in gestures, essential for a young person who is looking forward to be part of a diplomatic circle and to gain a reputable statute in society.
It is also well known that music offers a wide range of tremendous knowledge.
For instance, it is a smooth alternation of Mathematics and Physics, as it teaches measurements and also the power and the fluctuation of the sound.
As a result, it may be an excellent practical aplication of those school subjects, representing an entertaining way to understand them.
To sum up, I do not see how sudying music would be detrimental to a young man's development, as it plays a beneficial role in gaining the skills neccesary to become a respectable adult.
Every season more wonderful than the others but each special in their own particular way.
From the lively spring to the cold wet winter, I like every each of them because I am looking forward to seeing how mother earth changes every year.
However, I do have one favourite season and that is winter.
In my country, at winter time, the temperatures are usually below 0 degrees.
The weather is wet and it is snowing a lot.
Sometimes the layer of snow can reach two meters height.
The sun is not as brightly as it is in summer, therefore there is not much light neither.
Also the sun sets earlier, so the day time is shorter than the night time.
Despite all the things above, winter is still my favourite season of all year. Mostly because I love the cold but I think I can dare to say that even a human being who doesn't like it could enjoy winter.
In this season there are a lot of festivities and celebrations.
For example on the first of December it is Romania's National Day, Christmas is also celebrated at winter time, New Year, the Valentine's Day and a lot of others lovely days.
However, being out while it is snowing and trying to catch a snowflake with your tongue or in your hand compares with nothing else.
All in all, these are the majority of reasons why I consider winter is the best season of all year.
But, of course, the Christmas movies, which I adore, could have contributed a little to this.
Some students choose to study in foreign country while they are still in highschool or at the university.
To start we will speak about the advantages of studying abroad.
Then we will bring attention to the disadvantages.
Finally I will give you my personal opinion on the matter.
First and foremost, there are a lot of advantages for students who study in another country for a time.
As a matter of fact, they will discover a lot of things such as new cultures, new habits, and new people.
Some of them will learn a new language as French, English, Spanish or even Chinese.
The skills they will develop abroad will be a great help for later.
Futhermore students whom study abroad will become more independant from their parents and family.
Last but not least, they will an incredible experience that will remain for the rest of their lives.
At first sight, it seems there is no disadvantages of studying in a foreing contry.
That's not true.
Some students might feel desoriented. Young students in particular when they are far from their parents.
To some extent the youngs one might find difficult to fit in another counrty.
For instance, they can be disturbed with the local food or if they can't communicate easily.
To my views, studying abroad is a personal choice, and it depends on your attitude.
On the one hand, some people aren't meant to travel the worl.
They feel more confortable at home.
On the other hand are driven by the need of discovering new cultures.
They need to live wildly.
To sum, there are great advantages to study abroad for a time during high school or university.
But not everyone can suit it.
