A long life Nowadays we live in a world of teribilism and unconscience.
There are less wise people that it used to.
Life is the most precious gift that can be recived and I believe that it should be lived at the fullest, but taken in abstemious shots.
First and foremost, life is more enjoyable when you enjoy each and every small moment of happiness it offers.
It is proven that if we live our life sober, we are more likely to live longer and to get more time to have it all.
A live spent in peace and in harmony is something that many wish for, but few people actually achieve this spiritual fulfilling.
If you had a lovely family and a decent income, why would you work your fingers to the bone for more revnues?
Money cannot buy joy.
In addition to the forementioned, an intense life is a tumultous life that is very likely to end up earlier and worse.
For instance, it is a pity how many rebelious young people die in car crashes due to their love for high speeding.
Moreover, an exhausting career and countless white nights will be detrimental to one's health and will only bring pain and suffrance.
Life is more precious than to be lived like that.
Consequently, a busy schedule also neglects the family like, tremendous moments that are irreversible.
To sume up, the biggest achievement in life is to be at peace at the end of it, build memories to be remembered and to avoid as much as possible the self-harm cause by vices.
