Good morning, I am writing to in case of your future decision about banning the use of mobile phones on public transport and in shops and restaurants.
In my opinion decision like this is too restictive for people living in our town.
I think this decision is also bad for many reasons.
First of all, especially nowadys mobile phones are not only use for calling and messaging.
For many people mobile phone is used as a calendar, notebook, calculator and stuff like that.
Thanks to the Internet they can also check for example bus departures or shops opening hours.
On public transport people like to relax and doing things which can help them to kill the time.
In their mobile phone they can read newses, listen to music, read books, play vidoe games and many other things.
So that is the next good example in my opinion.
Let's see the shops.
There are many reasons for you need use your mobile phone there.
Many people have a shopping list in their mobile phones.
If you do not have the shopping list you may forget something.
If you forget something you have to maybe call somebody who remind you about it.
Next place is restaurant.
I think there using mobile phone is not neccesary but there is some group of people who need to be always in touch.
I think my arguments are strong and you will change your decision quickly.
Best regards. Pat
Living is a privilege not everyone is completely aware of, in spite of this awarness everyone wants to live up to the fullest.
The question is, what way is the right way to live your life.
Therefore the next question arises: A long life until 100 years old or a shorter life but much more intense.
For me the answer is obvious, as i chose my goals from very early on.
I want to achieve something that stays ,after I no longer live.
Subsequently the more time I have, the higher is the chance of accomplishing it.
100 years is a tremendously long period of time and the chances of getting ill at some point of this, are comparatively high, why you should always treat your body the best possible way.
Then you can use those years effectively for whatever goal you have set yourself.
Another reason for chosing the longer period of time, is the history you have, as nearly no one gets that old, you have a lot to tell and to experience in the first place of course.
Imagine getting a child, then becoming a grandparent and afterwards even a grand-grandparent.
Is there anything more fullfilling than love?
Moreovere, exquisit things are to be explored, memories to be made and stories to be told.
In conclusion, regarding to the shorter life, there are reasons for chosing this one two, but those for the longer one overweight by far.
