Which is the best for students to have the same teacher for several years or to have new teachers each year?
This question sometimes has debated in people who are interesting in Education.
Both sides have benefits, but I believe that it is good for almost all students to have new teachers each year.
In real life, we met a lot of different people, and they have varieties of backgrounds.
Children have to learn about dealing with different people through school life.
Having new teachers each year can help students learn about dealing with unfamiliar people and handling change.
Hiroki Murakami, who is my coworker, was born in an outside city, and there is only one small elementary school where the number of teachers was limited.
Therefore, he never experienced changing teachers in elementary school.
After entering middle school, he experienced to have new teachers each year.
He said that it was frustrated at first because he had to remember new teachers' characters and their routines, but he learned about dealing with new people through that experience.
His world might be more small one if not experienced it.
Having new teachers each year has more benefits to touch various ideas from different people.
It is comfortable to spend time with the same members, such as familiar friends and adults who you like.
It sometimes leads to close their world in a small society.
Getting new teachers can help students touch new ideas and make their world broaden.
Students can learn how to deal with others in a community by going to school.
Having many teachers can help them experience to develop the flexibility to others and changes.
For this reason, It is good for them to have new teachers every year.
