Now he hate music because his bad experience.
All things considered it seems to me that the students should be educated in the theory of music but they shouldn't be forced to play any musical instument.
My reasons for learning English There are many reasons to learn English, and everyone might have a different point of view.
To begin with, I will give you the reasons that led me to learn English a few years ago.
Additionnaly, I will tell you why it matters to me.
To start with, I wasn't very interested in learning English when I was a young girl.
I believed it was useless.
At the age of fifteen I changed my mind for crying out loud !
The main reason to learn english was to be able to watch American's movie in their original version.
As a matter of fact, I was a huge fan of Buffy, the vampire slayer and it was important to me to hear their voice without coverage.
Of course, I used subtitles.
Furthermore when I arrived in college, I had to take English classes.
It made me understand how necesary it was to improve my writing and speaking ability. Not only to be able to graduate but also because a lot of campany values it.
Last but not least, I love to travel, and I am very interesting in learning about other countries.
To speak English offers me the possibility to communicate easily with foreigners.
Today Knowing English is crucial for any worker.
So it's why I am studying English.
Articles, manuals are all in English.
Some of them are in my native language.
With the globalization, we need to work with foreign professionals.
So how are we going to comunicate if we don't speak English.
Many times they aren't native spoken English, many of them are Chinese, Germans, Spanish, so it's important to have a language in commom.
This language is English.
If I am not wrong, there are more English speaker who are non-native than native English speaker.
Of course, if you work in some rare areas that other languages are not important, so it's not important to learn.
But if you are in this situation and like to travel abroad, so knowing English is very important.
Travel companies always have insructions in English.
So if you wouldn't like to stay behind, study English!
