In 60th decade, traveling around the world was a utopian dream.
There was few flights and they were very expansive.
Therefore, the knowledge about the universal language (English) didn't be a commum practice in schools around the world.
However, with the power of globalization, traveling to several countries in the same life became a possible dream.
The amount of flights increased - side by side with your market demands - and the traveling culture has been spread as a new hobbie and a synonymous of happiness.
Finally, we arived to the 21st centure and we wondering: in the next years, will I traveling more?
It will become cheaper?
The answer, for me, it is all yes.
In a increasingly connected world, the boders will decrease.
On the other hand, I'm scary about the loss of culture shock between countries.
First of all, we need put in our bags just the wills and leaving at home the colonizing instinct that unfortunately still lives an our society.
When I was a child at school, during the music class, we learnt songs to sing at the end-year concert.
It was funny, because our teachers taught us new words and ballets.
When we grew older sometimes it happened to sing musical song, with solist voices: there were contents to assign roles. Once I won and I became the protagonist.
I was the happiest child ever.
When I was a girl, at the secondary school, during the music class we listend to classic music, as Mozart, Beethoven, Bach or Puccini, and we studied the history of the operas, as the Aida, the Traviata or the Turandot.
We also studied how to play melodies with the flauto, as "jingle balls" or "alleluia alleluia."
Oltough studying music was funny when I was a child, when I grew up it became a complete waste of time.
My teacher didn't take his job seriously and most times we wasted our lessons talking about other things or studying other school subjects.
The hours used to study music can be useful when children are still little, because they need to have fun and to understand which are their interests.
When children grow up, time should be spent in better ways.
For example in schools could be introduced again the study of our Costituzione, whose articles should be known by every Italian citizen, or civical education, whose knowledge is really missing, because people have lost their good common sence.
Morever, it could be developped geography taughts, because people, especially the young ones, ignore what they are surraunded about.
They don't know neither that Rome is our capital, nor that Pisa has the Leaning Tower, nor that Po, Arno and Tevere are our biggest rivers.
