On many schools children learn how write an essay, how to solve a mathematical problem and many other important subjects.
All this subjects are meant to impart the children the skills and the knowlegde that they need for their foreseeable future and education.
For some children it also helps to determine their hobbies.
With other words why can be music a part of each school curriculum.
I believe that studyig music supplies many advantages for children.
In this essay I will provide evidents that endorse studying music on school.
Firstly, studying music on school gives children the oppurtunity to discover their music talents.
There are many children who their home situation do not enable them to come in contact with music.
Further, there are children who parents cannot afford the instruments that they need to perform some kind of music.
For these children school is a good place to discover whether music is a subject they want to specialize or no.
Secondly, studying music on school helps children to develop social and creativity skills.
Many schools who impart music lessons gives also the children the chance to stablish their own music groups.
Through this many children will learn how to work with other people, but also how to deal with problems like quarrels.
Another vantage of studying music on schools is that music will incentivize the child's creativity, because children have the chance to write their own songs and to provide groups peformance.
To conclude, it is very obvious that studying music provides many vantages for children and that music is even important as other school subjects like history and Biology, because children learn needed social and creativy skills.
I think it is important to tell the truth in general.
However, it is sometimes necessary to tell a lie, too.
There are situations in which it is harmful for others to tell the truth.
For example, suppose that your friends ask you about what you think of their clothes.
Even if you think they are bad, you will praise their style.
In this situation, it may annoy your friends to tell them your opinion frankly.
In another example, if you are not satisfied with a gift from your friends, you will not complain about it.
After all, you should avoid disturbing others' feeling by telling them your true feelings.
Although you should not be sometimes honest, it is significant to tell others the truth otherwise.
If you choose not to be honest, it may lead to undesirable consequence.
For instance, if you concealed making mistakes in your company, it would lose trust from others owing to your faults.
This is a problem not only for you but also for both your colleague and your boss.
Perhaps your boss might have to resign his post to take responsibility for the distrust.
Thus, you should not tell a lie to others in the situation which it harms others.
In conclusion, it is ever acceptable to tell a lie.
However, it depends on the situation.
It is most important to distinguish the situation you should tell a lie from the one you should not.
