Dear Major Muller, I'm writing to ask you to dismiss the idea of banning the use of mobile phones on public transport and in shops and restaurants.
Mobile phones are an important part of our lifes these days.
While we are using the public transport they can help us to catch up with the latest news or stay in contact with our friends.
Thesedays there are also a wallet.
Some people have their creditcard on there phone or their ticket for the public transport.
I understand that it can be annoying if someone is having a phone call, while being in a restaurant or is using the public transport, but in world where everything is connected that the price we have to pay.
If our town were to ban the use of mobile phones in public transport or in shops and restaurants we would disconnect our town from the world.
Furthermore some people would use their car instade of the public transport.
This would lead to more traffic, which is bad for the environment.
But most importantly it is more dangerous if people us their phone while they are driving than if they would use it in public transport.
As there is no harm done to anyone, it makes no sense to ban the use of mobile phones in public transport or in restaurants and shops.
I appreciate all that you do for our city.
Sincerely, Ben Singer
First and foremost, digitalisation had brough us many changes and challenges.
Our environment had drastically evolved and no realm had been left aside.
In the situation, what about schools ?
How will they be in the future ?
Will they still be the same ?
First of all, I will tell you why I believe schools will be different in a near future.
However I will explain you why some things will remain the same.
To begin with, digitalisation had enter in our life at any stage.
As a matter of fact, we now have access to a large range of skills and tools.
Smartphones, computers and tablets are made available for everyone.
Additionally artificial intelligence can provide new way of learning.
Knowing that, I think, the school of the future will use those differents applications to reinvente itself and offer new possibilities.
For example, screens could be implemented on desk boards.
Furthermore, kids need to be able to use any technological devices easily.
Not only is it a way to fit the world but also is it essential to find a work.
Moreover, I believe, in just a few years from now, students won't need to attend classrooms anymore.
Indeed, I think e-learning will become extremely popular.
Actually, a lot of business schools are already using it and it an outstanding sucess, for crying out loud!
However, I believe some aspects will still be the same.
For instance, there will still be teachers, and grades.
Last but not least, I believe human contact is a need for young children and it can't be replaced by artificial intelligence.
Finally, all those transformations will take some time.
Better late than never.
