I would live a shorter life rather a long life.
There are two reasons why I think so.
First, I cannot be viable during all my lifetime.
At the terminal of my life, I will not be active like before, and I can only stay at a hospital.
I cannot endure the situation that I manage to live with aids of medicine.
I would like to perform something until my life is ended.
Even more, we can enjoy our freedom because it is limited by the surroundings.
If I lived in a long life, I would have few things to do and would be bored with my freedom.
Second, in my opinion, shorter life is more stimulating than longer one.
As I become older, I will experience less owing to physical restriction.
It seems to me that people face too many things between in their 20s and in their 50s.
Therefore, unless I would die in my twenties, I could have variable experience.
I could become satisfied with it.
Moreover, I set my life plan in which I will be dead in my seventies.
Considering the scheme, I am willing to try anything as long as I am viable.
It results in making me busy, but at the same time I can enjoy my time more than others.
In conclusion, I prefer living a shorter life to living a longer life.
It is significant for me to be active during my lifetime.
Thus, I always make much effort for fulfilling my life.
