First of all I would like to say that I am not university student yet.
That means that my opinion is not based on my own experience.
Firstly, life of university students might be hard and many students spent with their school more than 40 hours per week which is usual work time in Czech republic.
With this in mind, it would be very hard for some students to do a job.
I believe that the parents ought to support their children financially during their study.
The imprortant question is whether should the student live at home.
In my opinion, it is subjective.
The main adventige of living with parents could be the fact that you have really great background and it is cheaper than living on your own.
On the other hand when you decide to live alone or with your friends you will probably become more responsible and independent.
Furthermore, I believe that staying too long with your parents is no good for your relationship and your psychological development.
All things considered, I think that everyone should choose for himself and both choises are all right.
First and foremost, globalisation and digitalisation had brought many changes in our world, for crying out loud!
They changed the way we work, we travel and communicate.
For instance low-cost airlines companies appaered and home office had become common knowledge.
Better late than never.
Not only is it more important than it used to be but also is it an obligation in some cases.
First of all, I will tell you why I believe it is essential to speak a foreign langauge in 2020.
Then, I will shade my views regarding some aspects.
To begin with, it had become more and more difficult to find a job nowadays.
Repeated crises transformed the world.
It had become particularly difficult to reach a company expectation.
Actually, major market brands are asking people to be fluent in another language as English, Spanish, or Chinese.
It might sound demanding but this is the way it works.
Moreover, people are travelling way more than they used to do.
For example, a lot of students go for a world tour after finishing their degree.
In this case, it is better if not obligatory to speak English in order to able to communicate with foreigners.
Last but not least, some people are interested in learning about another language because it's part of a country culture.
Notwithstanding, in my opinion it is important to discover a different language than its native one, I believe it also depends on your way of living.
Indeed, if someone don't like to travel or is not interested in working in a international company there is no need to spend time on learning about another language.
I believe, it matters to shed light on different point of view.
