Dear Town Council, I think banning the use of mobile phones on public transport and in shops and restaurants is not a good idea at all.
As mobile phones have been near humans for over two decades and these electronic devices can be taken anywhere and can be opened within seconds.
Banning would result in people taking laptops everywhere they go and also use laptops everytime, which would again lead to a mass protest.
As the digital age grows, mobile phones get better and advanced than other devices.
As the name suggests 'mobile phone', people can take it anywhere without an additional 2.3 kg.
Imagine this, people taking laptops everywhere they go.
Restaurants, shops, restaurants and public transports.
Some people would just be using the laptops to navigate and call and even take photos.
That would be awkward to a normal mobile phone user as laptops can only be used as selfies and when not held nicely, it may drop and get damaged.
While on the other hand, mobile phones can be used for both selfies and normal photos.
As other devices are mostly just for work, school and others, mobile phones can do everything.
They can be used for work, banking, researching and more.
Consider this wheter mobile phones should be banned or not.
If mobile phones are banned it would lead to a huge protest which could make most of the high ranking workers to resign from office.
I disagree with it.
There are three reasons why I oppose that opinion.
First, it is not necessarily limited to sport activities to keep them healthy.
Running or doing yoga can replace them.
Some students and children will prefer doing such exercises to playing other sports.
If universities and schools made their students exercise in their facilities, it would be difficult to fulfill all students' favors.
Some students would not be satisfied with the schools' policies.
However, if the schools let their students exercise outside, it would be also hard to manage the students' activities.
Briefly, it is absurd from scratch to force students to do exercises regularly.
Second, there is little scientific evidence to support the frequency of playing sports.
Is it really enough to do exercise three times a week?
This opinion explains nothing about how many hours we should exercise.
At least, those who are in favor of this opinion should provide information about the basis of their statement.
In my opinion, we cannot improve the lack of physical activities by imposing unreliable evidence on students.
Third, I think it is not always good to make much effort to become healthier.
It is true that there may be no problem for many people to be forced physical activities.
However, it is not the case for some people with disabilities.
Such people cannot participate in sports as well as ordinary people.
To improve our inactive lifestyle, we only have to increase the opportunities of exercise.
It is appropriate for only healthy people, and this idea utterly ignores people who are willing to exercise but cannot do.
If the given opinion pervades among a lot of universities and schools, it will be natural to get rid of people with disabilities.
Thus, I am against this opinion.
It seems to me that this opinion is not persuasive and dangerous.
Therefore, I never admit it.
In my opinion, transport sector was highly hit with the currently pandemic.
Therefore, this sector will need to be more ecologic.
For me, in the future, people will travel with plane or with train because it will be more fast and safe.
Planes could go to any cities in less 2 hours thanks to supersonic technologies.
Of course, people still take boats but only for the pleasure.
Indeed, in our future society, take a boat for travel will not be ecologic with the use of petrol.
Therefore, a majority of people will take the train for the same reasons that they will take planes, the speed.
In the future, they only will take transport for the speed and not for the landscape.
Of course, cars would be always used but only electric cars.
To conclude, the future of travel will combine two factors, ecology and speed.
These will be necessary to protect our earth and travel in our planet.
