In this days, balancing between practical work and theoretical is one of the most important conflict in education system.
One program which is offered by specialists is involving students in practical work by volunteer work.
Community service has some pros and cons and considering these is important to make a good decision for teenagers.
At first, working in a volunteer environment in high school can help students to improve their skills.
Working as a volunteer increase their confidence and prepare them for doing real job.
In addition, learning work ethic is one of the most important aim of doing community service.
Student learn to how they can help other people.
Volunteers\u2019 teacher mostly are patient and energetic people.
These characteristics help teenagers to change their bad behaviors and develop their passions and ingenuities.
On the other hand, volunteer work can unsettle students' balance of time management.
Student must deal with doing homework, sporting, preparing for exams and practical work.
Generally, community service lacks structure and this can lead students to confuse in managing their time.
Besides, some volunteer atmospheres are unsafe and uncertain.
People who work in these places can be different and unknown.
So, finding a good environment is important and parents and the school\u2019s staff must consider it precisely.
In conclusion, developing social and professional skills are valuable and useful for students.
Achieving these goals needs practical plan and considering enough time in school. Therefore, community service has some significant advantages for teenage students.
Disadvantages of volunteer work are less important than its goodness.
By helping peers to manage their time and providing secure surrounding can reinforce volunteer plans in high schools.
Hence, students are able to be professional people in the society after finishing high school.
