Travelling as we know it and did it for decades will come to an end.
Due to the ongoing discussion about the environmental costs of easy travelling things start to change.
In future fewer people will use cheap flights for unnecessary weekend trips into sunny spots.
More and more people will become conscious and will try to avoid stress on the environment when starting over for holidays.
So, having fun in the neighbourhood, for example by doing bycicle tours or walking and hiking will see a renaissance.
This also will strenghten the rural economy, so that money could be spend to develop localm infrastructure and local offers.
This will lead to a broader variety of possibillitiies.
In the end, lots of people will find options for their vacation nearby.
Spending gallons of kerosine and polluting the sky and environment to allow people to have weekends in spain for less than 30 \u20AC will soon be a thing of the past.
So I hope.
