As an English\u2019s learner, I usually look for a new tool that enable me to improve my English level.
recently, I discovered "Write and Improve" which is a new tool for learning English differently.
I highly appreciate this new a useful resource.
Not only is it a complete tool, but also, it's easy to use it.
What I appreciate a lot in "write and improve" is the different functionalities that you can use to increase our ability to write essay as well as a report with following many either concrete advices or instructions.
The main features that this original tool offers us is certainly the corrections that it provides us when we finish each exercise of writing.
In addition, when you use this original tool, you can easily follow your own progression through the activities and also you to have an idea about your real level on writing.
The only the only gap that I noticed in this tool is the fact that there is no interactivity between writer and his corrector.
To sum up, I highly recommend this helpful tool for his relevance.
since I started his using, I continue to discover and enjoy all the elements embedded in it.
What is the difference between working in cities and working in rural areas?
for most medical doctors the diffecnce is huge and as weird as sounds, all of them prefer to work in cities.
They put forward several arguments to justify their choices.
at first, they think that in cities they could have much customers rather than if they work in rural areas.
For example, some of them claims that they can earn three times what they can earn in small villages.
Some other doctors justifie their choice by presenting other arguments: existense of high school; availability of garden or cinemas in cities.
In my pinion , neither these arguments are strong nor they are convincing bacause Working in the rural areas or in the villages is so helpful for communitiesas well as for citizens.
To sum up, I have a great esteem for doctors who prefer to sacrify their self centred and eventually accept to help people living in rural areas.
Living in a village or near the city can be very nice, because you have fresh air, neigbours you know and quite atmosphere.
But there is one big problem about living in the rural areas: there is always a deficite of medical doctors.
There are many reasons for this phenomenon.
On of them is that people are mostly interested in growth of their career.
And in a big city they have better chance for it.
They can start in a little hospital and by working hard and making enough connections they maybe can open their own practice and earn much money.
Another important point is that children and husbands or wifes of doctors have more possibilities to find a job or to go to an excellent school or university in a bigger city than in a village.
In rural areas there is always only one school children have to go or they must spend an hour or longer everyday to participate the school in the neighbour place.
I think that a good option to spread medical doctors through the whole landscape equable is too improve infrastructure in rual areas, so people living there will not feel themselves isolated and it will be more attractive for everyone to move to rural areas than to metropolises.
