Taking care of animals is always attractive to people.
Environmental concern makes people to find the ways to keep species safe.
But preserving animals in the zoos or in nature is the disagreement between the different group.
Some people believe animals belong to natural surrounding and the others prefer to visit animals in the zoos.
In my opinion, there are some reasons for both arguments but visiting species in nature is more acceptable for me.
Being in a secure space is the first reason for maintaining animals in the zoos.
Some people believe humans can protect species which are in the danger by putting them in the cage.
In addition, bringing animals in the zoos is the best way to educate people about their habitat.
Researching about animals\u2019 behaviors and how to treat illnesses is easier in the zoos.
On the other hands, the species suffer from physically and mentally problems because they are forbidden being in nature.
Space in the zoos is not the same as in nature for them.
Mental problems cause stress for animals and they may die earlier than when they live in a natural environment.
Also, keeping animals in the small cage ruins their freedom.
They cannot function like living in nature.
In conclusion, one stage of overcoming nature is dealing with wild species.
Some people prefer to keeping animals in the zoos to control and knowing about them.
But the others enjoying to see animals be free and live in somewhere they belong.
I also prefer to see animals in their natural environment and respect their freedom.
Last week I went on a holiday to Vancouver city in western Canada.
It was the best holiday I ever had and it was full of joyfullness and experience.
I have learnt so many things.
Vancouver is a bustling metroplis full of life.
I visited wonderful places such as Stanely park, Gas town and the Museum of Vancouver, and I saw incredible things.
I can say, those were the most astonishing places I have ever been to.
I aslo gave myself a chance to experince the landscapes, so I went 30 minutes away from vancouver downtown to be in Capilano suspension bridge park to experience fresh breathe.
In the Museum of Vancouver I took lots of pictures for the world war II veterans and I also read a little bit about the history of that place.
What I like most in Vancouver is the cultural diversity and open-mindedness of its people - they are very welcoming and friendly.
In addition, the nightlife is Vancouver is incomparable to other cities in the world, it is very special for restaurents and cafes.
I really fall in love with this fun-loving city and I wish I will have the chance to visit again.
