As a child everyone learns always to tell the truth.
But is it right option to do it everytime without exceptions?
I think that lies always come up.
At first you can think that lying can be convinient.
But often it has the same scenario: you beginn with a little lie about something unimportant, but with the time it grows bigger and bigger and at the end it will brust, because it is impossible to think about every detail and to remeber everything you had ever said.
For example you lie to your frient about being sick, so your can not go to his or her party.
Then you have to think out what kind of sickness it is, where does it come from, how long do you have this and so far.
And in some particular point you lies will break down.
And you have a big argue with your friend about everything you said to him, what was not true.
But on the other hand, if you will tell everyone the truth, you can not live in a community.
Sometimes you have to lie to stay polite or to motivate someone.
To be honestly with everyone about everything will make only trouble.
For example if your fellow asks you how you like her dress. It is polite to say that it is good instesd of telling her the truth that you do not like her look.
In summery I think that a question about when you have to be honestly and when not is a very complex topic.
