Should computers and tablets completely replace books in schools and universities?
This question is what some teachers may think.
Well, of course, both of them have advantages and disadvantages.
Of course, I think that idea is not correct.
We need libraries so that we can improve ourselves and is beneficial for our health.
Well firstly, the welfare of using computers and tablet.
Using the internet is the easiest way to search.
And it is also very agile!
But if you depend on it too much, you will get addicted to it.
And if you get addicted to the internet, it is very difficult to get back to normal.
Looking at the screen can also very bad for your eyes!
And if you look at the screen too much, it will affect your health.
Secondly, the advantages of using books.
Using books may be slow and hard to find, but it is the best way to learn!
You can improve your reading skills and your understanding skills.
And of course, your eyes won't get as bad as using computers or tablets.
