Going to university is a new big step in everyone\u00B4s life.
And a lot of freshman students think that they are only students when they move out of their parents\u00B4 house.
But it it realy so?
I think that nowaday it is common that young people rent their own flat or room when they begin their education in the university.
And this has often a good reason: Not every city has universities and not every university has the same directions.
For example if you want to study biotechlogy, you will have to go to university which offers suitable courses.
And if this university is in another city, your best option is to move to this place.
Now by mobility being more convenient it is easier to get to another city and it is getting normal that everyone moves out for study.
But on the other hand if you need less than an hour to your study place by train or bus from your parents\u00B4 house, I do not think that it is nessesary for you to change you flat.
Staying at your parents\u00B4place you can save a lot of money and it is very convenient to have your mum who makes your laundary and cooks food for you.
In summary I think that you do not have to move out without good reasons, because not through changing your flat you become a real student.
