Recently surfing the Internet I discovered Write and Improve, which is an online platform to improve English writing.
Write and Improve is a very useful tool, because it offers the possibility to practise English for free.
It is very inclusive because every English learner can use it, no matter their level.
There are exercises both for those who are beginning and for those who already speak Enlgish pretty well.
In this way, everyone can follow a personal pattern and choose their own goals to achive.
Infacts, there are areas with exercises to get several English Certifications, such as IELTS Academics or B2 First.
Write and Improve is so useful because writings can be checked in real time by the algorithm where it is based on.
Mistakens and mispellings are immediately individuated so that the student can fix them in real time.
Moreover, yellow highlights incorrect sentences using two different shades: the lighter one is for those sentences which have a few mistakes in their construptions, the darker one is for those sentences which are completely wrong.
This part is probably the only one of Write and Improve which should really be improved: it would be very helpful if, after higlighting an incorrect sencence, it suggested a way to make it better and more fluid.
Despite this little difect, Write and Improve is an optime tool to improve English and I strongly reconmend to use it to everyone English learner, from the beginners to the advanced ones.
In fact, exercise is important for our health, but there are other things that are more important than only doing exercise.
Our health is affected severely by external stimulus such as stress, anxiety and depression, which we may encounter in our day-to-day life.
Due to the increasing life demands, people are busier at work to meets these life demands.
As a result, problems like stress, anxiety and depression may occur making poor work-life balance; which has very negative effects on our health.
Exercise alone can never be the solution towards healthy body unless we find peace of mind.
we need to do practices that make us happy all the day.
In addition, our day should be full of various activities so that we do not get bored.
For example, having time to go out with friends for fun is an interesting idea that boosts our peace of mind.
Furthermore, taking up a new hobby like singing or playing guitar or piano or doing yoga are all nice activities that promote our mental and physical health.
There are plenty of activities that everybody finds a part of him/her in them.
Doing these activities along with exercise promotes our health.
