Dear Sir/Madam I would like to share with you my thoughts about town council's plan of banning mobile phones in public places like shops and restaurants.
In my humble opinion such proporsal has much more drawbacks than positive aspects.
I am aware of the fact that nowadays people lifestyle rely on mobile phones and this is indisputable that in some cases we very clearly overuse them.
Therefore some poeple claim that this may leads to pretty serious consequences like inability to understand social interactions.
It seems to me that this is rather extremely rare situations so that I believe we should not count it as a solid reason to implement above mentioned ban.
There are also opinions that using mobile phones can disturb other passengers on buses or clients in restaurants and shops.
Undoubtly we could find examples of such situations but I think it is too much generalisations.
I strongly believe that most people know how to behave in a way that does not hassle other human beings, even if they acquire mobile phone.
In summary I do not find that there are any sufficient reason to claim that ban on mobile phones in public places is necessary.
Some people might dislike modern devices, but it is still not enough to limit liberty of others.
We should live according to the rule live and let live.
