LEARNING HOW TO PLAY AN INSTRUMENT Music is often said not to be an important subject at school, but I could not disagree more.
The reasons why I consider music as useful knowledge are explained below: It goes without saying that music is one of the most old forms of comunication for human beings and no matter which your mother tongue is, everybody can understand the message that every piece of music contains.
Another point to take into account is that you can develope your creativity by learning music, especcially when it comes to playing an instrument.
By learning how to play an instrument not only can you understand better that universal language, but also you will value and understand better the effor it requires.
In my humble opinion, everybody should know how difficult it is to compose music, just like we learn the difficulty the rest of the subjects have.
Music is one of the oldest comunicative instruments created by humanity and it will always be a part of our development as species.
Apart from that, we can also learn so much about our own history by stuying and understanding music changes and tendencies through the years.
Last but by no mean least, art subjects should have the same importance the rest of the subjects have, due to people who are good at art ought to have the same opportunities to develope their skills the rest of the people posses.
Studying abroad is an opportunity for students to explore new lands with different cultures and traditions.
It is also a chance to discover new horizons in life; which ultimately add to our life experience.
I think, the experience of the travel itself from one place to another around the world is really amazing.
I am one of the students who struggled enough to study overseas in Canada, because I have the passion of experience life in Canada which is rich in cultural diversity and humane values.
Studying abroad broaden students' mindset, because they'll have the chance to live on their own away from their families for some time, which enables them to cope with the challenges they could face.
In addition to that, getting to know people from different cultural backgrounds is great opportunity to learn so much new things.
Although students may step out of their comfort zone and there might be some sort of culture shock, but eventually students get used to it, and will start to love their new destination.
Students usually choose to study abroad for getting quality education so that they can get into good career in the future.
However, some people believe that there are advantages as well as disadvantages.
For me, I do not think there are disadvantages for studying abroad except the fact that minor young people may be prone to some problems because of their young age if they are studying alone overseas away from family.
But recently universities and colleges arrange specific type of accommodation to such minor young people by putting them under guardianship of local family - and that's very good.
Some people have conservative ideas about studying abroad, and they fear the process of acculturation, because they want to keep their cultures without adopting new cultures.
Hundreds of years ago, travel could be very difficult for people, due to the fact that means of transporation were not available compared to the world of today.
In addition, travel at the time might not be as important as today, because people had everything that they need.
But with the industrial revolution, new means of transportation have been invented such as aeroplanes, cars and modern ships.
Therefore, travel has become easier and more accessibe to everyone.
As a conseqeunce, that has opened new opportunities for people to discover new lands and start global business; which has led to the globalisation that we witness now.
Furthermore, with the increasing scientific progress and technological advances in sciences like computer engineering and atronomy, the mankind introduced itself to much more possibilities; such as space exploration.
Now people need to travel to new countries for diverse reasons such as business, education, immigration and tourism etc.
So, in my opinion, I think the future of travel is very promising as long as we see a very thriving global economy as well as education and immigration sectors.
Hundreds of years, people would not imagine the travel possibilities we have now.
Similarly, travel can definitely change.
