Here, in this writing, I am going to expose the advantages and disanvantages of that matter.
To start with, I would like to mention how satisfactory spending time abroad could be for anyone.
First of all, by living abroad not only will you discover some new places and enviroments, but also you will be involved in a culture which can be very different from yours.
Whether you stay for a long period or not, being immersed in such situations is always a great learning in life, as long as you are disposed to be part of this experience.
If this is the case, you will get several new skilss such as speaking another language, understanding other lifestiles, and being able to adapt yourself to events you would not face in your own country.
Nevertheless, living in a different country could also be stressful, especially, when it comes to speak another language which is not your mother tongue.
In that way, you may need some help, if you happen not to know how to express yourself in that language.
Food and weather conditions can undoubtledly be a problem too, above all, if you go to a place where you will surely find the complete opposite of what you are used to deal at home.
However, these disadvantages can be lowered jut by adquiring the proper information about the country you are planning to go.
Last but by no means least, I would like to add that the whole experience resulted from living abroad will definitely made you a more mature and responsible person.
WRITE AND IMPROVE: A MARVELOUS TOOL When it comes to resources and tools for learning languages, it is often said that it is hard to find the right ones to reach the aim you have point to.
But, I have to admit that I was greatly suprised by the one called 'Write and improve' from the very moment that I started to use it.
Whether you have a good level or not, this tool already mentioned gives you the oportunity to test your brain, correct your mistakes, and, what is more, it shows you your erros at once.
That makes it enormously useful, since one can have a result in a matter of seconds.
Another utility worth mentioning is the clasification it makes of your mistakes, by using different colours to separate important mistakes from the ones which are not.
On balance, my consideration to this advantageous and innovative implement is nothing but extremely positive.
And, speaking from my personal experience, once you start using it, your motivation rises, especially if you are rewarded with a good mark.
I would like to end up by recomending its use to everyone whose concerns about writing are high.
I would not be exaggerating if I say that you will find the benefit of using 'Write and improve' from the very beggining.
