Offices tend to have two types of workstations for employees.
In one of them workers are secluded from others, while in the second kind no walls separate them from themselves.
As usually, these two situations have both some advantages as well as drawbacks.
On the one hand, people might prepare to work in open workstations, bacause they are surrounded by other coworkers, who are likely their friends or acquaintances.
That may lead to creation of pleasant atmosphere at work.
For that reason employees might enjoy their work, which would result in being much more efficient.
Furthermore, if someone had any difficulty with their work, then it would be hard to asked for help since other coworkers would be next to him.
On the other hand, I must admit that there are some people who prefer to work on their own.
Presence of other people might only disturb them, which would impact on their performance.
Moreover, I strongly believe that enclosed workstations or cubicles are much more quiet, which also may enable employees to focus more on their work.
To top off, it seems to me that answer to our main question depends on particular worker's personality.
For employees who like to be surrounded by other people more suitable would be open workstation, whereas to people who can be describe as lone wolves it would be most optimal choice so they should work in enclosed workstations.
It is true that zoos are good places for people to learn about animals.
And I used to go with my family to the national zoo in my country, and it was very amazing moments.
we had seen various wild animals and it was great experience to me.
However, some people believe animals belong in nature and shouldn't be kept in zoos.
It is right perhaps, especially when we think of it from freedom point of view that all animals should have the freedom to live in nature where they belong.
Keeping animals in zoos is not only a way of entertainment, but also a chance for animals caregivers to look after the sick animals that may be diffcult for them to survive alone in nature because of predation.
Furthermore, veterinarians carry out scientific researches about animals to better understand animal diseases and why they arise and how to prevent or treat these diseases.
That's why, animals may be kept in zoos for such studies.
I think, it makes sense to keep animals in zoos as long as this achieves promosing scientific outcomes as well as entertainment.
Nevertheless, I still see animal confinement as sort of supressing their freedom.
So, it is highly recommended that animal welfare authorities to provide safe zoos with suitable environment so that animals can still feel satisfied while they are being kept in zoos.
In my opinion, animal care should be given importance because they are essential part of the ecosystem that we live in.
So, protecting animals is protecing our ecosystem.
In conclusion, I would say, animals may be kept in zoos for entertainment, scientific reserach purposes and caregiving.
apparently, if there is no way to release all the animals in zoos to the nature, we need to be mindful to give better care.
