It is not a modern way to learn about animals from zoos.
Many people experienced going to zoos in their childhood.
In my memory, almost of animals in zoos were just sitting and lying in their cage with an uneasy face.
Nowadays, many TV programs focused on animals in nature, and animals moved lively in the program.
It is quite different between animals in zoos and one in nature.
I thought that keeping animals in zoos should be stopped and let them belong in nature, after watching such TV programs.
The origin of zoos is rare animal collections for an aristocracy.
They treated animals as unique objects, not creatures.
In present times, people treated animals in zoos as things that tell us the motion of animals in picture books.
Being in a cage and being exposed to human sight stressed a lot for animals.
It reported that giant panda in a Hong Kong zoo that was long time sterility got pregnant, and the reason for the pregnancy was that pandas could spend their time without any witnesses as of the zoo closure due to the pandemic of COVID-19.
This news indicated that human witnesses might be harmful to animals in zoos.
And more, there are many other ways to learn about animals without zoos in modern society.
We can learn about animals from books and TV programs and photos of nature magazines.
These ways do not harm animals belonging in nature.
It is not suitable to hold animals in the cage of zoos.
It stressed them and distort their lives.
Animals are not playing toys of human.
We should treat them as they are in nature.
