Video games are good or bad for children?
People have asked this question for such a long time.
Some people believe that it's good, others believe the opposite.
In my opinion, it has both positive and negative effects.
Positive effects?
According to Ted Talk, video games have many positive effects.
Problem and solving logic.
When a child play games like Flappy Bird, he trains his brain to come up with creative ways to solve puzzles and other problems in short bursts.
Accuracy.
Action games train the brain of players to make fast decisions without losing accuracy.
As you can see, video games give children positive effects.
However, too much of anything is just too much.
Video games could negatively impact your studies.
This is the clearest effect that everyone does know.
When you spend a lot of time playing videos game, you start to feel tired and you don't want to do your exercises anymore.
Next, it may cause insomnia.
Adequate amount of sleep is essential for your brain and body to be productive during the day.
However, excessive gaming, especially before sleep, can result to insomnia and sleep deprivation.
That's it.
Everything has two sides.
If you do it properly, it will give you positive effects.
If not, you'll have some problems.
So be careful!
One of the most popular games in the world is the video games.
