Sleep is essential for our good health.
We can see many advertisements for exercise on TV and in magazines so that the importance of exercise for our health is recognized commonly.
However, there is a thing that more important than exercise but not treated seriously.
It is sleep.
The lack of sleep can have various negative effects on our health.
Many studies show the bad influence of short sleep.
For example, the report published by the national center of neurology and psychiatry clarified that the lack of sleep could make our mental sensitive to negative stresses.
Appetite and sleep are related closely.
According to the research of Chicago University, the less sleep stimulates the hormones that increase our appetite and diminish satiety.
This study indicates that people with a lack of sleep might gain weight easily rather than others.
Many researchers show that short sleep is harmful to our health.
However, people treated the risk of it as a trivial matter.
Exercise is a good thing, but sleep is essential for our health.
