Study abroad?
Should or shouldn't?
Some people say "should," the others say "shouldn't."
So, which is right?
Everything has 2 sides so it's hard to answer which is correct.
Let's take a look about this.
First, I'll talk about its advantages.
Studying abroad gives you many benefits.
You can see the world, study in a better education, experience a new culture.
Your language skills will be improved extremely.
You will have opportunities to get a great job as well.
There are still more advantages of studying abroad but I think this is enough.
Now is about its disadvantages.
Homesickness.
Being away from your family and friends can be a lonely experience.
This can result in sadness and anxiety.
I have seen amount of students studying abroad have to come back because they can't stand the loneliness.
Cost.
An important thing that you have to concern is cost.
The cost of studying abroad can be expensive, especially when you don't have a scholarship.
Next is culture shock.
This rarely happens but who knows?
You will be faced with a new language, customs, food, dress styles, etc. .
This may make you frustated even if you have it fully researched.
My topic is the difference between a city and a rural area.
I would like to focus on medical doctors.
There are in the citis many doctors, more than in the rural ares.
Why? Is it a problem?
I start with the second question.
In my opinion it may be a problem for economic situation.
The doctors want to be in the citis because they can be in the middle of cultural and social life.
In the cities are more possibilities for education.
On the other hand the surrounding is anonymous.
The health problems of patients are connected to their respiratory tract for example influenza, coronavirus.
Other problems are connected to the immune system.
The different situation is on the rural ares. We can see advantages and disadvantages too.
The doctor can be a part of patient's family.
He knows his anamnesis and family genes.
The health problems are about a surgery of legs or arms.
Living a healthy life is not easy.
A lot of people think that for living more are necessarily only two things: doing exercise and eating healthy foods.
However, in a greater understanding, there are several habits that may be considerate to live better.
For instance, taking care with our healthy mental.
It's normal people say that the body is linked with the mind.
But just in few cases, people give the real importance for the mind's care.
Having a healthy mental is essencial to take consciense about how our body is.
If a person goes everyday to the gym, but lives in a routine full of sadness, he is not completely healthy.
Besides that, it's important understanding what things makes each one happy.
If a person is happy traveling, he should invest more time and energy planning his future trip.
Or if a person miss his family a lot, he should stay closer of his relatives.
So, there are a lot of factors that must be considerate to live better.
But the most important thing is that each one is different and just that person can know what make his happy.
