For me, the best holiday is the trip to Hueco Mundo last summer.
I went with my family and some of my friends.
We chose this destination because we heard that it was one of the most must-go countries in the world.
It was also where my brother had been learning so we wanted to visit him as well.
Rumors is indeed not wrong.
It was gorgeous, more than you could imagine.
The beauty of Hueco Mundo was unbelievable: The buildings with glittering lights, the incredibly clean streets and so on.
The food was really good too.
It was simple with rice, vegetables, some meat just like we had in our country but it tasted delicously.
We stayed at a hotel on the capital.
Next day, we visited our brother about 5 kilometers away.
He took us to many places: museums, galleries, etc.
We learnt many things: culture, custom, clothes,...
We stayed there for more 2 days and the last day, we got on the plane and went home.
It was the best holiday for me.
I not only had a lot of fun but also learned many useful things.
Being healthy is importance as you get older.
Some people work hard all their life to earn money then they ignore they selfl care both physical and mental health.
Therefore, this could lead to spending their earmng income to cure a sickeness, instead of preparing for their retirement.
In my opinion taking care of your health and your wealth are crucial for living.
Why wealth is necessary.
As we live in a capitalism society so money could provide a high standard of living, therefore getting rich is the intimate goal for most people.
Wealth is a major supporter for optimum health because it gives you the financial freedom to make healthy choices and avail of any existing health and fitness resources.
Unfortunately, in our market place today, the healthier food choices are more expensive than the damaging processed varieties.
This is why wealth is also our freedom of our financial security.
In contrast, betterrhealth is central to human happiness and well-being.
It also makes an important contribution to economic progress, as healthy populations live longer, are more productive, and save more.
Many factors influence health status and a country's ability to provide quality health services for its people.
