We often see TV news about elderly women living close to 120 years, with the reporter asking her the secret of healthy living.
It cannot be denied that recent development in medical field has dramatically lengthened average life span.
However, I do not value highly of those news reports, as shorter but intense lives should be more meaningful.
Firstly, not so many 80 or 90 year-old people can afford to live on their own, forcing their sons or daughters to support their daily lives.
Although living together makes family bonds stronger, it must be a burden for younger generations to support their parents while working or raising their children.
Some even spend their last ten years of life hospitalized, which accompanies tremendous medical cost.
In no way should lives without health be happy.
Secondly, having shorter lives may be a motivation for younger generations to appreciate their lives well.
Despite having adequate free time, some businessmen waste their time, staying home on weekends idlelly.
As most people spend their twenties through sixties working at the same company, such activities as doing hobbies or travelling on weekends are indispensable to avoid mundane lives.
Having less time after retirement encourages younger generations to seek what leads them to spend their time happily.
For these two reasons, I believe not having excessively long life span should be a shortcut to spending meaningful life.
Have you ever wondered: What will our travel ook like in the future?
We will still travel the same say as we do now?
My prediction: It may be different.
We may travel faster, safer and it less impact on the environment.
At present, you can see that there are so many problems about travel: emissions, traffic jams, traffic accidents,...
Therefore, many scientists, engineerings start to think about how to change our travel.
They are working, testing to create new vehicles to minimize the problems I mentioned before.
Several ideas have been introduced.
In 2017, Elon Musk showed his project about Hyperloop, a sealed tube or system of tubes with low air pressure through which a pod may travel substantially free of air resistance or friction.
He also conducted a test and it worked.
I know, there will be many concerns surrounding this project but it's still a positive signal for our future travel.
I guess you have heard about flying car.
Many protoypes have been built since the early of 20th century.
Most recently, a flying car named Cezeri was first introduced and it worked fine.
There are still many other projects, ideas to change our future travel.
Hope it will become true.
