That is a hard reality, but always fewer medical doctors decide to work in the rural areas where a high rate of deseaes and ills are expected over the next decades.
This is an aptitude related to different social and economic issues, most of them affecting our modern society.
The most impressive is the lack of good willing and the bad aptitude to help others.
Rural areas are becoming more and more crowded after many people make a comeback in the countryside, where some new deseases are unfortunately spreading.
New jobs are spreading in different areas but it does not seem to interest young medical doctors.
It is not difficult to guess the reasons, first of all we are speaking about areas involved with famine, wars, draughts and every kind of risky situations that does not help to persuade doctors.
Another important point is that rural areas are cut off from the most important places of a city and they often are not provided with the most essential services; the last but not least it takes long to get a city.
Some solutions are going to be thought to improve the situation, like better means trasport system or the building of new facilities that simplify doctors lives in rural areas.
Some new services at doctors disposal is not the only solution.
The economic crises make people poorer, it means they do not have enough money to afford detailed and suitable cure.
IAs I see it, governments should made sensitive-based decisions like funding hospitals in ruaral areas and let a raise of payment at the doctors.
