Television, a media appeared in the 1950s, is one of the most important inventions that changed our lives.
Everyone knows that the main purpose of a television is entertaining.
But have you ever wondered: "Can it also educate?"
From my point of view, it definitely can.
How can a television educate?
By the programs shown on it.
When I was a kid, there was an educational program shown every morning.
It lasted for 30 minutes and it provided some Math lessons for children.
Nowadays, more and more programs produced to teach students Math, Geography, Science,...
Even cartoons can play that role.
For example, Tom and Jerry teach children how to be a good guy.
As you can see, now we are dealing with COVID-19.
Students can't go to school.
Therefore, in many countries, televisions are used to teach the students while they're at home.
In a nutshell, there's no way that a television can't educate.
Television has the potential to do that.
It depends on us.
