Nowadays, most students decide to study overseas for a while.
Studing in another country has some pros and cons, and I will argue both sides in this essay.
The main reason to choose studying abroad is broden your horizons.
People who go abroad could gain the new experiences and face a new culture to deal with.
For example, students who are living overseas could learn to adapt themselves with the new situations and think more rationally about their surroundings.
Secondly, moving away helps students to learn a new language and give them a good opportunity to research with a large range of references.
Moreover, dealing with a new language increases their brain capacity as well.
Turning to the other side of argument, there are some drawbacks to study abroad.
The main disadvantage is culture shock.
Students might face a new people who are not familiar with them and this make them feel loneliness.
This is not possible for them to cope with this new condition easily.
The other problem must be mantioned is, students have to start from scratch.
It means, they must start new life and it is possible that they have to live with low money at first.
Also, they might get a student loan to pay university fees.
In conclusion, although there are some considerable pros in moving away to study, there are some disadvantages to consider carefully.
Studying abroad could open students' mind and also, improve their language skills.
On the other hand, they might not adopt themselves with new place quickly and also, have difficult financial problems.
