We are living in a digital era that video games are developing rapidly.
How do video games impact on children is an argument among their parents.
In my points of view, play video games will have both positive and negative impacts on the children.
The positive of playing video games are developing children\u2019s brains.
It makes them more innovative.
Besides, playing video games is the way of stress elimination.
On the other hand, playing video games also have many negative impacts.
The first is the children waste time and money to play video games.
The second is the children\u2019s health problem such as eyes defects.
Their sight is worsen because the time of sitting in front of screen.
Besides, the addiction of video games playing make children ruder and aggressive in their behavior.
The worst negative impact is games addiction.
For example, children are likely to imitate games they played.
Many teenage crimes are result from game addiction.
In conclusion, the children\u2019s playing video games have both positive and negative impact.
How their parents control and face with those impacts are important.
