Nowdays medical doctors are mainly working around urban areas, this trend might be associated to a better salary.
However, there is st a growing demand for doctors in rural areas that it is not possible to reach.
There are many reasons that explained this tendency along several proposals to tacke it.
One of the biggest problems is the medicine is evolving dramatically.
As a result, doctors need to be up to date, and for this, they should study at universities or colleges that are always located in cities.
On the other hand, doctors have to compete for a place to be a specialist or consultant, there are only few places available and these places are highly competive.
In addition, the income in cities could be higher compare to rural areas, and obviosly these is a key factor to have in account.
On the other hand, these trend is generating a lack of doctors in rural areas.
In fact, according to the Health Department, there are many hospitals without a doctor, that situation is worsening with the time and patients are struggling to find a health provider near to their towns.
This is a problem that should be tackle between health departments and universities.
One solution is develop a way to young doctors through rural medicine with good salaries and offering also a continuing devoloping for their careers.
