Nowadays, it is very common that some students choose to study in another country during high school or university.
It is very important when someone is learning a new language, he or she can has contact with not only the language, but also the culture and living abroad is a great experience for anyone who wants to learn about the language and the culture of another country.
On the other hand, students who choose to study abroad can lose some opportunities in their country.
Students can redo their school year because the subject in another country is totally different and perhaps a university school can miss a job opportunity in that year he is traveling.
To sum up, it is a great chance when someone can study oversea.
It is not an opportunity that all people can affort it because it is very expensive and even if students can stop their lives for one year or more, it will be a terrific experience and it will be very important for their resum\u00E9 and personal experience.
A month ago, I asked my English teacher, Mrs. Gomax what should I do to improve my English writing skill.
Then, she suggested that I should try the website named Write&Improve which is sponsored by Cambridge University .
So, I tried it and found it useful for me.
Once you enter the website ,you can choose the level you would like to join.
There are three levels which are beginner ,intermediate and advanced.
You can freely go for a suitable level for the ability of your English knowledge .
You can also creat an account .
It already gave you the titles what you have to write .
For example,let us say you choose the beginner level ,you can see the different titles with questions .
If you are going to write,click the question , write the answer and then submit it when you are finished .
It is really useful for me.
I feel that my writing is improving within a month.
And I like the way they motivate the students .
When your writing is finished ,it gives you some feedbacks and awards if you reach the goal they set.
You can see your progress at the progress graph as well.
That is my favourite part as I can see my progress day by day.
I like all functions involving it except one thing\u2014that is it can't correct each of your mistakes exactly.
However, I would like to recommend this website my classmates who wish to improve their writing .
I am sure that you all will see the good results.
Nowadays doctors are not tempted to move into the country as they were back in the day.
Cities are no dirty places anymore and instead physicians are greeted with a generous income and a wide offer of free-time activities.
But essentially there are more potential patients in a rather tight space, allowing the doctors to abandon long trips to bedbound patients.
As a result you don't waste too much time driving around, which you could also use to cure even more patients in a day.
You see: money is the cue.
To solve the problem of doctor-shortage in the country you have to attract physicians by securing them extra help by the authoroties.
For instace you could offer them special conditions for the building process of their doctor's offices.
Alternatively they could be provided with lower running taxes or prices for their equipment.
Another option would be to give more places at universities to aspiring students of medicine who consent to work for a certain period in rural areas.
