The best holiday that I ever had was in January in 2006.
My husband and I have decided get married in this month because we wanted to celebrate our engagement in our parents' town since we had been living 6 hours far from them.
Another reason to choose the date and the place was because we had a lot of friends in common that spent that holiday with their relatives.
All our friends were gone to another city to work, so we could meet them in holidays and vacations.
It was an amazing party, with all our family and most of our friends.
I had a beautiful dress and we invited 400 people.
After the party we spent the night in a hotel and we had lunch with our family in the same place where the party happened because a lot of people had lunch with us.
After some days, we went back to our apartment and now almost 15 years after, we live in a nice house, in another city, with two daughters and one fish.
In our country,Myanmar,it takes time the teachers to be changed to one school from another. Because they have to serve at the same school for about four or five years to be promoted .
So, I rarely experience being taught by different teachers.
I don't know well the differences between having new teachers and same teachers each year.
I believe that both have positive and negative effects.
For some students, they like having the same teacher for several years because they are accustomed to his or her teaching method and they like it.
But, to be honest, I really would like to be taught by new teachers each year.
In my opinion, having new teachers will give us something new to learn.
For example,supposing we do not like the teacher now teaching, then we can expect another one is more better next year and his or her teaching method may be way better or may be more fun.
As I mentioned before ,we could learn something different from her and she can attract us to be interested in the school lessons ,I think.
On the other hand,the new teacher might be worse at teaching .
However, I like to be having new teacher each year as I wish to be taught with different teaching ways by different teachers .
