There is no doubt that volunteer work this day have become a famous work due to the fact that people have became more sensetive and carrying about the people around them.
However, the question is; is it suitable to have volunteer work as a requiremnt for graduating from high school?
In this essay I am going to discuss this penomenen from both point of views.
On one hand we have people who argue that forcing our children to volunteer is considerably a bad thing to do.
People believe that the essence of volunteer work lies in our intention.
For instance, some students might not be willing to volunteer so when we make them work arbitrarily they are going to hate it and in this casewe lose what really is the meaning of this work, which is to give all you could uncondotionally and with passionat.
Moreover, on the other hand people argue that making our students work vulonteerly could benefit many people and in the same time we teach our students to have loads of exprience in such field, which will benefit then in the long-run.
Good examole here is that they will learn how to be patient and control you time, also to respect people and to learn this work skiils would make you life easier.
Eventually, we could say that forcing our students may not be the right decision.
Instead, we could tell them the importance of this worl and leave it alternative.
