Books and technology nowadays are in war.
Both have a side which fight each other.
The reasons are many. Like the prices, quality of the products.
Personally I do not think that computer and tables should replace books in school because it can be very expensive for the family to buy these technologies.
Reading a book is 100 times better than read something on a tablet for example, you can not enjoy them like a real book.
Also give a tablet to the students would mean give the chance to play video games in schools under the eyes of the teachers without any conseguences.
This already happens today with smartphones.
Books are also useful to take notes, which are important in a student life or you can underline important paragraphs in order to have a better understanding of the topic which you are going to study.
Technologies are not useful for the teacher because a lot of them do not know how to use the modern phone, pc.
I personally think that using the book is the best way to teach in these and future days.
