Every student should have the possibility to choose where to study.
Most part of them can't do it, because going studying abroad is very expensive.
Obtain a room in universities' campusses is quiete difficutl, becaus there is a limitate number of available rooms.
So, a lot of families haven't any other alternative on paying affit.
A room can cost around 400,00 euros per month in normal cities, but in the most expensive ones, such as Milan, prices are around 700,00-800,00 euros per month.
Moreover, despite being public, university has taxes to be paid, which are calculated basing on the annual salary of the family.
The problem is that the base under which people don't pay is very low and a normal family needs at least 2.000,00 euros per year to pay university taxes.
In addition to that, there is material to be bought: a pen is always a pen of course, but a book can even cost 60,00 euros.
When I attended university, every exam took at least three books.
Then there is the bus, to move around the city.
At the end is obvious that studying abroad is an economic choise: those who can do, they do it, thos who can't, they don't.
I chose to remain because luckyly my city offered me the university course I wanted and because I didn't want to leave my family, my boyfriend and my cat, whom I'm very close to.
Probably, in other conditions, I would have gone away, in a foreign country, to learn the language, to open my mind, to grow up.
Certainly, studying abroad forces to grow up because you're alone, but it is necessary to be a responsible person, a condition too rare nowadays.
Living alone doesn't mean living out of rules, but it's a chance to follow our own path.
Workplace Design There is no doubt that one of the important places that people stay at for a long period of their days, is their work place, therefore it sould be designed in a way that make you feel comfortable and ready to accomplish your duty.
However,in this article I am going to examine various types of office designs.
Firstly, one famous design is known as the open desgin, where there are no walls to seperate different desks, so all workers work in one huge hall.
