Speaking personally I think that having different teachers each year is better because it means an opportunity to learn in different ways, to know a new person with diverse qualities and thoughts which can be enriching for the students' personal and profesional growth.
On the top of that, if a student has a different teacher every year, he or she likely will develop his or her ability to adapt to the changes; which represents a great chance for the student's development.
Furthermore, having a new teacher implies new challenges and a new ways to learn or to explain the subject's topics, as a result that the students can use a set of tools to learn better and they will feel enthsiastic to do new exercises and activities.
On the contrary when a student has the same teacher for several years, it would be unlikely to discover the way she learns and understand better or develop the skill of adapting to the changes as well as the student can stay in a confort zone and lose little by little the enthusiasm because there are no changes, no new ways and probably no more challenges.
