Well, I think this is a issue debate because there are many elements to take in account in order to express an opinion, as for me I think the video games have a negative impact on children when they are too young and there are grounds for believing this.
The first reason is that nowadays there are so many kind of videogames but the most popular videogames are about violence and killers which increase the probability of agressive behavior in children, such as bullying or being agressive with their sinblings.
Then, one of the most crucial bad effect on children for playing video games is on their health owing to they spend a lot of time in front of the screen, this damage their sight.
Besides, the lack of physical activity has repercusions in their muscle and bones as well as increases the probabilities to be overweight.
Apart from this, other negative consequences on children are the isolation and poor interpersonal skills due to they play videogames for long hours in closed spaces, they don't interact with other people so they don't practice communication skill which would bring out some problems in the near and long term in the school, such as difficulties to make friends, challenges in teamwork among others.
Adittionally, there are so many cases that have shown how children get obsessed with videogames that they try to do less things in their houses and other activities which take their valuable time.
One instance could be they just eat junk food and some sodas, which are not healthy so as to save time.
Another example is that they don't do their homeworks or don't study at home so that can invest much more time to play videogames; as a result that they make poorly in the school.
Finally, it seems to me that videogames are harmful for the children development, owing to the bad effects, which I've already mentioned, in personal, physical and psychological aspects.
