Nowadays people are looking for online English courses.
This is a new type of education and have some advantages and disadvantages that have to be had in consideration before applying an online course.
On of the main advantages, it is the online education allows to reduce cost as courses don't need a classroom and all the facilities as computers and printed materials that usually schools have to provided to their students when they are attending a face-to-face course.
For example, Write and Improve is an online platform that help students with writing activities through interactive exercises, moreover, this system has digital resources as different writting levels and virtual examinations depending on IELTS or general training.
Indeed, students can monitor their progress and recognize their strengths and weaknesses in real time in front of their computer wherever and whenever they wish.
An additional factor to consider is that this online learning platform has some educational resources such as edition and writing programs with the aim to facilitate the learning process.
On the other hand, some people could criticize that lack of human physical contact that is inherent in this online platform.
Most important, being bilingual or multilingual is a social skill that humans developed in real situations, and only can improve this skills in real life.
The online platform rely on course materials but lack human interaction than languages have as corporal language.
There are some language abilities that can only be acquired on real interactions that obviously internet can not replace.
For example, pronunciation online programs are unable to teach about all the phonics variety, accents and intonation.
Despite these drawbacks, the future is online education, and this is linked with technological advances that obviously are going to tackle these situations, and probably are going to reemplace somehow face-to-face classes.
