To be a volunteer is a good thing.
However, if the volunteer is "required," it may not be good.
The goal of volunteers is "help."
Whether help humans, animals or the environment, people do it from the bottom of their hearts makes themselves feel great.
Besides, helping others can give them a sense of accomplishment and self-worth.
On the contrary, someone who is asked to be a volunteer, not aiding others by their own will, may not make all-out effort.
These volunteers just want to reach their goals as quickly as possible; therefore, they won't leave no stone unturned.
The high schools which demand the voluntary work from their students are well meaning, but that could distort the intent of being a volunteer.
The high schools should find some attractive ways, and guide students to the right directions.
Only do things from the bottom of one's heart could acqire the treasure of being a volunteer.
