First of all, I think it is a fantastic experience with so many advantages and some "disadvantages" which I prefer to name them as learnings.
By way of introduction, studying abroad it is highly recommended in the majority of schools and universities because of the opportunity that a student can have in order to improve another language.
Apart from that, there are so many skills that one studen can develop or improve during an exchange, such as communicative and social skills, due to the student meet new people from a different country and from a different culture, he has to find ways to interact and make friends.
In addition, the student would learn to work with multidiverse teams which is really significant for his or her resume for the long term.
Moreover, an incredible advantage from having an exchange is to visit different touristic places, such as beaches, desserts, mountains, museums, lakes and archeologycal places.
Besides, the student can try new and diverse dishes which are traditional or very popular in the residence's country.
On the other hand, the student will have the challenge to develop the capability to adapt to change, owing to the student is going to live far from home in a new city, as well as far from friends and family.
She has to face the changes in her routines and start to visualize and plan the new activities according to her circumstances.
In spite of, all the opportunities and advantages there are also some disadvantages from having an exchange, one instance could be that it can take much more time to finish a degree, due to the university just allow the students certain number of subjects which is no bad at all because the universities do this in order to make your exchange more enjoyable and with a little bit of less stress.
However, when a student starts studying in abroad there are some difficulties in view of the new university has differents rules and processes to assess the students.
Nevertheless, another disadvantage of studying abroad is that is an expensive experiences that is to require too much money.
Unless that a student wins a scholarship to make the exchange, which it just cover part of the expenses, but on the contrary she will have to pay the flight tickets, the housing, the food and costs of traveling and the payments to the university.
Finally, speaking personally I would recommend to all the students to make an exchange in wherever they want and not only learn and enjoy but also lose and find yourself again in that new country.
