Speaking personally, I think zoos are good places to learn about animals and there are other reasons which bring about so many benefits.
First of all, in my opinion zoos allows us to learn about the characteristics of animals, such alimentation, endangered species, the places where they from, behaviors and so on.
Moreover, zoos make the people feel conscious about how some actions have effects on the animals and in their habitats, one instance could be the industrial development, which is generating pollution in rivers and oceans, in the air and if that was enough this also provokes soil erosion and acid rain.
Another example is the trash that we create can have a bad effect on marine species as tortlues, sharks, penguins whales among others.
On the top of that, I believe zoos represent a house for many animals and zoos can save many animals from clandestine hunting.
There have been so many cases in Africa and Asia about how hunters which just chase and kill the animals, in order to obtain their tusks in the case of elephants or their fur in case of bears, seals and sea lions.
Bearing this in mind the zoos can offer security to the animals and it means a way to reduce the clandestine hunting, as a result zoos prevent animals from extinction.
Aditionally, zoos represent a place where some animals can receive veterinary care, which has saved animal lifes; as well as it seems to me that zoos try to provide similar habitats to the animals in order to make them feel at home and they don't lose some instincts once that they can go to an habitat free of clandestine hunting.
Nonetheless, it is just necessary to take into account the treat and care that animals have to receive from zoos, such as food in good conditions, veterinary care, spaces with the necessary conditions and so on.
As a conclusion, I think zoos are good places they can provide so many benefits to the animals and teach us so many valuable things about them.
The purpose of this report is to inform the English teacher about my experience with the program called Write and Improve.
First of all, it needs to be said that this website is a really gold mine for all the students who want to practise and improve their writing skills.
On the one hand, here you can find many workbooks, organised according to the levels of the Common European Framework of Reference for languages.
Moreover, there are different types of written assignments, from short and simple texts like notes and messages to more complex ones such as reports, reviews or even essays.
Furthermore, you can practise writing about a wide range of topics and, as a result, you have to use English more effectively.
On the other hand, you can create your own workbook and write about anything you like.
In addition, you receive feedback on your work in just few seconds.
Therefore, you can improve your writing level, for example, by using more adjectives in the right places.
To sum up, this programme is a free and very useful tool which help us to become much better learners.
