Given to the fact that most medical doctors prefer to work in cities where they will make a lot of money instead of working in rural areas, an unbalanced situation appears where people in rural area receive poor medical care and people in urban area receive good medical care.
This unbalanced situation caused people to move towards cities and leave away rural areas.
One of the reasone behind this is there is not enough financial support from the Government and poor administration to rural area.
It causes doctors to loose their motivation to work in rural area , if they can receive more incentive in cities.
To solve this situation, the Government plays a great role in mininizing the gap between cities and rural areas by trying to provide more incentives and supports for doctors who work in rural area.
Such incentives could be present in form of financial support.
