In my opinion, it is not wrong to keep any animals in zoos because zoos can save many animal lifes in many reasons.
The first reason is many zoos are the places that any endangered animals can live without hunting by huntmans in their natural habitats.
The second reason is to breed some animals that are almost extint and reintroduce them to thair habitats agian.
This program can improve the genetic in the nature and reduse cross breeding in animals herd.
Moreover, some animals have problems to mate for example, clouded leopard males are very aggressive when thay heat and they can kill their mate while they are mating.
That is no use if clouded leopard females die from mating.
Sciencetists and veterinarians find the way to increae their population by artificial insemination technique.
The last reason, zoos is the shelters for amimals from wildlife trafficking and we can't let them free because they have been brought from the forest when they was young.
In the other hand, zoos should provide the environment in animals cages like thier natural habitats and strengthen their behavior by supporting enrichments in the cages in order to avoid steriotypic behavior.
