With the development of globalization, the number of students to study aboard is increasing dramatically.
20 years ago there were only three main destination countries for most chinese students to study aboard: Japan, UK and USA.
Now chinese students are dispersed everywhere.
Beides the previous popular countries like Japan, UK and the USA, other european countries such as Germany, France, Italy are also becoming popular for them..
There are actually advantages and disadvantages of studying abroad.
Firstly, The students who study aboard, can experience different culture and life and broaden their knowledge.
Secondly, most students also want to improve their foreign language.
For instance, the most chinese students don't really speak English in their daily life.
However, good English skill is a must in almost all work fields.
Therefore, many students choose to study in the USA to improve their spoken English and get better understanding of the western culture.
Besides advantages, there are still some drawbacks that one cannot ignore.
Firstly, the cost for aboard study is relative high.
For example, especially in the USA, the students are paying around 50.000 dollars per year.
It is quite expensive for most students.
Secondly, many students who study aboard cannot really adapt themselves to the new environment, they don't have many freinds there and always feel lonely.
Thirdly, as far as I know, for example, many chinese students are much too shy and are not good at accomodating themselves to the new culture and environment.
Therefore, they only try to get in touch with other chinese students and have very little chance to spreak English or other foreign languages.
As a result, many of them still cannot spreak English fluently even after the aboard study.
In general, studing aboard is a good chance to boost the foreign language skills and experice different life style and culture.
However, how much one will benefit from it, vary from person to person.
