It is argued that telling the truth is vital for every moment of life.
While lying has some drawbacks, I quite agree that we need to use lie in some fundamental occasions.
There are some benefits to hide the truth in some ways.
On the one hand, if people face a situation which is a matter of death and life for them, they must tell lie.
Some times you must not reveal the truth if you think it could put you and people who you love at risk.
For example, when somebody is threatened by a theif who wants to give important information, they have to ignor telling truth to save their life.
In addition, in the some national circumstances dicision-makers have to give wrong data or lie to the public.
It means when a country face a foriegn interference like the war, polititions must prevent to tell the truth about their strategies and missions.
For instance, in the war between Iran and Iraq in 1980, the Iranian comenders did not reveal any data about the wepons and their plans to the public or media to avoid any dangerous situation for soldiers.
If any vital information have been disclosed to people showing the honesty, country would fail in the attack.
In conclusion, although telling lie is unacceptable between some individuals, in my view, in some specific situation we must neglect the truth to save our life or national benefits.
