Zoological gardens are a controversial component of human society.
They provide a safe refuge for endagered or injured animals but these parks can be abusive in their treatment of creaturs as well.
There are not only plenty of davantages but also lots of disadvantages of zoos.
Firstly, the proponents state that these facilities help us to conserve endangered species.
Zoos have brought several annimal species back from the brink of extinction.
For instance, California condors were down to 27 before facilities in Los Angeles and San Diego started breeding programs to protect them.
Several other animals such as bongos, Reget Honeyeaters can also take credit for their survival thanks to zoos.
Secondly, zoos provide an economic boost to their community.
Zoos can be local, national, or international attraction that people want to see.
These attractions are often sate spaces for young families to come out and enjoy a day together.
Apart from this, these facilities can create good-paying jobs, encourage entrepreneurs to be active in their community, and provide indirect profits to local businesses as well.
However, the opponents state when animals are born in captivity, they become dependent on humans.
The reason why most of the animals that are in zoos today are the offspring of captures animals form the generation before is the fact that the descendants are unable to cope in the wild by themselves.
Futhermore, there is an ethical question that we must answer.
Most wild animals thrive when they can live in their natural habitat.
When we bring them into a enclosure of any type, then it can have a direct and adverse impact on their health.
Orcas are an excellent example of this issue.
Their lifespan sees s reduction of 70% when they live in captivity.
In general, the discussion about zoos are very controversial nowadays.
In Thailand, many parents support their children to study abroad in order to get new experiences and improve the languages.
There are many advantages of studing abroad for example students can lean new curriculums or techniques that are not tought in Thai education.
Students can improve their language with native speaker of each country that they have gone to.
To learn the traditional culture is a very good experiences in student life.
Moreover, students have freedom to do things that they want unlike in Thailand that parents always keep their eyes out their students.
After the students have graduated from high schools or universities, they also keep contract with other freind around the world that is very important for their career path in the future.
On the other hand, the disadvantages of studying abroad are prety seroious.
Some students can not adapt with new environment and they feel home sick.
Language barrier is one of the problams when many people study in orther countries.
When they have to study hard and have no one to consult, they might have mental problem during study.
Some countries don't completely accept foreinge people and being racist can happen at any time.
In my opinion, It is a good chance to study in another country because there are many new experiences but student have to prepare themselves so that they have to face with unexpeted incidences.
Video games have become a staple in our modern, technologically driven culture.
While kids have been crazy about these for decades, the introduction of smartphones and mobile gaming systems has pushed them to new heights.
Ofen based on fatasy, they also reflect both history and current events.
But whether it's a good or bad thing is up to debate.
The proponents state that the video game may get unexpected benefit from them; better vision.
They have been shown to increse players' ability to dintinguish subtle difference in shade of gray.
They may help players increase their ability to visually detect the direction of movement.
It was found that gamers spotted targets on a cluttered screen 80% of the time, while non-gamers managed this only 30% of the time.
Secondly, video games involve taking risks, and the ability to strategize.
It teaches patience, preserverance, and the right judement.
It also helps people find new friends and social connections.
Besides, gamers become better at critical analysis and learn to concentrate on tasks at hand to completion.
Thirdly, It has been found that people are more confident, energetic and emotionally positive when they play video games, whch is exactly the opposite of what depression brings about.
People who feel depressed lack physical energy, find it difficult to carry out daily tasks and are generally pessimistic.
Thus, playing can reduce the risk for depression, help with arthritis, and even be a therapreutic option of aphasia.
However, the opponents state that there are also plenty of disdavantages of video game.
Firstly, video games are designed to be addictive, so it is essential to have some self-control.
Especially people with poor impulse control or who have a hard time fitting in are most vulnerable to game addiction.
Secondly, video games often act as replacement for real-time human connections.
People who find themselves playing hours upon hours of video games may find themselves losing touch with the relationships they've bult with other people.
Thirdly, Video game addiction could lead to other levels of psychological stress as well.
Gamers may suffre from low self-esteem, have social anxieties, or even suffer from depression.
Excessive gaming can also inspire feelings of guilt and shame.
It is possible that uncontrolled gaming could enhace the signs and symptoms of other mental disorders.
Video games are not bad for you as long as you aren't overdoing.
So, enjoy your downtime and relax with your games but get out there and keep your life as diverse as possible as well. because eventually, you have got to win the game of life.
The best holiday ever At the end of September in 2020, I had a short but very exicting holiday in Switzerland for almost one week.
In the summer semester break, I spent all th time to learn the programming skills with Python and finish my seminar thesis in the International Finance chair at the University Mannheim.
It is quite stressful and chanllenging for me.
Therefore, I need a holiday to relax after that hard time.
After the discussion with Max, we have decided to make a short holiday in Switzerland.
The reasons are as follows: firstly, compared to the holiday expenses in other European countries, the average expenses for holiday in Switzerland is relatively high.
We cannot afford a vocation longer than one week in Switzerland.
Secondly, due to the COVID-19 emergency, there are much fewer tourists in Switzerland.
It will be much comfortable and less expensive for us to have holiday there.
Thirdly, we only need around 3 hours from Mannheim to Zurich.
Therefore, it is very close for us and we don't need to spend much time on the way.
Therefore, we had a wonderful vocation in Switzerland.
During these days, we have seen not only the modern city Zurich but also the Tourists cities like Luzern and Interlaken.
Among all the sightseeings, I like the wonderful landscape in Luzern most.
It was amazing beautiful.
We have booked a hotel on the mountain with a view of the lake and other mountains.
I will never forget this wonderful view.
In conclusion, this is the best holiday for us.
