I will always remember visiting USA for the first time.
That was the most exciting holiday I have ever had for several reasons.
And, in this writing, I am going to mention the reasons why I do think so.
To get started, It took place when I had just finished my degree.
I was quite young and unexperienced then.
Nevertheless, somehow I knew it was going to be one of the greatest experiences one person could ever lived.
A summer in New York just sounded as perfect as it truly was.
Had it not been for the fact that I already had a friend living there, I would have never made the decision of going there that fast.
But the truth was that having the support of some close friend who knew well that enormous city, meant the world for me.
Visiting New York, the city that never sleeps, simply was as making a dream come true for me.
What I fisrt did once I was there was finding a job as a waitress, as I had plans to spend there the whole summer.
I met some new friends at my job, and they showed me some important and distintive places from New York.
I remember feeling tiny while I walked around the most famous skyscrapers.
I also remember the crowded streets at every single moment, the lights, the singular cabs of the city.
It all was magical to me.
Nevertheless, there were some drawbacks that should be mention as well.
Perhaps it was too much time for me to spend far from home for the first time in my life.
It was three months missing my family, the food at home, my friends, and, especially, my mother tongue.
I was not quite good at English at that moment, I have to admit.
Last but not least, I would like to conclude by adding that, even though those downsides, I would certaingly recommend this kind of adventure to everyone.
Not only did I learn a lot about what living on your own means, but also I learned a lot about myself and how independient and responsible I can actually be.
