Now is the start of a new school year.
In the past one year I finished several things from my to do list.
Firstly, I have started my master program at the University Mannheim and I have done it very well.
Secondly, I applied a seminar thesis in Finance area and get a quite good grade at the end.
Thirdly, I have learned the programming language Python, and done the empirical data analysis with python.
Therefore, I am very satisfied with my progress in the past one year.
However, there are still several things that I need to improve in the coming year.
Firstly, although I have started to program with Python, I still need to contunue the programming exercise to master this program language.
Furthermore, it is also very important to apply the financial basics in Python.
Secondly, I still need to improve my English and my German to C1 level.
Thirdly, I need to improve my skills with Microsoft software to be fit for the job.
Last but not least, I need to train myself to get well along with others. Since I am quite social distant.
To achieve my goals, I have made the daily and weekly schedule to remind me and track my progress.
Nowadays there are more options for studying and improving the own preparation than to the past.
In spite of the evolution of the school arrangements, there are always advantages and drawbacks as well.
Thus, what are the advantages and disadvantages of studying abroad?
Firstly, a student, who has studied abroad at least some months, has major job opportunities than other students.
In fact, the most important societies and industries of the world have been always searching for a young graduate with this background.
Secondly, studying abroad improves own language skills, English in this case.
It is verified by various research studies, which stated that going abroad for study or work helps to learn fastly a foreign language.
Moreover, it can make a person feel more self-confident, with a improvement in the social relationships.
However, there are also some possible drawbacks.
For example, it comes out great costs, from the economic point of view.
Therefore, a further issue might be the distance between the student and his family.
It is not so easy leaving all and going to another country, totally different and so far from home!
It corresponds to break all our habits and start again.
It takes a lot of time to get used to a new different (and strange sometimes) lifestyle.
In any case, it is an incredible experience that can change our own life and will remain in our mind forever.
It is worth absolutely.
