I am writing this letter because I saw your article this morning about your idea to ban mobile phones out of restaurants and other public places.
I would like to share my opinion about this idea, so you hopefully change your mind.
The first thing to mention is that all people in this country are free to choose where they want to use their mobile phone.
Using a mobile phone in public places is not a crime and therefore it could not be banned.
Secondly, a lot of humans use their phone for functional purposes.
For example, when an employee has a work meeting with an empoyer they can meet each other at the workplace, but it is also possible that one of them works in a restaurant and the other one works from home.
In this case they need to call each other.
So it would be very unpractical when phones are not allowed anymore in restaurants.
When I was reading your letter I could understand what your intention was to ban mobile phones.
Everyone is now a days only foccused on their screen.
This means that nobody makes new contacts anymore when they are, for example, on their way.
Also the social aspect in a restaurant or shop disappears, because nobody talks to each other anymore.
But in this case, I would like to suggest to make people aware of their actions in stead of to ban phones from public places.
In conclusion, I have noticed your letter and I would be aware of my actions in the future, but I do not think it is a well taken decision to forbid mobile phones from public places.
