Some prefer to live longer without adventurous life.
Others, however, are concerned that once in a lifetime means there is no second chance.
Thus, they would attempt to challenge everything as they can and go on adventures, when they are living in the world.
As far as I am concerned, living an exciting and extraordinary life is more valuable than long term but boring life.
There are several points that will be addressed below.
Firstly, life is irreversible.
No one can predict whether afterlife exists or not; therefore, we should seize the moment and try to challenge the unknown when we are young.
Eventually, those difficulties and challenges we have conquered and go over are turning into unforgettable memories in our life.
Additionally, human beings are fickle.
Some people choose a peaceful life at first.
However, when they are dying, they start regretting countless things they have not done before.
People desire to live in peace and quiet; thus they would avoid doing unpredictable behaviors which may bring unstable and risky factors into their life.
However, health conditions should always be an inevitable issue once people are getting older.
For instance, some old people may have dementia or they are out of action.
It not only brings problems but also becomes a part of burden to their families and offsprings.
Thus, it seems living too long still may not have a good quality of life even though the life is peaceful.
To conclude, everyone will face the end of human\u2019s life, thus the quality of life is more important than quantity, and we should value quality.
Most people watch interesting shows or movies on the television to entertain themselves.
The question is whether televesion can also be used for education purpose.
Regarding this topic, the opinions are mainly divided into two groups.
Some of them think that we can use television for education.
Other argue that television is dominantly used for entertainment and it is difficult to use it for education.
The supporters state that we can use various type of television programs to educate our children or to accelerate our knowledge about the unkown field.
For instance, there are plenty of programs for English learning, or basic cognitive training programs for childern.
They are well designed for children with many funny features so that childern can learn the new knowledge and will not be bored.
Furthermore, there are also many different documentation videos for adult to extend their horizon.
However, opponents argue that it is quite difficult to implement this ideal concept with television. Since there are so many obstructions especially when children watch the television.
For example, they pay much more attention to the funny szenarios than the content.
Futhermore, there are also many advertisements while the program that will also disrupt children from learning.
Finally, most children, as well as most adults, are more likely use televisions to watch shows or movies than learn new kownledge.
As a result, television can be used for education.
However, due to various drawbacks, it may not be the optimal tool for this purpose.
