To: Glenda Smith, English teacher at West Academy From: Michelle Inglis Subject: A new school year Introduction This report describes what should be done to achieve our goals in this new school year.
Reading skills To begin with, our reading skills have been practised for ages and we are pleased to see that we can now understand longer and more complex texts about of wide variety of topics.
Listening, speaking and writing skills On the other hand, more listenig, speaking and writing practice must be added in order to use English more effectively and do well in our studies.
Working hard for achieving our goals More specifically, we are expected to listen as many as possible audio recordings to help us understand extended speech about unfamiliar topics.
In addition, we might improve our writing by analysing different written assignments.
Moreover, as long as we practice our conversational skills in pairs or groups, we will communicate better and we might become more fluent speakers.
Conclusion To sum up, I believe that if the above recommendations are carried out, our English level will be improved considerably and all our goals will be achieved.
