Health or wealth?
With the development of new technology and society, the amount of consumption goods to meet the human demand is increasing dramatically.
Meanwhile more and more people are driven by their consumption desires and want to work harder to get richer.
It is interesting to discuss whether health is more important than wealth.
Some argue that it is more important to be healthy than to be rich.
Others disagree with it.
However, the answer to this question depends on various factors, such as individual financial situation, the comprehension of social security, value choice and personality.
Since these factors varies for different people and countries, it is no wonder that people have different choices.
For instance, most employees work round 72 hours per week in China. Because they usually have high expenses and may also have morgage debt to pay back each month.
Furthermore, there is no effective social security, Chinese must save money for themselves and for their parents, just in case.
As a result, many people have already suffering from various health problems at a very young age.
In a highly delevoping society, it is hard for people who are not driven by overwhelming consumption desire.
Therefore, most Chinese decide to work harder to get richer.
Nevertheless, many German choose another life style than Chinese.
Many German choose to have a fun and relaxing job and have a better work-life balance.
Most people in Germany works no more than 40 hours per week.
Some of them even only work 20 hours weekly to have more free time for their family or their hobbies.
Because the social security in Germany is relatively comprehensive and sufficient, people don't have so much uncertainty to worry about.
Some people believed that health is crucial than wealth, I also have the same concept as them.
Money cannot buy health despite having the ability to acquire the best medical system however; money is earned through hard work.
Nowadays there a rapid growth of competition in the market as the world is constantly changing thus people are fighting to keep their jobs and solve their bread and butter issue forgetting how important their health in a stressful environment.
Being overworked can lead to health problem such as fatigue, increase chance of having hypertension and other health problems.
But there are some health problem that is incurable take Human immunodeficiency Virus (HIV) despite nation pouring money into research it have yet find a cure.
On the other hand, health can bring joy in our life for an example, if someone is on a trip enjoying parties and all sort of crazy thing while being healthy but all of the sudden he fell ill not being able to spend his last few days on wonderful trip, everything will turn into anguish.
Furthermore, if you were healthy, you would be able to gain wealth.
The reverse is not possible.
Health gives you the ability to enjoy what life has to offer, and create experiences that are often more cherished that physical goods.
Therefore, I conclude that health is more important that money although money can bring joy to some people life but greed will one day overcome them turning them into a demon
