I don't see any problem with being as old as the whole century.
Maybe your health condition will annoy you sometimes, but with my perpsective, I won't have got this old until the time, when all cars will hover in air like some balloons.
I mean, health and medical services are surely going to be not only more accesible, but also better, faster, more precise and less painful.
Imagine that, being a centenarian, but feel like in your middle sixties.
I'm not afraid of that.
When this demands are fulfilled, I am inclinating towards the first option.
I simply like my pace, and peace.
Maybe I used to be a bit ferocious, but how many persons in their teenage years didn't, hm?
There is no need to live your life intensively, without any sleep, practically surviving from day to day.
In my humble opinion, settling down, eventually don't moving a house much, having a good wife, husband or any other partner, maybe make some kids, Doing a stable and prospering job, going for the culture, simply fighting with the life normally.
You may enjoy the rush, adrenalin and joy of your short life, but it's important to realize, that anyone of us can hide a great potential.
In your later life, some people can contribute to this society so much and although some geniuses have died rellatively young, they can't be the majority.
So, shorter life can be a waste.
All of this is only my opinion.
Note this.
