There seems like a divide between school having students not to take any music class and school forcing students to study and learn to play a musical instruemnet.
Given such division, it seems plausible that we should let student choose depending on whether he or she likes music.
Surely, there is a scientistic fact that music can develop students ability in the aspect of imagination and preception.
Besides focuing on acdemic studies, music can relieve students pressure and have a fair judgement.
However, it is not always true that every student has the interest in studying and learning music.
By involving music in a must requirement at school could increase students' burden in studying, and therefore, it could affect his or her academic performance in other subjects.
Rather he or she likes music or not, the choice should be up to student preference instead of forcing them to choose what to study or what to learn.
Otherwise, it could have a negative impact on students' development.
