Personally, I think office's design is an important issue for the producivity and efficient of collaborators, due to I consider the offices must have a more open design, with no walls separating employees from their coworkers.
First of all, it is known that the most successful companies which have won the awards as the best place to work, they care about the places' desing where their collaborators performance their activities every day; they don't have walls separating the peers, because they consider that walls can mean a line which restrict the collaboration and creativity inside the company, hence the rate of new strategies and new plans of actions reduces.
Apart from that, when there are no walls in the offices the people perceive more fairness and equality, and implies a way to be more dynamic and adaptable about the coming changes, this latter is essential owing to the business world is full of uncertainty and complexity.
Adittionally, it is important to consider the health of workers not only phisycal but also mentally, when it is designing the offices.
So, according to some studies the spaces where the people work must be wide enough to allow them walk and clear their minds so as to reduce the stress levels, increase the creativity and to promote the movement in their sedentary lives.
On the top of that, it is claimed if the offices have ergonomic designs the productivity of the workers improves due to the collaborators feel more comfortable and satified, I would like to drive home this vital part, when workers don't have worries about the space where they have to work or they don't have negative feelings about the discomfort, they can focus on what they're doing and have more energy for the activities as a result they leverage their sinergy in teamwork.
Finally, I think the spaces for offices should be wide and ergonomic for the administrative employees, in order to promote the efficiency, creativity and productivity
