Introduction The purpose of this report is to evaluate Write and Improve website and to answer is it a helpful tool in learning English.
It will also consider possible future developments.
I have been using this website for three months now and I have completed around twenty writing tasks.
Advantages First of all there are plenty of writing tasks availble on the website.
Starting from basic lavel, the user can make his progress completing more advanced tasks.
The checking system works very fast.
An user waits only few minutes for checking results.
Disadvantages Although the checking system works very fast, it doesn't contain more precise information about kind of mistakes made by users.
Basically, it forces you to check what you did incorretly outside of Write and Improve.
In my opninon designers of the site should think about changing this solution.
Recommendation.
I would strongly recommend using Write and Improve website.
Not only it helps developing writing skills but also allows users to express their opinions on lots of different topics.
I went to Panama when I was 10 years old.
I saw lots of interesting things like The Panama Canal.
It is a famous landmark of human engineering which links the Atlantic and Pacific oceans to create an essential sea route.
This gives the possibility of being a short and cheap transit route for ships responsible for transporting goods.
I also went to an island called Chichime that belongs to a region called Guna Yala.
Guna Yala is an indigenous region in Panama, inhabited by the Guna ethnic group.
There I pass two days I swam in the sea and walked through the island.
I have been into the Biomuseum, too.
It is a natural history museum that is located in Panama City.
Its intention is to change the way we see, understand and conserve nature and its biodiversity.
It was my favourite trip because I learnt a lot of new and amazing things about the world.
Before I decide what life I prefer I want to clear up the definition of intense.
Because what does intense exactually mean?
I my words, intense means a busy life.
Not onlt a life full of adventures but also a life full of hard work and strict deadlines.
Taken in consediration this definition I woul prefer a calm life until 100 years old.
I choose this one because of personal events.
A few years ago my mother got a heartattack.
This was a consequence of to much pressure.
She wanted to move, wanted to achieve at her job and had to much to care about.
It delivered stress and whorse consequences.
In order to enjoy my life I want to relax.
I don't want a lot of stess in my life.
I think while having a calm life you can still have a lot to look out for.
There are fun things to do and several occasions to celebrate life.
Why would you rush your life if you can enjoy if for many more years?
I do have a sidenote to my statement.
What I need most in my life is my family and friends.
I want them by my side for those 100 years.
Because celebrations without having some to celebrate something with? So relax, don't stress and enjoy life.
Should we free all the animals?
In XXIst century a lot of eco-friendly movements gained popularity.
Some of them have been proposing deleting the zoos.
They argue that all the living creatures should be free and deserve better treatment.
Are we supposed to open the gates and set the lions and other creatures free?
It's an issue we should discuss.
Eco movements claim that animals can be happy only when they live in their natural enviroment.
Personally, I can not agree with that.
In my opinion animals that live in zoo are the lucky ones.
They have safety and food and they don't worry that some predator may eat them tommorow.
Although, sometimes it's a pitty to look at siuch a majestic animal like a tiger to be kept behind the bars, but we should remember that by doing this, we help to preserve some kinds of animals.
For example, pandas wouldn't survive if we don't keep them in zoos.
Moreover, I think that children can learn somethig going to the zoos.
In the future they may become nature lovers.
In conclusion, I think that the zoos should furrther exist.
This is the solution I would recommend.
