Video games are one of the most used medium of entertainment at the moment.
They are loved by children, who used them more and more.
However people are divided by different points: someone believes that video games are dangerous for health.
On the other hand, somebody stated how video games are useful and may have positive effects.
What is the right choice ?
Are there any other strategies?
Personally, I would argue that playing video games for many hours may involve issue, from view one to hard headaches.
It is confirmed by the fact that more and more children and teenagers wear glasses nowadays.
Concerning about some positive effects of these games, I believe they are improbable.
It depends on the genre of game which we are playing.
Many war games and action ones have been available for years and often they are requested by children rather than adults or teenagers.
It would be a problem from the educational point of view.
A child who played this kind of game could show a more aggressive behaviour than one who didn't played it.
I think that children have to read books and stay outside with other ones as well.
It will be funnier than staying at home.
I hope their parents will get the right choice for their sons.
Nowadays our society teaches us to chase wealth, but is it really the key to hapiness?
Personally, I believe that keeping a good health is more valuable than living in luxury.
First of all, unless we are healthy, we cannot make the most of our life and never achieve our full potential.
Therefore, we should take better care of the aspects of our health that are in our control such as exercise, food and sleep.
But, in order to have a healthy lifestlyle, we do need enough money to cover our basic needs.
Although it's stressful when we are worried about little money, a huge amount of it won't make us happier.
For example, studies of lottery winners show that after a relatively short period of time, they are no happier than they were before their win.
On the other hand, for a healthy body and mind it is essential that we do as much physical activity as possible.
But, the rich are supposed to have their luxury houses cleaned and their fancy cars repaired.
As a result, they do less exercise than is required.
In conclusion, from my point of view, the health is the most important treasure in our life.
My holidays in norway: My grandparents and I, at the age of eleven went to trip to norway to visit my aunt in easter-holidays.
This was a very special trip for me, as it was the first time to travel without parents and siblings.
We went by plane, disembarking from the airport of Frankfurt and arriving in the capital of Norway, Oslo.
