There were many discissions about which work enviroment is most productive.
The most offices I vistited, there was an open space where employees have their own desks.
They can talk to each other, discuss something but also hear each other on the phone.
So there are some advantages and disadvantages about an open office.
The advantages are that employees can see each other.
They can know right away if your are avalible for questions or your busy.
It also a quite nice ambiance.
However, there are some disadvantages.
Most of the time it is rumours.
Different kind of people are talking, to each other and on the phone.
It's also not possible to discuss something in private.
However, there are some offices who have cubicles.
This can be good for the productivity of the employees.
Unfortantly, most employees find this very lonely.
They like to talk to their colleagues.
Talking to colleagues motivates employees.
To conclude, I think working in cubicles is productive for a few hours.
For the long term I would recommend a more open design.
Almost everyone associates holiday season with fun, making new friends and having the time of their lives.
I agree with that associations wholeheartedly.
When it comes to describe my best holiday ever, one specific trip pops up in my head.
It was two years ago.
I was 18 and it was one of my first holiday with my friends.
We went to a Bulgaria as a group of 6 friends.
Three of them was my best buddies, and there was 2 girls yet.
We were having a great time there.
We had a hotel within walking distance to the sea, and there was that marvellous vietnam restaurant on the way.
We were making a stop there very often.
But not only due to these entertainments it was my best holiday.
During that trip, i got into a realationship with my old friend, Marta.
That atmosphere of holiday carelessnes surely made it easier.
That was my best trip, and holiday as well, ever.
I found a love of my life, the one that i'm engage with now.
We all have great memories from there and will be reminding that time probably for the rest of our lives.
University represents a special moment in the life of a student.
The carrier and the future job depend on this kind of preparation.
At that moment, students can decide to go away for studying or living at home with their parents.
These two possibilities have advantages and drawbacks.
Firstly, one advantage might be the possibility to be very close to the faculty.
There will not be necessary to use transports but it is possible to go there by walking or by riding a bike.
Moreover, another advantage is to stay with your own without being stressed by old daily issues.
Therefore, you might get more relaxed, paying attention on your studies and activities.
In addition to it, you can meet new people and make new friends at the university.
What a stunning experience!
However, there are some drawbacks.
For instance, your habits will change drastically: you will have to organize your routine differently, doing houseworks and cooking for yourself.
In this sense, everything you neglicted up to now.
It is time to roll up your sleeves!
In spite of these difficulties, university life is an incredible experience.
In my opinion, I would prefer to live on my own rather than staying at home with my family.
