I think all students should have to study music because all the advantages and benefits it brings about.
Besides studying music is a great opportunity to develop skills and qualities in students.
First of all I want to drive home some of the benefits of learning to play a musical instrument, the first one is the development of the creativity and use of the left hemisphere of the brain of students which as a consequence they can have success on other activities at school.
Besides, other benefit of studying music is that it can make people feel relax and focus, according to some studies, the people who play or study music can reduce the rate of stress in their lives and can release good hormones as serotonine and dopamine, which make them feel happier and have a better wellness.
Apart from that, the music is a way to express ideas, feelings and thoughts hence it contributes to improve the emotional intelligence in students which mean an amazing advantage for the students' future in their relationships, self-esteem, empathy as well as self control.
Furthermore, when students learn about music they can communicate with other people no matter from where they are, because music is an universal language.
On the other side, there are so many people who don't have the oportunity to study music or learn to play musical instrument as piano, guitar, violin or ukelele even when they desire it and they dream with it, so if schools can teach them about music and how to play a musical instrument this can be a chance for the students to dedicate their lives to the music and in the future they could likely be excellents and renowed artists.
Finally, I would like to say that learning to play a musical instrument and studying music are not only two ways to promote the creativity and art in the students but also the music is a way to share feelings and thoughts, a way to connect with many people from different places from different languages.
