Since a few weeks I started to use Write and Improve.
This is a website where you can pratice your English writing skills.
The main feature is that is checks your writing immendiately.
The computer give feedback about how much you wrote about the topic, how youre sentences are and correctes some incorrect words.
With yellow marks it says where you need to improve.
For me the usage of this website is very helpful.
I started two weeks ago and have already imporved my writing skills.
Within each essay you write is says on what level you are.
So you can track your own growth.
I need to achieve the level of Advanced English, so for me the notification on which level your are is the thing I like the most.
However, I also like the divers subjects you can choose to write about.
On the other hand, there is one thing I'm not so positive about.
Sometimes the computer says you need to improve a sentence.
But, it doens't says where or how.
I found this very difficult.
Overall, I do like the website and does help you improve your English write skills.
Therefore, I would recommend this website to everyone who wants to achieve an English Certificate.
Recommendation
Studying abroad has became very popular among students in Europe.
Results of the survey conducted by Cambridge University shows that experience of most of the student who went abroad is positive.
But, are there really no disadvantages?
Fisrtly, I will discuss pros of studying abroad.
For sure, students who decide to study in another country are able to exerience living in a different culture.
It may open them for another points of view.
Secondly, students who are usually not wealthy can visit new places and not pay huge amount of money for that.
They can also make new friendships with people with whom they wouldn't normally meet.
But, for some students, it may be very difficult to find in new environment.
For example, it would be hard to adapt for Iranian citizen in some of Western Europe big cities.
Another thing is that level of education is very different among European countries.
So, for some students it is better to stay in their country, where this level is comparably high.
To summarize, I believe that studying abroad is beneficial for students.
They should apply for going abroad if only they have a chance.
To start with, most of the time it's not a good idea to tell a lie.
However, there are some cases where telling an lie is fine.
In the Netherlands we have a holiday called Sinterklaar.
Each year on December 5th an old man visits the country.
He gives presents to children and spreads candy.
However, the old man doens't realy excist.
It's the parents who rent a man in a custome and buy the presents.
The things the children believe are a lie.
However, in this case, the lie brings happiness within it.
It makes people believe in something, something exciting.
At ocassions like Sinterklaas it's okay to tell a lie.
However, in most other scenarios, it's not okay.
It's not okay when young adults lie to there parents about where there going.
In addition, it's also not fear to lie to your partner.
When people tell a lie, they don't consider the consequences.
When people find the truth, most of the time the lie will upset them.
It isn't a nice feeling knowing someone is lying to you.
For example, when your partner is secretly texting with another woman.
You often find him texting on his phone.
You confront him, ask the question why he is on his phone that much.
Do you want him to tell the truth or do you want to live in a lie and found out later?
I think you know the answer.
So my advise, when telling a lie, think about the other his feeling.
Would become happy not knowing or is it better to tell them?
