Some people claim that exercises and staying fit is the most important thing in our lives.
Is this really true?
Or maybe we are excagerating it's importance?
I will try to answer this questions in below essay.
There are plenty of benefits of exercising.
First of all, staying fit improves both your mental and physical health.
Results of the research conducted by Cambridge University clearly shows that even twenty minutes of walk can prevent some serious dieseses.
Secondly, sport may become your new hobby.
It's always better than staying at home and playing computer games.
Moreover, you can meet new people if you start playing team sport like football or basketball.
Are there mmore important matters in our lives than exercisising?
Of course there are.
I can easily think of several. For example providing money for your family, finding true love or staying in touch with your friends.
However, in my opinion finding 30 minutes a day to run or exercise with You Tube video is not a big problem, and benefits are undeniable.
