Nowadays, most of the population lives in cities, either small or big ones, and due to that, villages and towns are starting to dissappear, which leads to several problems such as the lack of medical service.
Firstly, it has been asserted that medicine is one of the most elected and better rewarned jobs, and it is important to take in consideration that this carrear can only be studied in a city, so that is the prime reason for why most medical doctors choose to live in a city rather than a town.
Furthermore, salaries are a crucial issue to have in mind when talking about that problem, since it is well known that city jobs are way better paid than small-town jobs.
Although it is a severe problem, it seems that no solutions are given by goberments or town councils when some of them, could be as simple as raising salaries and offering more advantages to people speciallised in medicine, so they can find convinient moving from a city to a town.
Besides, if that problem was more shown and stressed by the goberments or the social media, it would spread more, and more people would know about it, instead of ignoring it like most of them do.
In conclusion, the lack of medical service in towns is an important problem to tackle since people in towns need medical assintance as much as cities do, and with a little of concern and solidarity, it could be very easy to solve.
