From my perspective, health is more important than wealth.
As we all know, we can buy anything and enjoy evrything we like with wealthiness but I think that health is more imperative than wealth.
Do you know why?
This is because in order to have fun or to enjoy our happiness, the first thing we need to have is a healthy body.
When we are having a sick, we do not have energy to carry out activities in daliy life.
Consequently, we will not feel happy even we are rich .
A person with a healthy body can live a longer life compare to a person who is rich but not healthy.
Honestly, money cannot buys us a new life, cannot buys us time and it even also cannot buys us a healthy body!
On the other hand, a healthy body enable us to have a longer life and it able us to spend more time with our beloved famliy and friends.
If we are healthy , we will feel more happy and cheerful.
As we all know that there is nobody likes to get sick and no one likes to suffer from different kind of illnesses. For example, coughing, fever and getting a cold.
We all know that getting sick makes us feel uncomfortable and we have no energy to carry out our daliy activities.
Thus, what for even we are rich? As we cannot do anything if we are sick.
In conclusion, I totally agree that health is more essential than wealth.
Last week, I went to Da Nang city which is one of the most livable city in Vietnam.
Da Nang is located in the central of Vietnam.
It was the first time I had ever been there.
My first impression about the city was that it was so peaceful.
The polulation is far less than Saigon so that streets are not crownded and people are not in a hurry as people in Saigon.
The atmosphere is so comfortable as there isn't much carbon emission and the temperature is approximately 20 censius degree.
This atmosphere reminded me of Dalat city which is also my favorite destination.
The scenery of Da Nang is so beautiful because it is a coastal city.
Visitors can enjoy a sea view and mountain view at the same time.
In the first morning at Da Nang, I walked out door along the beach and enjoy the breath-taking view here.
It is a once-in-a-lifetime experience.
Around Dang Nang city, there are many tourist attractions which are famous not only in the nation but also well-known worldwide.
I spent one day to visit Ba Na Hill, one of the most popular tourist destination in Da Nang.
I really enjoy the spectacular scenery here and took a lot of pictures.
I wish I could stay there longer.
Today medical doctors wants to stay in cities not just for the money they can get, essencitial facilities and medicines are not available in rural areas, it can be stressful saving lives if you don't have the basics elements to do it.
Another reason is because of their families, in cities they can provide better standard of life, access a better education system for their kids and for themselves, it is important for a medical doctor update their knowledge constantly and in rural areas that's hard.
Some doctors claim they don't get salary regularly in rural hospitals and don't have proper accommodation to stay.
Now, how can we solve these problem?
well, making rural hospitals more attractive for medical doctors.
Reserve post-graduate seats in medical colleges for doctors serving in the public sector, for at least two years.
Improve medical infrastructure in rural hospitals and provide necessary stock medicines and supplies, so they can work without problems.
