I agree with the opinion that learning to speak a foreign language is important these days.
I have three opinions to support the idea.
First of all, speaking a foreign language expands the world we can join.
Our jobs can not be dealt with domestically these days.
In particular, the population in Japan has been decreasing for several years.
At the same time, more foreign people who want to get jobs in Japan are coming to Japan.
Japanese people have to work with foreign people recently.
In addition, it is severe to sell Japanese products only in Japan under the situation.
Thus, Japanese companies should sell their products globally.
If they can only treat Japanese language, they will lose the opportunities to get their products be known in foreign countries.
The situation is the same for the people in other countries.
Therefore, to enlarge people's world, to speak multinational languages is easier way, and the job efficiency will be improved.
Secondly, we can earn a lot of money if we can speak more than one language.
In Japan, English speakers can get a job paid much money, and have a rich life.
Many Japanese don't have a skill for speaking English.
CEFR level for English speaking of most Japanese people is less than B1.
If Japanese who has more than B1 speaking level, he can get a chance to work with people in foreign countries, and he can get higher wage.
In other countries, people who can speak foreign language are elite and able to obtain much salary.
Thirdly, learning to speak a foreign language may help the reading of a foreign document, and the skill let us make a lot of time.
From the technological side, the most reports are written in English.
Thus, we should read these foreign documents to interpret what it is described.
If we can read English smoothly, we will earn any time, and we can conduct any other things.
If we can treat only mother tongue, we would gain limited information.
Learning a foreign language is effective for us to make a lot of time for conducting many jobs.
To sum up, speaking a foreign language such as English is able to expand our job capacities.
It goes without saying that living on your own is one of the most crucial decissions a person has to make in their life.
Moving away while you are studying is increasingly claimed to be the correct decission.
My thoughts about that matter are going to be displayed in this writing.
To get started, I would like to point out some of the advantages living on your own while studying has.
No doubt, once you are at college, your life changes dramatically.
Ever since then, you are not a teenager any longer and you are capable of making some important choices that have significant effects on your future.
One of them could be to choose to live by yourself.
To do so, it is undoubtedly needed to find a job which provided you with the economical resources necessary to afford your expenses, even if it is a part-time job.
By undertaking a job, not only will you understand how hard life can be but also you take some crucial responsabilities such as working in team or dealing with people.
Nevertheless, some drawbacks should be mentioned.
Living by yourself means that you are the one who is responsible for the shores at home.
As a result of working and taking care of the shores, you do not get round to studying as much time as you wish, and that could be negative for you in the way that your academic results can be worse than you expected them to be.
Last but by no means least, I would like to conclude by bringing focus to the fact that had it not been for those drawbacks, living on your own while studying would be the perfect moment in your life for you to find out who you are, who you want to be, and where you belong to.
