Currently, television is globally known as one of the most inneeded things in human's life.
What is the importance of having a television in our own house?
Is television that important?
If one day television disappeared in our life, are humans able to live without it?
Thus, lets take a look the importance of television that brings us.
First and foremost, television not only entertains us, it is also able to educate all ages of people from the young ones to the old ones.
Television creates a window upon the world for us to understand and explore more about the four corners of the world.
For example, we can widely acknowledge the things that happens around us by watching television.
We didn't even need to travel around to get the latest news, we just need to sit on the couch and switch on the television to watch the lastest news.
Isn't it sound so simple and convenient.
From that, we are able to get educated from the news that are reported in the television.
Do you know why?
This is because there are a lot of people shared their experience through the television and we are able to learn some new stuffs from their experience and avoid the same mistakes that they have done.
As the saying goes, 'prevention is better than cure'.
We can prevent the occurrence of the same mistakes that others made and this can reduce the troubles happens in our life.
Beside, we are able to learn other languages by watching television.
For example, there are a lot of people would like to learn Korean language so they watch Korean dramas from the television.
I think this is a quite useful way to learn other languages and be educated.
Apart from that, I have seen many parents allow there children to watch English movies on television.
This is because children are able to develop their English language skills from young age.
From my one of my experiences, my niece is able to speak fluent English at the age of five, I am astonished by her.
After asking her mother, I knew that my niece actually started to watch English movies from the television at the age of three.
This really shows that television able to educate children.
In addition, children can also learn some moral values from the movies.
This can help to nurture a good behavior in the children.
Currently, parents often allow their kids to watch documentary films from the television.
This is the light of the fact that to help them develop vast cauldron of knowledge and know more about the world.
Hence, television can educate people.
