I'm in the process of creating a blog in English languae to satisfy my passion for writing.
After taking a look on Write and Improve, I jumped up the chance to practice and get my English writing to a new level.
I was a bit confused at the beginning when I realised I wouldn't be provided with any basic guidelines a for how to write a correct pharagraph, in stead, I almost only had to cope with tasks which is scheme alowds me choose my appropriate level to start with.
Well, I think this is the place you can totally improve your English yourself by writing and writing again.
Our mission is to keep practising every single day, the program will check your spelling, show the incorrect and track your progress.
Sounds great right?
I feel like I'm creating my own world of writing, I give my resoning and opinion to each debate they provide.
Don't worry, they don't score your presentation based on your persuadable sentences, so feel free to let things out from your sight and comprehension.
Of course, there are always something amerges to challenge your patience.
When I had finished about five or six tasks, they frustrated me with the board on the left showed my levels going down, it made me feel that the more I wrote, the less progress I achieved.
Bearing in mind this must've been first challenge, I put it back to my mind and headed fowards to other tasks.
And step by step, I could finally appreciate my effort when I figure out my English writing has been going so farther than I had expected - less incorrect spelling, less shilly sentences and in less time.
The program will help your English writing skill just like it's done for me.
But don't never underestimate your patience in this case, trust me.
