It is said that 80 percent of a language is vocabulary and only 20 percent is grammar, so this is often overlooked, although it is equally important.
Supported by teachers in face-to-face lessons will help to clarify any issues and even push students above their limits because they can impart some personalised advice.
Studying a language largely based on online lessons requires a high level of self-discipline and self-motivation.
In terms of flexibility, it may be an advantage as different time zones or suffering from illnesses do not matter.
Owing to the fact that the easiest way of internalising a language is being surrounded by it, it is highly recommended to stay abroad to boost the progress of learning.
This can also be a once-in-a-lifetime experience that students always like to reminisce about.
To sum it up, difficulties may arise no matter which method you choose, but drive and determination coupled with patience and perseverance will lead to success.
Keeping this in mind, do not expect yourself to run before you can walk.
