Have you ever had a friend who is able to play at least one kind of musical instruments?
Yes, you might have.
Do you find out that they tend to do everything which has to use brainstorm mostly faster and with better result?
The experts would say that studying music helps them.
So a yes from me.
I totally agree that students should study music, it not only benefits their studying, but also works for some certain situations in their daily lives.
When we start to know more about music, it should be a little hard for some one, but when you keep playing with them, you will longer feel like doing homework, but like making friends.
The point is that you will finish a thing you have never done before, there no reason for a smarter brain you get after acheiving another skill.
You might not use music as your life-long job, but you should learn it as the right support: Firstly, it's helpful for your concentration.
When you're studying to read a song or trying to remember chords to play a song by the guitar, you're required to completely focus on it, because you won't want to break up beautiful pieces of music into chaotic sections.
Yes, you need to learn how to be wholy a part of the song you're playing or creating.
Next, I don't think you would say that you have never been stressed out for your job, even you really love the job.
Surely you can listen to your favourite music to make a balance between work and living life, but if you can play a song for yourself instead, it even work better.
Is it wong when I've just said it a right support for your path of career.
Besides, do you agree that working or studying with a so good memory is something you are quite jealous of someone who have it?
You would go from the attemp of getting each music notes into your head or each complex rythm of some hard songs, to back-up which you can use whenever in your working with the aim to make things more convinent.
Does sound great?
Do you fancy applying a music class today?
Nowadays, most people share the viewpoint that music is not a trustworthy choice when deciding a professional career, in spite of that, music lessons should not be forgotten or ignored, as music provides a great amount of benefits to people of any age.
Firstly, it is undeniable that music may seem to be not as relevant as other subjects at school that could be maths, history or biology, for example; however, some researches about music and learning how to play an instrument easy to handle, have asserted that it can help children to improve their bodily skills, memory, social habits...
Secondly, the amount of music lessons students have is an important point to consider since, given the irrefutable advantages of music, it is also true that music can not be a prime subject.
Therefore, it would be reasonable for students to enjoy from 1 to 3 music lectures per week.
Last but not least, the obligation of studying that subject should be mentioned too, because music should not be a mandatory subject in every school year, instead, students may study it mandatorily only one course so they have more general knowledge, and from then onwards, it is advised to give them the opportunity to choose if they want to continue their music studies or no.
In conclusion, from my point of view, everybody should be enabled to know their study preferences in order to choose what subject pleases them more, and music, can not be excluded from that list.
Today's generation inclined towards the routine of indolent which is hazardous for health.
Being involved in sports might help students to be physically fit and active in any kind of performance whether it is taking part in competitions or studies.
Educational institutes are concerned about the physical fitness to students for the betterment and healthy lifestyle.
I totally agree with the statement that schools must inculcate the sports activities for young people.
To commence with, it is true that sports helps the young generation to build strength to participate in various activities.
It also leads them towards the healthy routine which curbed the sedentary behaviour in any field.
Moreover, it can be seen that people who involves in sports or do regular exercise are more active than those who only sits and enjoy food or stick to their phone.
In addition to, sports activities also build self confidence in students which helps them in achieving their goals.
On the other hand, today's generation is clinging with the technology or mobile phones due to which they got possessive to their gadgets.
Most of the study material are available on mobile phones.
However, it restrics them from outdoor activities.
Furthermore, this sedentary behaviour leads them towards the health issues such as, obesity, anxiety, mental depression.
As a result adults get addicted to the consumption of alcohol, smoking or other substance.
Thus, to dealt with these situations and to make the youth more active parents should encourage their children to take part in sports from the early age.
And school plays a vital role to promote these activities because it is the place from where we adapt the habits.
Having considered all the above points, I totally agree that educational institutes should impose the exercise classes or sports events to evasion of unhealthy diets and the sedentary lifestyle.
It is difficult for most of the children to adopt these habits; nevertheless it is not impossible to obtain in our daily routine.
