These days live alone become common , so some people suppurt live alone and rely on yourself. while others believe that you should be live with your family.
this essay will discuss both sides and will draw my personal conclusion.
in one hands , some students prefer to rely on themselves especially when they graduate from high school , because university sit is usually far from the city , so theye want saving money , for example , transportation and fast food .
in addition , when you get used to provide money and preparing food yourself . you can succeed in forming a family in the future.
so that's why some think it's amazing to get through tough situations on you own.
in conclusion , after careful analysis of point views , I believe that live with your family is very important , especially when you live in ASIA OR AFRICA continent , because people are prefer the Customs and Traditions .
Sone high school students leave their parent's house to live by themselves, whilst others prefer to stay with their family members in a shared house.
In my opinion, it's better to stay with the family because they can provide the unconditional support during critical situations , and help their childrens to concentrate on their studies.
Even though it is true that students learn a lot by living on their own, I think it is good to live in the family house.
One reason for this is that they provide all kinds of support whenever required without expecting anything in return.
This means that they won't be under pressure to do any sort of household work and as a result, they won't get depressed.
To illustarte this, recent research by leadin psycholigists in the USA has shown that the students, who spend their childhood with their parents by living in same house, never feel demotivated.
Another reason why i believe that it is important to stay with parents is that kids need to focus and concentrate on their studies.
Parents home is the best place for this because they get all the resources and additionally, elder people can share their expierence which would lead pupils to understand the subject better.
For example, according to extensive research,pupils aged between 10 and 20 who stay with elders do far better in exams than those who stay on their own.
In conlcusion, although it may be hard to live with parents, I think they provide the best support which cannot be given by anyone else.
Also students can take help from elders in studies in order to acheive good marks.
