I had a lot of 'best holidays' along my life.
So, choosing just one of them it's a big task for me.
I have been thinking and I decided to chose one when I traveld to the beach to work as an internship in Ubatuba.
In that city, I knew people who are close to me until now.
Every day that I spent over there was full of knowledge, funny and reflection.
I miss so much when I got off working and I went to the beach to swimming and drink some beers with my new friends.
Besides that, my co-workers and I shared the same house for one hole month!
It was funny when we cooked together or helped each other to get out to go to work.
This time was amazing!
When I returned to my city, I thought a lot about what I wanted for my life and what were my goals.
Certanly, this hoidays changed my life and I'm grateful for lived all these.
What is life?
Life is very complicated.
It depends on the person.
Some people's life is full of happiness, some people's life is full of surprise, some people's life is full of sadness and even some people's life is full of hardships.
We must choose our own life, we have the right to choose the life we want to live on.
I saw many people's life were tied up by their parents.
Their parents did not give them to have the opportunity to choose their own life.
I am feel quite pity for them.
As for me, I won't let the others to lie a single finger on my own life, I insist to choose my own life no matter how.
If I was given to choose to live a long, calm life until 100 years old or a shorter life but much more intense, I think I would choose to have a shorter life but much more intense.
Do you know why?
This is because living a shorter life does not need to suffer from many different kinds of illness like diabetes, heart attack and hypertension.
When we are getting old, varies of illness and disease will start to come towards us.
This is because when we are old, our body starts to deteriorate and our immunity system will start to decline.
After hearing these, do you still want to live a long, calm but suffer from sickness live?
Of course not!
Everyone get ill when they are old because this is one of the part of life.
This is why I would rather to choose a shorter life but much more intense instead of living a long, calm life.
Plus, we feel very lonely and sad when seeing our own friends and family members passed away one by one.
Sadness and loneliness bottle up our heart little by little when we are losing our loves one.
If I live a short but much more intense life, most of my friends and family will still stay by my side and I am able to confront the most brutal setbacks and hardships with their help.
I am sure that they will seek solace me if I am defeated by failure.
Hence, this are the reasons why I would choose to live a short but much more intense life.
In addition, do you want to see yourself getting old?
As for me, I do not want to see those wrinkles keep on appearing on my face, my hair turning black to white and my back getting more and more hunch.
These are the sign of getting old and this reminds me that I am getting old and need to get more help from the others.
I don't like to depend on the others because this might be a burdern to the one who takes care of you.
Furthermore, a short but yet intense life can make us to live in a good shape and full of different colours.
In conclusion, a long, calm life will not only makes us feel very lonely but also sad.
Therefore, I choose to live a short but intense life over a long, calm life.
Some people believe that nowadays is not necessary to learn languages.
The question is why.
At present, the mobile phone have apps that translate at the moment.
For this, many people thinks that it is not vital.
From my point of view, I consider that it is very important to learn a language.
My reason are: First,when you are reading a book in English, it is different to read a English book that Spanish book.
The meaning of the phrases changes from one language to another.
Second, when you learn a languange , your mind changes.
That is, there are studies that have demonstrated that if you learn another language (different your mother tongue), you will improve your cerebral cortex.
Your brain secretes substance, which help to avoid degenerative illness, like alzheimer.
To sum up, I consider that it is very important to learn languages and discover other cultures.
In Taiwan, there are a lot of people want to learn and improve their English.
English is the worldwide language, and we have to use it in many situations of our daily life, such as business, traveling, and so on.
Recently, I have discovered a helpful tool, Write and Improve, for Englisher learners to practice their English writing skill.
Write and Improve is a free website.
You just need to register as a member or sign in with your facebook account, and then you can use it for free.
In the website, you can choose the level which is suitable for you or which you want to challenge.
When you decide the level, you will notice that there are plenty of questions in each level.
It provides different kinds of conditions for you to practice.
In addition, in the task, there is a timer for you to clock the writing time.
After finishing the writing, you can click on "Check" and see the feedback of your writing.
Moreover, you can revise your writing in accordance with the feedback, and check again.
According to my experience, Write and Improve is an useful tool for people who wants to learn English writing skill.
Practice makes perfect.
Please do the exercises everyday, if you really like to improve your English.
You will find out the effect.
Write and Improve is an app by the Cambrige University made for students in order to improve their writing.
Having used it for almost a month I am going to summerise my experiences with this app in the following.
Firstly, I would like to write about the biggest advantage Write and Improve has, namely the check function.
This means you can write a text and after completing the task, the programmm checks it for you.
This has helped me, not only improve my grammar and vocabulary, but also my style of writing.
Next, the app is helpful because there are many different levels of language.
Therefore, Write and Improve enables their users to improve and move on to the tasks that best fit their needs.
Lastly, I have to mention an aspect of this website I have not found helpful, which is the costs.
Although the fist tasks are for free, most of the workbooks have to be bought.
This is a border for learners who do not have the money to pay for the app.
In conclusion I can highly recommend this app, since it has helped me and many other users improve the English skills.
I started thinking about this question when I was a child, because when I was eight years old I saw the film "Troy" for the first time in my life.
Our history teacher gave us the homework to watch that moovie because we were studying the Greek history in that period.
I was so impressed by Achilleus's character, because he could have anything he wanted: a long life, a wife, health and a family, but he chose, being aware of the consequences, to leave for Troy, knowing that he wouldn't ever come back home.
I could'nt explain why, it was totally unobvious for the little girl I was.
But then, going on whatching the moovie, I got it clearly: he was doing it for glory and immortality.
Living a long and calm and boring life would have make him upset, which is the point of living 100 years if your life doesn't worth to be lived?
Emotions, feelings, experiences are what keep us alive, so I would prefer living a shorter life, but full, lived and not wasted, instead of spending my time doing nothing because everything is dangerous.
If you stop a moment and think about the risks, you will understand that everything is risky, so you wouldn't do anything.
I'm not talking about having mad experiences, I'm just talking of living freely and fully, tasting every single moment that life has to offer to us.
Besides, we have just one life, it's pretty unconvenient to waste it.
