Should computers and tablets completely replace books in schools and universities?
When there are more and more computers, tablets, some people asked themselves something like that.
To my way of thinking, computers and tablets should completely replace books in schools and universities.
Firstly, computers and tablets are much better than books because they can hold a million time more infomations than the average 400-800 pages book.
If you want to find something, it will take you 15, 20 even 30 minutes to get infomations from books.
But with a computer or a tablet, it would take less than 5 minutes to get them.
Secondly, computers and tablets hold much more types of data than a book.
If you are carrying a computer or a tablet, that also means you are carrying a thousand books.
Finally, they are more convenient.
An e-book costs much cheaper than a tradiontional book.
The informations in a digital form can be edited, shared easily.
This makes them overall convenient for students who might not be able to afford one copy of a book each.
In a nutshell, computers and tablets are much more convenient than tradtional books.
They sould completely replaces books in schools and universities.
