It is argued that all the students should be pushed forcefully to take part in sports games at least 3 times in a week.
I agree with this because those activites would help people to live a healthy life and are important for students to focus and concentrate.
Even though it is true that sports activites take a lot of one's time, I think these activites are very important for all the individuals, especially for students.
One reason for this is that it would lead to them losing weight and leading a much healthier and happier life, so in long run, they would enable them to be an active individual.
To illustrate this, recently norway implemented strict rules and regulations for all the high school students to play games on any three days in a week.
This had a dramatic effect on keeping the weight under control.
Another reason they are necessary is that students can achieve better results in exams.
This is because exercises will make the students tierd, so they can get the sound sleep in the night.
This would let them to focus in their classes and understand the subjects better.
As a result, they can perform better in class test and in final exams and eventually, get a well-paid job.
For example, there is some evidence to suggest that pupils aged 1between 10 and 15 who play any games do far better in exams than those who don't do any type of activites.
To conclude, although students might not find sports games interesting, I think it is important becuase students can live a beautiful and happy life.
Also, they can acheive better marks in shcools and universities.
