Compared with the television broadcast in other countries, like the United Kingdom or the USA, Italian television is very young.
During its first decade, Italian television had, as its first aim, an educational role.
Indeed in the 50s more than half of the Italian population was not educated and they did not speak Italian but they speak dialects.
The national television broadcast, RAI, had some programs with the aim to help school in learning Italian language, history, civics, etc.
RAI had this educational role until the 80s, when it changes its aim to better compete to private broadcasters.
Since the entertainment overflow the educational role, to the point that, on the contrary, it began to have a bad education on the audience.
In the last few decade, national broadcast tried to come back in its educational role, even with such little projects.
Now we watch new television channels with cultural and educational aim.
