In my opinion videogames represent a great hobby for children but they must be limited.
As everything, they have good and bad things.
In fact, they are not a useless thing because, due some studies, they can help children improving their skills and intelligence.
But they are also instructive for them because specific type of games such as games with a story line or a plot based on mythology or history can help children increasing their knowledge and their interests and educating them about important values like love, respect or bravery too.
Obviously they have also negative things, such as inadact games for people under eighteen years or the easy access to the community.
The latter can be a good thing but, for children, it can be also dangerous expecially without a parent's supervision which could avoid any type of cyberbullying.
So, I think videogames are a great instrument for children but hey must be used wisely.
The future of travel Do you ever wonder about the future of travel?
I\u2019ve always imagined how the technology could change the ways to travel over the world.
It\u2019s why I did a research about the currently progress about it.
To begin with, the ways in how we can travel have changed notoriously.
The transport is faster and cheaper, such an airplanes, boats.
Other thing is the fact that if you want to know new places you could do it through virtual tours even though we could do space travel.
In other hand the attractions will be the same, along the years people always want to visit the same places, pyramids, museums, archeological sites and so on.
Other thing to consider is that unexpected trip cancellations, delays and emergencies will continue to occur.
In conclusion people think that in the future will be easier travel, almost everyone will be able to pay for a trip and the space travels will be a possibility.
But we have to be consents that there will be situations about travels that won\u2019t change and we couldn\u2019t avoid like bad weather or technical problems.
