What is more important: health or wealth?
Different people have different answers to this critical questions.
Everyday, we see people sacrifice sleep in order to work extra hard and secure monety gains.
We also see people spend their hard earned money to treat a disease that has caused them a lot of pain.
There seems to be a cycle of prioritizing wealth and then realizing that what is important is health.
In my opinion, money is very important particularly in the current competitive world, but it is just a mean to and end not an end; what people should aim for is living a healthy life which are free from sickness.
To begin with, one's happines is not fully dependent on weather he has money or not; it is about not experiencing chronic pain wheather mentally or physically.
It is true that sometimes having money can eliviate the pain, but it also could cause the pain.
To illisturate, think of afflunt people.
compared to average person, they experience a lot of stress and worry due to the possibility of losing their wealth.
Moreover, they need to put additional effort to sustain what they have accumelated over the years.
From this example, it seems that not owning much has its benefits.
