What are my reasons for learning English?
I had to think about this question while I was studying English becasue I felt that I was losing my motivation and not performing as I should.
After thinking, I found that I study English for the following reasons.
First, I want to learn English because I need to access the massive content writting in that lanaguage.
As we all know, English is the most spoken language in the world, and in it a large content, such as books, movies, etc.,
has been produced.
By being able to read and understand English, I can easily consume the information and learn from them and that will greatly help me succeed in my life.
Second, English has become the language of business, and anyone who wants to do business on a global scale has to learn it.
Due to development of transportation method and communication, it became possible to trade with other organizations from different countries, and for successful interaction, there must be a common language between the two parties.
English happened to be that language.
In the end, people could learn English for various reasons.
For me, I noticed that there are a lot of materials written in English that interest me.
Additionally, I would like to be able to commuicate with international bussniesses.
An old Chinese curse states: I wish you to live in curious times.
We all definitely live in curious times now.
Everything changed in 2019 when the coronavirus pandemic started.
We will face the consequences for a long time.
How it would affect our ways of travelling?
One thing is certain: it would not be the same.
First of all, in 2021 we still may be forced to focus on domestic trips.
Before the roll out of the vaccine there will be obstacles in crossing the borders.
I expect that the situation may go back to normality in early 2022.
Secondly, the costs of the planes tickets may rise dramatically.
A lot of airlines went bust and those that continue operating may be forced to cut losses.
Apart from that, even before the pandemic, some of the people claimed that we shouldn't use the planes because of the environmental issues.
Does it mean that we will stay at home?
I don't think so.
Maybe we will switch into electric cars and trains?
We'll see soon.
Poland is a country where we struggle to improve the health system.
A lot of things has changed but there are still a lot to do.
One of the most serious issues is lack of medical doctors in rural areas.
They usually prefer to work in big aglomerations or even go abroad to countries like Sweden, Germany and United Kingdom.
What is the reason of this situation?
In my opinion, main cause is the salary.
In rural areas doctors usually earn less than those, who work in big cities.
Secondly, life in rural areas is less interesting.
Doctors study at Universities which are located in big cities and they are used to the hustle and bustle.
Living in a small village may seem very boring at first glance.
What can be done about this?
I believe there are several options possible.
First of all our government should rise the salary for the doctors who decided to move to remote area of thecountry.
Secondly, there should be investments made in the infrastracture.
Fast trains and good roads would allow to travel fast to all of the big cities.
I have watched many films in the past, and I have a few that I like more that others.
If I have to choose one to be my favorite, it would be Leon the Professional.
It was filmed in the 90s in New York City and has unusual and interesting story that made it in the top of list of favorite movies.
The movie begins in an apartment building in one of New York neighbourhoods, and in it there in a family that hardly can be called a family.
There were frequent shouting and arguments; no body got along with others.
It is not suprising when it become known that the father is involved in illegal activities with criminals and corrupt police men.
One day, the corrupt police men invaded the building and broke into the apartment.
they search every room in the apartment looking for drugs that they have given to the father.
As soon as they learned that he does not have the drugs, every one was murdered without mercy even a small child.
Right before the police men arrive in front of the building, a young girl, who was about 8 years old, had just left her troubled family to get a break from all the negative energy and also to bring some milk.
She was lucky, but she still need to return to her family.
She had no other place to go.
While she is entering the building, she felt that something is wrong.
She could hear noise that is not familiar.
She continued cautously, and when she approaced the door of her apartment, there was a well-built man carrying a machine gun.
Frightened, she did not stop and contiued walking stright passing her apartment door; she peeked and saw her father on the floor covered in blood.
She knew what happened, but tried her best not to show any emotion, or she will also be killed.
While walking, a door blocked her way.
It a neigouber's aparment door.
After a moment of hesitations, she knocked on the door a few times and waited for rescue.
As she was losing hope of escaping that tough situation, the door opens.
She felt like it was the door of heaven.
It was Leon, who opened the door, a professional hitman.
He was watching the whole event and know what happened to her family.
He saved her, but he is now responsible for her as she has nobody.
How could a hitman take care of a child whose entire family was just murdered?
You need to watch the movie see what happens next.
A great number of university students live far from home and live independently.
However, other ones live at home with their family members.
I am of opinion that students who live far from home have a greater chance to develop their soft skills, and this essay will outline a couple of reasons.
To begin with, Living independently has been commonly regarded as an essential element in a person's development because of its beneficial impacts on other aspects in person.
A student living far from home must adopt their surroundings by expanding a wide range of relationships with other counterparts and getting used to a series of unexpected situations revolving around mainly financial burden.
Having multiple practical experiences helps the student become stronger and confident not only in school life but also at a societal level.
Besides, the university period offers students especially those who live far from home numerous wonderful opportunities, like either getting a part-time job or involving a voluntary campaign, to develop their soft skills including presentation, and team-working which are really essential after graduation.
Without the time restriction by the parents, a living far from home student in university could spend hours hanging out or studying in a group with other students which helps bridge the gap between them and constitutes long-standing relationships not only in academic settings but also in far-distant future.
In conclusion, although university students living independently face numerous emerging situations due to the lack of their relatives, this also offers multiple amazing chances.
Getting a part-time job and acquiring long-standing relationships helps the students become mature.
Firstly, I think that volunteer work should be a requirement to graduate in all the schools, because there are several benefits in this type of activity.
For example, it's an oppurtunity to learn about new subjects, including things outside of your social environment.
In addition, an american research from Michingan University stated that people who practice volunteer work live about four years more.
Similarly, another research proved that volunteer workers have a better balance between their professional and personal lives and, consenquently, less stress and more positive energy.
Despite of many people say it's a waste of time, volunteer work can change people minds in a good way by making them be more sensitive and, therefore, understand better the social problems.
In conclusion, a certain amount of volunteer work can be very helpful in order to develop better students as human beings, because that is also included in the school missions.
The technologic development is our present and it will be our future.
For this reason, it will surely influence the way we travel nowadays, hoping that it will make it better.
During the years experts and engeneers have focused their knowledge and capacities on artifical intelligence that will lead the world's logistic in the future.
One of the most important examples is the authomatic drive (or smart drive) which is the idea (and actually the present) of authomatic cars and veichles.
This technology will not only change our own veichles, but will change the public transport too.
In fact, in the next years, we will probably able to find authomatic cabs or buses that won't need a driver, making the transports more efficient and quick.
On the other hand, also private cars will have the possibility to be driven by a specific authomatic system which will make streets safer than now and reducing risks related to driving.
The school of the future Have you ever think about how will be the schools in the future?
As a teacher I\u2019ve always asked myself how will be the school in the future.
World is in a constant change, medicine, communications and education has been changed as well, we know that system education need be innovated.
Firstly with the news technologist and internet, everyone has easy access to information about everything, in consequence teachers won\u2019t the unique source of information then they will become as guide.
Secondly the abilities like public speaking; will be more important than academic knowledge.
However abilities don\u2019t supplant and academic preparation and you\u2019ll still have to learn Mathematics, science or history.
Then professional certifications will be important but never will be such important as an academic titles.
To sum up, the educational system needs to link to the needs of a changing society, we have more access to the information and we can learn thing by our own, but a professional degree and help by professors always will be important and essential.
