To begin with, I am going to talk about if I believe that television can entertains and also educate.
On the one hand, I consider that Television should be more educated because it is possible that some type of programm can distorts reality.
The younger people believe that it is possible to earn money by doing anything.
On the other hand, I consider that nowadays television is changing, especially programms .
For example, there is new show called "El condesador de Fluzo" and I think it is perfect for undertanding history or to discover new things.
In addition, the people who go to the show explain things it very well.
In this show there are writters, comedians and historians of all kinds.
To sum up, I would like to say that I really think that television is changed for the better. Especially for young people do not fall into stereotypes.
In my opinion television is a good vehicle to educate but it is often bad for that aim.
In fact, there are programs that could be very diseducative for young people which could give a bad vision of the world, such as gossip's programs or violent cartoons and serieses, but also with programs that include a bad language that could influence people that watch it.
On the other hand, television has great features that could make it great for education, such as the news, films' channels, sport's channel and so on.
But I think that nowadays people are looking to something different from television.
For example, people prefer using internet and its features to search something that they don't know, learn new languages or discover new things every day.
In conclusion, I think that television is a valid educational vehicle but it will be replaced by digitalization soon.
