First of all, I would like to set about with wealth, in other words, money.
Indeed, you can manage to do loads of things such as buying expensive cars or having a spectacular phone.
Even though you afford to buy something essential, you cannot buy affection and health.
Have you ever considered what will happen to your tremendous fortune after you die?
Your facilities or the extent of your fortune won't be important.
Besides, you will marry someone devoid of affection, enthusiasm, and sympathy. A person who won't appreciate you.
Accordingly, you won't be happy unless you find someone who loves you.
Consequently, your money won't be valuable unless you have a soulmate and health because you cannot manage to something without these crucial things.
My recommendation is for you to be aware of your treasure.
In my opinion, this is a paradoxal statement.
In general, I think that health is surely the most important thing in people's lives because without it we wouldn't be able to do anything.
On the other hand, in countries like USA, the sanity is not free, and poor people could be discirminated from sanity treatment.
It is also true that middle class' people can live healthy without an enoromous richness, but it's also true that there are rare illness that require specific operations and treatment, and they could be too expensive for them.
Otherwise, I think that everyone should have access to every sanitary treatment, but it is actually an utopic idea due to the economics problems that are involving the world.
For this reason, I think that the two things are truly connected much more than people expect, because without health wealth couldn't exist, but without richness, nowadays, health is not guaranteed for everyone.
