Is this important to always tell the truth?
I would say yes but not for every situation.
One thing for sure, how much we trust on one person depends on a mount of believable presentation and possibility they can give us.
Each activity or relationship in our society is formed based on platform of the belief we create for ourselves and for others.
There might be some times we spend on seeking somewhere we refer to be part of and will never or little be in doubt of people surround.
Living in an environment of the truth is the guaranty about being always clear on social systems and transparency of any relationships.
It's definitely view of life we all have been trying to build in.
One for addition, I know we had been taught to tell the truth since very early childhood that was an basic installment for the awareness of any situations later.
Gowing up and whenever we refuse the truth with some certain situations, we are likely to feel apologetic and regrattable.
On other hands, it is also important for sometime not telling the truth.
In some circumstances, we are required to lie someone if this benefits them.
I remember it called 'white lie' which is forgiven without guit as you find it the most possible selection to apply.
If your lie does not take a toll on anything or anybody, it is fine to use then but you should accept one thing signifcant is that you may be less beliveable later in life.
This is definitely a drawback.
Take all factors mentioned into account, telling the true plays a key roll in our lives and society.
But it is completely acceptable to make it lie depending on circunstances and we need to assure that you have positive reson to do it.
I believe having different teachers can bring benefit to the studants.
First of all, each teacher transfers the knowlogy to the studant using a unique methodology.
So, if the studant has only one teacher for several years, this studant won't know learn different things through different ways.
Second, different teachers are able to share many points of views or perspectives about one topic.
It can help the studants to develop critic sense and evolve their thoughts.
If the studant has only one teacher for several years this studant will begnin, early or late, mimetize the thoughts of his teacher.
Third, If the studant has many teachers for several years, it can help the studant set up his character. Because the studant can observer, analyze, and then decide what is right and what is wrong. How each teacher handle with different situations.
Futhermore, having many teacher you won't became boring.
In resume, having many teachers have more pros than contras.
I have heard that you, as town council, is thinking about banning the use of mobile phones on public transport and in shops and restaurants.
I think this idea needs to be analyzed carefully.
Firstly, due to the increasing use of mobile phones in public spaces, an American research stated that people are losing the ability to have a real conversation.
As evidence, nowadays it's common to go to a restaurant and see people around the table, all of them just using their cell phones without talking to each other.
In other words, people are become increasingly addicted to mobile phones that they are not paying attention to the real world.
Therefore, banning use of cell phones in these places would force them to strike out a conversation with someone and be more aware of their surroundings.
Despite this, the use of mobile phones has allowed people to contact someone quicker.
For this reason, cell phones can be very helpful to get people in touch especially in emergencies.
These emergencies embrace all the kinds, such as work and health emergencies.
In sum, banning completely the use of mobile phones on public spaces, like restaurants, shops and public transport, is not the right choice to do.
In my opinion, the use should be permitted only in emergencies, because it's impossible to ignore some benefits of cell phones in modern life.
