According to an American research, telling the truth all the time time has several benefits to human health.
For instance, it can be less stressful to your life, because you do not need to overthink or to be worried all the time about the possibility of being caught.
Moreover, it improves your memory considering that telling a lie demands some cognitive effort and this can be harmful to your mind overtime.
To put it more simply, always telling the truth can provide a better life quality.
However, in some cases, the truth can be painful and unpleasant to your listeners.
To give an illustration of that, sometimes a person is in a bad mood and expect some compliments to encourage her, but you decide to tell the truth by saying desmotivating words.
In this situation, the truth hurt the other person feelings and certainly did not improve her life quality or reduce her stress.
Therefore, telling the truth is not always the better choice, unless it's related to violate a law.
In this case, the truth is better, because you are going to get caught either way.
On the other hand, when it envolve people feelings, it's important to analyze each situation carefully, owing to the influence that the words can affect other people minds in a good or in a bad way.
Learning a new language Regard to the question whether learning to speak a foreign language is as important nowadays as it was in the past, the answers differ among different group of people.
More specifically, the answer for this question depends mostly on people's education level and type of occupation.
On average, the more educated people are, more likely they learn foreign language.
While most blue collars or people only work locally may not need to learn to speak foreign lanuages, most white collars or people who work in a international atomsphere necessarily to master at least one foreign language, especially English.
Due to dramastic development of globalization and international trading, mastering one or more foreign languages is seen as a basic skill that employer will expect from their employees.
Beides work, there is also increasing need to speaking foreign language in the vacation if you travel to another countries.
All in all, there is a general increasing requirement of speaking foreign language, e.
g.
English these days than in the past.
Personally, I have several reasons for learning English.
First of all, over past years the English language has become the most important language of the world and It is nowadays an international language that is spoken by everyone.
For this reason, learning English is not only a pleasure but also a duty to be part of a globalized world as it is in our present.
On the other hand, I really like the phonetic as well as the culture that is related to it.
In fact, I think that the traditions and the story of this language are very fascinating.
For me, learning English is also a great opportunity to have a speed contact with computers, where English is the universal language.
In the end, I think that English should be teached at an high level of quality in every country, to give the possibility to everyone to communicate without any barriers.
