Recently a lot of schols have been adapting new solutions in order to create possibilities for students to learn practical skills.
Some of them allow pupils to do some voluntary work in time of classes.
Is this a reasonable solution?
It has became a subject which is discussed by newspapers and in TV programs.
I will try to present reasons for and against in below essay.
The main reaason that supports students volunteer work is that they can actually help in places where this kind of help is needed.
I mean places like hospitals, shelters and hospices.
There is always something more that could be done there.
Each additional helping hand counts.
Next reason is that student can gain extra experience by helping other people.
I honestly believe that one can not learn such skills in school.
In my opinion these skills may be very useful after graduation.
Also, having volunteer work in your CV may be a factor that will decide about getting a job.
Employers usually prefer candidates who have such experience.
What about reasons against?
I find a very few indeed.
But, you can always say that students should not be forced to do volunteer job if they don't want to.
I guess this supposed to be free decision of each person.
Somebody forced is never a good employee.
To summarize, in my opinion schools should allow students to help in hospitals, shelters etc.
But, it always has to be a free decision of each pupil and his parents.
