In my vision, it is most effective to work in open space that have no walls to separate workers from their colleague.
Some people say that they can concentrate on their job by working lonely.
But, I think that it is not efficient for both themselves and their coworkers.
I have two points about this.
First of all, talking to each other while working is important more than working quietly.
I do not mean that they can talk about anything without job like their hobbies.
I want to say that people working in open space are able to help one another.
Then, helping each other with working leads to not only efficiency but also making relationships between them.
So, it is best way to work in open space.
Secondly, workers can be eager to work by seeing their colleague working.
If they work in separating room, they are possible to focus their job bu cannot see working of other workers.
On the other hand, in open space, there are people working arduously wherever and whenever they see around them.
So, indivisuals in office will want to work their coworkers and it generates multiplier effect.
Lasatly, All in all, I described two points about my idea that it is better to work in open design office than in separating office.
Recently, we can see many changes about how to working.
Then, there are diversities to work in present society.
So, we will have to adapt to working style in the future.
