I've already visited some zoos, one in Brazil and another in Germany.
But, afterwards thinking for a while I concluded that zoos are not good places for animals. Because they are not in their habitat and holding them in a fenced place its stressing for them.
Once ago I've watched a movie called Blackfish on Netflix, which talked about an orc named Tillikum.
It was captured from the ocean where it was living taking care of its group and being humans took it from there to cloister it in one of the most famous aquariums in the world, called Sea World.
There it was taught to jump out of the water and to make funny tricks to entertain the public however, in the backgrouds it was cloistered and stressed out.
But humans did not take that in account, and one day during a presentation the orc freaked out and killed a presenter in front of the public.
That said, I believe that humans must to live with animals in harmony as in the most higher level as possible.
