Inn my point of view I think that both could be a good way to learn English.
In one hand if you have only one teacher for many years you can create bounds with him and he can see your weak points and focus on them, however if you are always with the same teacher and he always teach you the same way you can get bored or maybe his teaching method is not the most suitable for you.
In the other hand if you have more than one teacher you can learn different learning methods because each teacher have different teaching methods and personal characteristics, besides it can be more interesting for you because every year you'll know new people.
To sum up both have good things but if I had to pick one I would pick to have more than one teacher, because I think that it might be more fun and probably better for my learning.
Healthy living is the most popular topic in every year, people believe that it can help you live a longer life.
If you read articles or healthy magazines, it's all about exercise, healthy eating, sleeping, and nutritious food.
So we can't say that exercise is not the most important thing but there are also others things.
Some people may have time for exercise, but not everyone can do that, especially, the working-age population.
Working people are always busy and exhausted with their works, so it's difficult to organize their time for working and also exercise.
On the other hand, there are also alternative options for being healthy such as healthy eating and getting enough sleep.
It's simpler than exercise and everyone can do it.
Although healthy eating is easier than exercise but some countries, healthy foods are more expensive than fast foods.
To solve this problem, people can choose nutritious foods that can find in articles.
A healthy lifestyle is not only about exercise, so we can choose alternative options such as healthy eating, getting enough sleep and choosing nutritious foods.
It's not easy to be healthy but it's important for your body.
