Hello Jim, how are you?
Some days ago, you sent me an email in which you asked me if I had gone to that music concert.
Well, this is the reason why I'm writing this email.
As you know, I went to the concert of my favourite rock band, the Red Hot Chili Peppers.
What an amazing experience!
Listening to own favourite music band at a concert is a totally different experience.
In addition, there were many people, crowded and attached to each other like sandwitches.
But it seemed not to be important with respect to the band.
They were fantastic, performing not only the last released album but also their greatest hits such as 'Callfornication', 'Give it away' and so on.
The whole audience jumped with Flea the bassist and Anthony the frontman of the rock band.
The concert lasted three hours and half more or less.
Time passed very fast!
It seemed to have lasted just some minutes.
Actually, this was just the only drawback.
Anyway, I'm going to see them again.
The next time, you have to go with me!
See you, lots of love Jack
