What are the reasons for this problem?
The reasons are diverse for this reason, so then we will analyze some situation and factors which force to work the medical doctors in some cities instead of a rural areas. -
Notoriety to work in famous Hospital: most of the important Hospitals are in big cities, for instamce Memorial Hospital is in NY City and you can get more reosurces to enter in some research & development projects. -
Experience working on specific specialities: most of the medical doctors want to specialize in specific medical areas like Traumatology, Cardiology, Oncology and Hemathology.
These specialities cannot be practised in small Hospitals or rural areas, so then, physicians would prefer to work at this Hospitals where are in big cities. -
Better Salary: this factor is the consequence of the last 2 factors commented before, if you have experience and notoriety, you will earn more money because you will treat more patients, you will receive some offers from private Hospitals and you can combine your practise at public and private Healt Care, having two salaries that it is quite comment in Health Care environment.
Understanding these 3 Key Factors, that's why they want to work on big hospitals.
I just try to answer your second question "How can it be solved?"
It wil be solved if we can build some big Hospitals which connect some rural areas and meet Notoriety, Experience and Salary, this concept is called Reference Hospital and you can attract some medical doctors to this rural areas and of course to ensure a salary which will be competitive agaisnt the Medical Doctors working on a big cities.
To sum up, if you want to have good medical doctors in a rural area, you should get Notoriety, Experience and Salary, but also, a Work life balance thay you can find in most of the rural areas such as Fresh aire, inner peace, not rush, less stress and live close to mountains or coast.
