English has become a must-know language for most people who want to have a better life, a decent job, etc.
Therefore, many people has tried to learn it.
Some people choose to learn by going to English Centers, the others choose to learn through the Internet.
When you use the second method, you may be confused because there are too many platforms for you to choose.
Today, I will recomend you a new platform, which just has been released recently, Write and Improve.
The name tells everything.
The main features of this tool is to improve your Writing Skill.
That's right.
There are many lessons devided to specific levels: Beginner, Intermediate and Advanced.
It also has the lessons helping you in your IELTS exam.
That's cool, right?
When you finish any tasks, click Check and then wait for the error checking system to check your result.
It will tell you what should be changed, what is necessary or not...
And then, you can check again to see if the changes you did is good or not.
But, nothing is perfect.
This tool is not an exception.
I have tried using for a week and sometimes, I got a problem with the error checking system.
Sometimes, it didn't work well.
For example, in a task, I used the word "Complain" and it recognized that one was not correct???
An other thing I think it's a drawback of this tool is that some of the tasks are not necessary.
For example, it has a task that tells you to write about your experiences you got after helping at a pop concert.
I don't think many people did that thing.
In a nutshell, this tool has its pros and cons.
The cons may make you confused sometimes but in general, this is a good tool for people who want to improve their Writing Skill.
It goes without saying that, living a long and succesful life is a craving every individual has.
However, when it comes to choosing between having a long but calm life and a shorter but more intense one, no doubt I would stand for the second option.
My thoughts about that matter are going to be displayed as follows.
To begin with, I would like to point out some of the reasons why I would undoutedly choose having a shorter but more exciting life instead of a long and calm one.
Should there be something remarkable about our mere existance, it would be surely the fact that we all have just one life.
Owing to that situation, life itself is unique and genuine for every single person, making it the most valuable treasure one has.
We all are well aware of, at some point, our lives will get to an end.
Perhaps because of that statement I consider that, in terms of time, quality prevails over quantity, in the sense of the more experiences you have, the higher sensation of happiness you will feel.
Nevertheless, some drawbacks should be mentioned concerning a shorter existance.
By living lesser, not only do you miss the opportunity of witnessing how your children grow, but also you are not able to get to know how the future gets developed.
Last but by no means least, I would like to conclude by bringing focus to the fact that no matter what your choice may be, the most pivotal thing is that you have to be who you want to be during your lifetime, whether you are understood or not, because that is how you will find the sense of belonging.
Dear town council, I am writing to you regarding the issue of baning mobile phones on public transport , in shops, and restaurants.
Although mobile phones have alot of disadvantages, such as social disintegration, awful effect on health, and trespassing others privacy by taking pictures of them or recording their voices without taking their permission. We need to consider that the phones are essential and connot be disposed of or banned for several reasons.
To begin with, phones are important to report any accident that may occur at public areas, like a car crash, a fire, a crime, and a severe health condition.
In those situation, it is critical to contact the police or special forces to deal with the circumstances at once.
Secondly, there are alot of people that need to take calls at all times, like doctors, Salesmen, policemen, parent (in case their children need them), and in general everybody.
Prohibiting people from recieving urgent can result either in people not going to shops and resterants, or causing protests to dwell in order to stop this ban.
In addition, alot of students use phones to listen to their recorded lectures or read a novel on their way to their destination on public transport.
Preventing them from seizing their time and using it wisely will affect them badly.
In the end, I believe that allowing mobile phones is the write desicion for the comfort and safety of people.
Sincerely, Batool
