As you can see, nowadays, more and more medical doctors want to work in cities, where they will make a lot of money, instead of rural areas.
This lead to a phenomenon of lack of doctors in those places.
So, what are the reasons for this problem?
How can it be solved?
This essay will examine the main reasons and suggest some resolutions to solve it.
One of the main culprits resulting in this common trend is the fact that the salary and benefit packages in urban hospitals are more attractive than rural areas.
People might have the tendency to choose a generously-paid job after working several years, medical doctors are not exception.
They would prefer to contribute for city hospitals, where the amount of patiens is enormous, which means they could get a higher salary.
Another factor adding to this issue would be related to the disparity in living standard between cities and rural areas.
Being a doctor is a heavy profession, hence those working in this field desire for a deluxe lifestyle.
They think they deserve to have it.
So, how to solve this problem?
There are some resolutions for this issue.
One of them is that government should enhance the fringe benefits for doctors who working in rural hospitals.
In detail, bonuses could be rewarded for fresh graduated medical students if they chose to devote themselves to those institues.
In addition, workforce distribution should be taken into consideration.
This means not all the doctors graduating from medical schools can work in their favorable places.
It depends on their academic.
In a nutshell, there are 2 reasons has lead to the lack of medical doctors in the countryside: One, the disparity in living standard, salary, benefits between cities and rural areas.
Two, the desire of having a deluxe lifestyle of them.
If the government and individuals share collective responsiblities, it's possible to solve this problem.
