And this is powerful I highly recommend this.
It's true that working area plays an important role to the workers, especially the ones working in an office.
Open office and closed office, which is better?
It's hard to answer.
So, let's take a look at them.
Firstly, open office.
An open office is an open work environment where there are no enclosed office room or walled cubicles for employees.
Usually, employees work in the same room, beside each other, while sitting along a huge desk or workstations positioned close together.
Many workers prefer to this design because they can easily communicate with their own teamates or even different teams.
It's more likely to establish relationships among each other.
But, this design has some disadvantages.
First, noise.
You can't definitely avoid noise when working in an open area.
If you and your teammates are working on a task that requires quiet to concentration, this design will make it a lot harder.
Secondly, conflicts.
When a group of people with different personalbilities and belief are crammed into a prison-like room to work for 8 hours a day, there is a high posibility of misunderstandings and conflicts.
Finally, spreading illness.
When someone is being sick with communicable disease, they can easily transfer and spread the virus to the rest of department.
That's about an open office.
How about a closed one, a traditional design one?
With this design, workers have more safety, privacy and stability.
Moreover, many workers tend to more concentrate on their work while sitting in an area surrounded by something.
But, just like the open design, this one also has some disadvantages.
Firstly, cost.
A closed office is more expensive to build and maintain than an open one.
Since each employee has his own workplace or cucible, you will need more area to fit every member of your team.
Secondly, low supervision.
Each employee has his own workplace, so it's hard to supervise what he is doing.
Is he working or playing games?
In a nutshell, each design has its own advantages and disadvantages.
It's hard to say which one is better.
