These days, some high schools consider volunteer work as a requirement for their students in order to graduate.
Is that necessary or not?
To my way of thinking, I think it's crucial.
There are several reasons why I say that.
Firstly, it is proved that volunteer work give pupils essential skills and pratical experiences for their future lives.
Through volunteer work, pupils can get social knowledge and skills such as public speaking, fast reflective skills, interpersonal skills, etc.
Life has different stages.
Pupils should not only just focus the school life but also the social life.
They should know how the world is going on outside school.
Having expertise but lack social knowledge, that's really bad for their future.
Secondly, it also shows that pupils have the ability to contribute to their countries.
Almost volunteer work is related to resovle unemployment, gender inequalities, crimes,...
In addition, participating in those activities shows that pupils have concerned and had capabilities of giving solutions and improvements to bad social problems.
Finally, social relationships.
Participating in those activities helps pupils improve their social relationships, extend them.
They can meet other people, make friends with them.
That really helps them with their future lives.
In a nutshell, volunteer work is crucial for pupils. "
Without community service, we would not have a strong quality of life.
It's important to the person who serves as well as the recipient.
It's the way in which we ourselves grow and develop," said Dr. Dorothy Height.
