Nowadays, many schools require students to learn and play a musical instrument.
Some people say it's not necessary, students don't need to learn it.
The others say the opposite.
To my way of thinking, I think music should be taught at schools.
Why?
Music is a subject to help students relax after heavy studying hours.
As you can see, students must learn many subjects at the same time.
Math, Literature, Physical,...
everything.
The classes go on continously.
One class is finished, the next one is going to start in a few minutes or even immediately.
It means that except the break time, students don't have many time to relax after finishing a class.
Music will help them with that problem.
In addition, the curriculum of this subject is not heavy.
Students just need to know some basic knowledge such as some chords, notes, etc.
They don't have to learn like they're going to take an entrance exam to a conservatory.
Finally, music classes can make an opportunity to detect music talents at school.
This contributes partly to develop the art of nation.
For example, many historical stories in the world recorded the famous musicians who educated from normal schools before.
If there had not been musical classes at school, the world would not have had any famous musicians and singers.
In a nutshell, music should be taught at school.
It's not only help students relax but also make an opportunity to find music talents.
