Indeed, some video games can have a negative impact on children.
But, in general, video games are not necessarily bad for children.
There are a lot of educational games in the world, for example.
Children may learn lots of vocabulary through video games.
They could learn social skills in some cases.
Moreover, playing video games are safe in terms of children's body.
Playing outside can be dangerous especially for children.
Besides, I think that forbidding children playing video games can rather have a negative impact if the children want to play video games.
They could feel pressure for strict rules.
Of course, playing video games all the time is bad for their health.
There is a problem that children do not play outside nowadays.
They should sometimes play outside so they can do exercise.
In conclusion, we should not forbid our children playing video games.
The thing is, we should watch out for the video games what our children are playing.
If the game is not suitable for our children, then we must tell our children not to play it.
When it's not the case, we should let the children play freely.
