Sports should play an important part in everyone's lives, but unfortunately, they don't.
Physical activity keeps both the body and the mind healthy and positively impacts one's life.
The negative effects of an inactive lifestyle should not be ignored because they affect more than we are led to believe.
Besides the obvious effects, obesity and the health problems it causes, the lack of physical activity also affects the mind, leading to unhappiness and unproductivity.
First of all, doing sports activities at least three times per week is enough to make a change in one's life.
These activities would provide most benefits especially if they were between classes at school.
Taking a physical activity break between chemistry and maths, for example, gives you a break from mental activities that require you to focus and give you some time to clear your mind and prepare for the next class.
An active lifestyle leads to an active mind.
This has also been proven by scientists.
When doing sports, the body releases endorphins that trigger a positive feeling.
So, there are no disadvantages of increasing students' and school children's physical activity.
Second of all, it is vitally important to make everyone understand the dangers of an unhealthy lifestyle.
The way we live our lives is the root of all of our problems.
An inactive lifestyle will never allow anyone to become the best version of herself or himself and it might actually cause more serious problems, like depression or physical ilnesses.
Young people are most impressionable and that is why it is strongly recommended to teach students and school children about the importance of an active life as soon as possible.
All things considered, there is no doubt that sports activities are as important as mental activities and they should be mandatory in school.
I agree with the people who believe zoos are good places for people to learn about animals.
The knowledge of animals is very important to people.
People can respect animals more because of those knowledge.
Moreover, animals in the zoo are not in so bad conditions.
Usually, they are treated really carefully so that they do not feel stressed out.
On the other hand, animals in nature are in very brutal conditions.
Some animals cannot survive in such environment.
Thus, I think animals do not have to belong in nature and it is not necessarily wrong to keep them in zoos.
The important thing is to respect those animals and nature, but not let them be free without thinking.
We are the same as them in terms of living thing on the earth.
Let us not ban zoos and let us keep them comfortable.
And then, let people learn more about them.
I think that studying abroad is really great thing in the main.
The students who go studying abroad could learn various things from it.
For example, they could be independent because they have to live on their own.
Not to mention, they have to speak in another language, so they could improve their language skills.
Moreover, they could learn cultures of the country where they are studying in.
They could even make friends in those countries.
Those experiences would be precious without doubt.
However, I think that there are some problems.
The cost for studying abroad would be very expensive.
Some students could not afford to go and live abroad.
They would have to borrow some money because of that.
What is more, they would be able to suffer from loneliness.
They could not meet their family and friends back in their country.
I do not know if they could persevere it.
In conclusion, I guess that to study in another country for a time during high school or university is a great idea.
Despite of that there are some problems, the experience in another country outweighs the problembs.
The experience in another country would be lifelong treasure.
