Obviously, to be healthy is more important than to be rich, but in every countries and in every societies richness helps to be healthy.
This is a problem not only in countries like the US, without a welfare state, but in countries like UK or UE members: people with good job and good wage could eat healthier and having better cures.
This is not a matter of access to private and better structure, but if you pay well you have a faster and good service also in public health structures.
And this is not a matter of corruption: health has a cost, and the public could not afford it as better as it can ever.
Same problem is for healthy food: poor can buy cheap food, and cheap food is dangerous, unhealthy, fat, rich of preservatives and sugars.
By contrast, rich people can buy organic and safer and healthy food, because this food is often very expensive.
