Everyone has a favourite thing, since he was a child.
A colour, an animal, a book, a season.
In particular, the favourite season of the year is said to be the expression of our behaviour.
In this article I am going to explain you what my favourite season of the year is and why.
The season better represents me is winter.
I love winter because I like to listen to the blowing wind under the window, looking to the snowy land in the coldest days.
It made me feel relaxed.
It is very special for me: I have many happy memories of my childhood in that season.
When I was a child, I used to go out with my younger sister to play with snow, rolling up to the snowy ground for example.
Winter is very often associated to Christmas time, one of the best moments of the year.
In fact, I love opening Christmas gifts with my sister and my parents, in the Christmas morning.
I remember how exciting that moment was.
I was looking forward to discovering what present I had received.
Winter is this for me.
Memories.
I truly hope that each parent has a right to raise their children the way they find appropriate.
However, feelings and believes are not only difficult to articulate, but also very individualistic.
Therefore, looking at what data tells us is crucial.
Like any other other tool, video games can be put to good or bad use.
For example, if young children play a game designed for teenagers, it will harm his psyche.
That's because games can evoke strong emotions, and confroting them with a defenseless child is a bad idea.
It can lead to anxiety or aggression in the long term.
Another harmful way is to allow our childer to play unlimited amount of time.
If there are no restrictions in place, child will play for the whole day. And sometimes even the night.
In contrast, educational games are very useful and desired.
We play video games bacause they are fun, and if we can make learning fun, the success is inevitable.
To summarise my short asnwer, I'm for a reasonable and controlled use of video games. Not only for educational purposes, but also for pleasure.
