How we can actually decide who's believes are right, and who's are wrong?
I went to Paris, France ten years ago.
It was the most significant holiday to me.
Before that time, I have never been abroad.
I remember that I was very excited at the time.
I love French culture, especially the art and cuisine.
Also, I got on an airplane for the first time at that time.
By the way, I went there with my family and friends.
My friends were excited about the holiday as well.
In Paris, firstly, I went to a hotel that I was staying during the holiday.
The hotel was really beautiful, classy and magnificent.
I was really exhausted right after arriving there because of the jet lag.
On the next day, I went to Disneyland and really enjoyed myself in there.
There were a lot of attractions.
On another day, I went to the Louvre, the famous museum.
I saw many famous pictures and sculptures.
Besides, I ate a number of delicious meals.
I love French cuisine very much.
Definitely, I won't forget these precious experiences.
I would love to visit France again.
I certainly think exercise is important for our health.
It is a fact that is proven by scientific research.
However, are there things that are more important?
Yes, I guess that there are indeed more important things than exercise.
For example, it is food which we eat in everyday life.
There is a famous proverb, "You are what you eat."
I think it is true.
If you do not take sufficient nutrients, you are going to be sick.
I assume people tend to have unhealthy food these days, for instance, they eat a lot of junk food.
They should eat more healthy food.
Another important thing for our health is a sleep.
I believe that to sleep is underestimated by most people.
But actually, it could be the most important thing for our health.
We can get refleshed by enough sleep.
It is also beneficial to our brain as well.
If we feel stressed out, it will affects our health.
But sleeping can get it out of our mind.
We have to get more sleep absolutely.
Although I have written as above, exercise is also important for our health without doubt. We have to think about them all.
