Schools are set to educate the students.
Traditionally, there are teachers and students in school.
They must go to school almost every day until they graduate or move another school.
They must get up in the morning in most cases.
Some students have their lunch at the school.
Others have their lunch at elsewhere.
They ought not to go home until after-school.
Almost every person in the world experienced such stuff.
I always doubt whether or not the students should go to school physically.
I think schools' duty is to teach their students itself.
They do not have to attend schools in real as long as they study what their school teaches them.
There are online study courses everywhere nowadays.
I assume students in the world do not have to go to school unless they study at somewhere else.
They could study without schools and it is enough for them.
In those ways, they do not have to spend a waste of time, too.
I do not want you to get me wrong.
There are certainly some good points about that schools exist physically.
However, it is not necessary.
I think television could educate people in general.
In fact, there are a lot of educational TV programme in many countries.
Of course, we would be able to learn many things from books or something else.
However, television can give us stuff in action.
For example, we can watch various wild animals on TV. Their life, food, shape and so forth.
It is very important that something are moving in reality.
Sound is also important, because we can watch various things with the sounds.
It is not necessarily TV programmes that is educational.
For instance, there are a number of educational videos on the internet.
The thing is, television is a thing which lives in our everyday life. Because it is everywhere in our life.
We can watch something we did not know until we see it.
I think that it is really fun.
And sometimes we could discover something educational on TV.
This is why I would say that television cannot only entertain us, but can also educate us.
