What can be more important than exercise?
One needs an energy to be able to run, jump, or do yoga.
Therefore, there are at least two more valuable components to our health: food and sleep.
In 2017 the Noble prize in medicine has been granted to a team leaded by professor Rosbach.
The team researched on circadian rhythm.
Their discoveries resolved around sleep-wake cycle that is embeded into our cells.
The research denotes that our bodies function better when we adhere to these patterns.
Furthermore, it revealed that each and every organ of our body function according to a slightly different pattern.
Therefore, it's not only important that we go to bed at a certain time, but also that we eat at a certain time.
Generally speaking, people who sleep well tend to be more relaxed and less spiteful.
By the same token, an appropriate amount of bed-time precludes the need for inordinate daily coffee intake.
Than there is exercise; the third component of circadian rhythm.
To be heatlhy means to feel tired in the evening and refreshed in the morning.
Therefore, we should exercise at least 30 minutes a day to avert the effects of our sedentary life style.
