Last week, I went to a music concert held in the magnificent musical hall of Suzhou.
I have been expecting this concernt for a long time, and I even booked ticket three months in advance.
The primary reason I choose this particular concert is because Lang Lang, an internationally renowned pianist, would perform in the concert.
I got to know Lang Lang when I was just six.
You probably know that I have been playing piano for 10 years, and the key motive for my persistence is because of Lang Lang, my spiritual tutor.
The concert was very well organized.
Lang Lang played at least 10 pieces of masterpiece on the stage.
You cannnot imagin that all audiences stood up and applauded for Lang Lang after each piano piece.
Nobody went out for break during the concert.
Lang Lang was so polite that he went back to the stage for three times after the final piece, and he played two more pieces to return his thankfulness.
I had a wonderful night that day, and my interest in piano has been sparkled once more; therefore, I cannot help writing to you, and I wish to share my happiness and excitement with you.
Best wishes, Michael.
Hello, everyone. Today, I have the opportunity to write about my opinion the Television can educate.
Now, it is time for writing, let's begin: Television is a device extremely useful or harmful, it is depend on the person who is using it, because if the person is disciplined, is interested in knowledge, watching educational programs, take advantage of cultural programs. These actions permit people to be educated.
Otherwise, if the person is not disciplined, is not interested in knowledge, watching movies, series, novels, comedies and other entertain programs, it means, no take advantage of your time, this person not be educated.
I think, television is useful so much or is harmful so much as the same Internet.
Smart people learn languages, do courses, download programs, exchange knowledge with other people, other cultures, other countries. While fool people misspend their time only see jokes, memes, spam information, they do not want to learn anything, their interest is nothing, upset the world.
It is overnumber lazy people that not take advantage of the useful things.
It is the difference with people that effort themselves and being success.
As I see it, it's more important these days rather than in the past, owing that today we have a more globalized world where you can fly and do tourism or live anywhere and besides we're communicated throughout the world by internet, therefore each day we can speak with people from another countries and learn from them.
Right now the most international language is English, hence I believe in the present moment it is very important to learn it.
Nevertheless, it is true that in the past it was harder to acquire a new idiom due to the lack of opotions they had to study.
For instance they didn't have all the apps, courses, idiom schools and so on, that we currently have.
To summarize, from my point of view today it's more important for the reason that we are living in a more gloablized world where we can speak with people from other countries each day, although learning a new language has been always very useful and interesting and I recommend everyone to do it.
It is true that we're all taught to always tell the truth.
But, in fact, sometimes we do not follow that lesson.
We do the opposite but the interesting thing is it's somehow accepted.
So, did our teachers teach us wrongly?
No, they didn't.
Being honest is important.
That's not erroneous at all.
But, in some circumstances, lie is more preferred.
First of all, telling lie can sometimes motivate the people we care to excel.
Humans are very competitive and always want to be the best at every task they have been assigned.
Whether they are taking part in an athletic event or taking an examination, they feel more motivated if they think it is possible to archive the best result.
You may know the fact that it's an unthinkable thing for some them.
Nevertheless, instead of telling the truth and completely destroying their hope, being a liar in that cases is better.
Secondly, being honest at all time may lead you to high level of anxiety.
Not all truths are good to be revealed.
Some of them can make people unpleasant.
For example, last week, my friend asked me what I thought about her new hairstyle.
Well, I said frankly it looked terrible.
Although she didn't express any anger mark, I knew she was very upset inside.
She hasn't talked to me since that day.
Therefore, be careful what you are going to say.
In a nutshell, telling the truth is crucial.
Well, no doubt about it.
But, sometimes, you should do the opposite.
If not, you may regard about what you said.
Since the dawn of times, man travel from place to place at the expense of the most precious and irretrievable currency; time.
We can now travel at speeds that were beyond the imagination of commuters just a hundred years ago.
I don't want to sound disparaging to the inventions like Hyperloop, but it seems like we are touching the limits.
Therefore, the future of travel won't be much about the time, but about the comfort and safety.
Even now, when I'm writing this article, some long distance planes are equipped with the latest comforts and luxuries.
You can travel accross the Atlantic in your very own cabin which is like a one night stand in a five star hotel.
When you arrive, you will be rested. Almost like the struggle of trip never happened.
I believe that sooner or later we will be flying a mini version of town, where you not only can have meal, but also visit a hairdresser or a doctor.
