Zoos represent a new entertainment for all people, from children to adults.
The number of them is increasing more and more every day.
This is the reason why no-profit organizations like Green Peace do not agree with that phenomenon.
In fact, they believe animals must belong in nature and zoos seem to be prisons rather than peaceful and funny places.
In my opinion, there is no point in taking wild animals chained into zoos: they must be got free, as we are.
There are many ways and alternative solutions to see them.
For example, safari and other tours do not require any restrictions for animals.
You can go with a guide and visit these stunning natural parks, admiring the beauty of local wildlfe.
I know that the staff of every zoo treat animals well.
Moreover, every uncorrect behaviour and bad treatment is not allowed.
Laws are clear and it is a worth.
Even though animals are prisoned in zoos, they are safe and well treated.
Anyway, from my point of view I would prefer to see all animals free in their habitat and,in general, in the wild nature, in their right place!
