In conclusion, from my point of view I believe that we should practise exercise because it has too many benefits for us, however we also have to be aware that there are more important things we should do in order to have a well balanced life.
For instance one important thing which I suggest is practising meditation, for the reason that it is a great way to relax our body and mind.
Schools have been involving in many evolutions for the last decades.
Still now they are changing because of the pandemic emergency.
New tools and a new approach are tested in order to cope with this hard period.
Are there effective? Are not they?
What might schools be in the next future, when the emergency will go to the end?
These are hard questions to be answered, but we will try to do it in this article.
CoVid emergency has led everybody to stay indoors, changing drastically our routine.
Students get used to attempting online lectures, from the primary school to the university.
The goal is to keep teaching as best as possible.
However, many problems occur in this way.
For example, children and teenagers do not receive the same feedback as well as in live lessons: as a result, they cannot learn well new topics and their preparation level gets lower and lower.
On the other hand, most university students are experiencing these kind of activities with good results.
