Nowadays, people can read books on their computers or tablets, or even their smartphones.
Then, students in general could use those devices to study in schools or universities.
Should they replace books in those situations?
In my opinion, computers and tablets should completely replace books in schools and universities.
They are simply convenient.
Books take significant space.
Books are also damaged as time elapses.
On the other hand, computers and tablets do not take so much space.
Also, they can contain considerably many books.
More importantly, the students do not need to carry such heavy textbooks.
There would be less troubles if they do not have to bring their textbooks all the time.
Of course, computers and tablets inevitably need electricity while books are don't.
However, the advantages of computers and tablets outweigh its disadvantages.
On balance, basically, schools and universities should use computers and tablets to get the students study.
If there are problems with them, then they should use books in those cases.
It is inevitable that new technology replaces traditional stuff.
