In first place I have to say that universities are spreaded across the entire world, there is not a single country without it.
There are different ways to face the university.
On one hand we have students who live at home with their family, on the other hand we have students who decide to move to another town on their own.
If I had to choose where I would prefer to stay, I surely prefer to stay with my family.
Especially because they pay for my needs and I can focus on studying and exceeding the various exams, but most important I can count on the support of my family when something goes wrong.
For example when you fail to face an exam, and you have to reface it again.
It is the worst feeling you can feel.
Besides, moving to another country can help a lot student in growing up.
Because it allows you to pay for you needs, you have to work, to pay and you also have to study for your exams.
You can make new friends in your new country, maybe friends that are doing your same school.
By and large, scholar use to live with their family while studying, because is more simple than going alone in a new place and quitting your comfort zone.
In conclusion, as I said before I prefer to experience university by staying in my comfort zone and focus more on the studying.
