It's a common belief that video games can have a negative impact on children.
However, I am against that idea for the following reasons.
We all are in the modern world which is full with smart equipments, so the entertainment tools of course are different from the things we used to have.
Most of them have to do with technology ,and video games is a example of the popular entertainment way with children these days.
Video games is available and covenient in our modern devices like TV, smartphone,...
So, children don't have to think much of what they can play in their freetime.
Besides, children can be relaxed at their home instead of going to the cinemas, parks, game centres.
Moreover, video games are interesting and various.
Many game manufacturers have to compete for more profits, which makes them create better video games than their rivals.
Then, there are many wonderful games for your children from educational one to entertaining one.
Educantional games can provide your children with many necessary skills to survive such as making deceison, matching clothes, designing homes...
Another reason is that your children can make friends through video games.
Online video games allow people to play with others from different countries, so children can buil more friend relationships, learn other languages and cultures as well.
It is very useful in the multicultural world.
In conclusion, playing video games have many benefits that should be encouraged more.
Televison is a widely used medium.
Apart from it being entertaining, I also believe that it can be educative.
Televison can be used for multiple purposes.
These are for example entertainment, advertsing but also education.
The purpose differs per programm.
The televison shows on the commercial channels are often more entertaining, whereas the ones on the public service broadcasting are often educational.
Examples of educational programms are documentaries about a variety of subjects, such as a new earth.
There are also many educational programms for kids, like 't klokhuis.
Apart from that there are also programs which are both entertaining and educational such as 'the secret of the master' which is a painting show where the viewers also learn about art history.
In conclusion, televison can also be educative.
It depends on the kind of televison show and the purpose of the makers.
