Sometimes people want to find something brand new and almost their priority is going abroad.
I realized that there is the same thing happening to students: some of them choose to study in another country for a time during high school or university.
Of course, it always has both advantages and drawbacks.
I want to start with advantages first.
Studying abroad is a opportunity for students to access to different study environment.
There, they can work with foreigners as much as possible.
That leads them to learn other languages quickly and effectively.
Moreover, the amount of knowledge they gained is significant.
Students will be familiar with modern study equipments, scientific teaching methods and working styles of foreigners.
Therefore, it is easy for them when they had a chance to work in an international company or embassy.
So, they will make a contribute to develope their mother country.
Besides, when students study abroad, they will gain more experience.
Because they have to live far away their family, they had no chance but taking care of themselves.
They will know how to prepare a meal and manage their money.
Another advantage is that students can make more friends and enjoy the feeling of a traveller while they are studying.
On the other hand, there are some drawbacks of studying abroad.
The noticeable thing I want to say is the homesick feeling.
Students will miss their family and their classmate much and feel alone sometimes.
Besides, in the beginning, they maybe get some culture shocks and can't be adapted other customs.
