Well, I believe that sometimes is acceptable to tell a lie.
First, It is very difficult, maybe impossible, tell the truth all the time.
It will be hard, and so disagreable tell the truth all the time.
Imagine if you tell the truth for your wife all the time.
You stopped to talk with a friend in the street, nothing wrong, but your wife needed you quicly, so you said that the traffic was bad, beacuse of this you were late, end of the history, no fight, no problem.
There are many examples to show how it is reasoble to lie sometimes, for instance, If a person ask you about her clothes, or about the new hair colour, or about the results of the plastic cirurgy, and you consider ugly, or a disaster.
What should you say?
The truth?
Worth? Of course that not.
It's better to lie, perhaps not all lie, it is not necessary to say, it is beautiful, but you can it is not bad (the truth is bad), but which the value to make the person sad?
It is better a little lie.
Sometimes it is important a little lie too about the perspectives about the life too, for example about the someone's health, about the economic situation, about the reality.
It is not necessary to be crude.
In my opinion both points have their advantages and disadvantages.
I will start with living at the university with other students.
The first advantage that comes to my mind it's that the experience can be amusing and you will remember it for the rest of your life.
Another advantage which I think it's quite interesting is the fact that you'll be forced to leave your comfort zone.
Therefore you'll have to buy your own groceries, prepare your meals, do the washing and so on.
However, there are some disadvantages either.
For instance, your mates can lead you to an unhealty life and you can lose your focus and as a result get bad marks in your exams.
Besides, if you live out you probably will expend more money.
Let's talk now about living with your family while you're studying.
Firstly if you are living with your parents you'll be able to save more money.
Secondly, you have more chances to be more focused in your exams for the reason that you won't have bad influences.
In conclusion both options are pretty good, but if I had to choose between one of the two I would choose to live at the university with other students for the due to the fact that it's a more enjoyable experience.
Yesterday, my children agrued about the purpose of television.
One said that it could entertain in many ways and played a vital role in modern era.
However, the other insisted that it also educated peoplep in many areas.
And I finished their agruement by combining the both options.
First of all, television can entertain people.
With the large number of films, game shows and news, people can be relax after the hard day.
Almost TV programs were recreational and amused which made you laugh imediately .
By that way, television is an ideal mean for you to kill the time.
Moreover, TV manufacturers created some kind of smart televisions that you even play video games and sing karaoke with others.
They also allow you to connect the Internet and access to social media.
Therefore, television is an ideal means for entertainning.
Besides, television can educate people in different areas.
Many educational programs for kids was published like 'Wildlife', 'Spell with Mrs.Jenny."
Moreover, there are some game shows that provide viewers with life skills.
I learned a lot of ways to cook in a 'ABC's kitchen'.
In conclusion, television not only entertains but also educates.
It is often said that it is important to always tell the truth, but it is ever acceptable to tell a lie?
Firstly, I want to state that I agree with this phrase.
As I see it, if you want to be someone who can be trusted by other people and have their confidence you have to be honest with them and no matter what tell the truth.
Besides, if you are someone who normally tell lies, then you have a big chance to forget the lies you had told and therefore people will notice it and as a consequence you will lose your credibility.
Although, in some cases you can be allowed to tell a lie in order to relieve others' pain.
For instance, imagine that your dog is sick and sadly he dies, so now you have to explain it to your children.
Don't you think that instead of explaining them that your dog has died you could tell them that your dog has found his mother and he has gone to live with her?
In conclusion, I'm one of those who tries to be honest and always tell the truth, owing to the fact that at the end you know what is real and what not and for this reason I believe that there is no point in telling lies to other people.
