Telling the truth is not always easy.
However, there are situations in which lying may be the more efficient decision.
Many people argue that lying is one of the worst things one can do and always telling the truth is very important.
Wether I believe so aswell will be discussed in the following.
First of all, it has to mentioned that the legitimacy of a lie depends on the situation.
If the lyer and moreover the person that is being lied to was not offended in any kind I conscider a lie as legit.
However, those situations occure rarely and one have to carefully analyse the importance of the situation.
For instance, when only once arriving delayed at school the importance of that situation would not be crucial and no involved would be violated physically or mentally.
Nevertheless, the danger of analysing a certain situation unsuitable is still existing.
Furthermore, I do not recommend lying in decisive cases of life.
In crucial cases of life a lie can destroy relations and worsen situations rather than heal them.
Moreover, the lying person itself may not endure the burdens of distortion and may suffer even more than the person which is being lied to.
For example, when hiding a fraud to one's partner the matter would be turn out better when telling the truth than veiling it for a certain margin of time.
When confessing a lie the opposite person may recognise the guilt and forgive.
On the contrary, hiding the truth could cause and horrible effects on a person.
Dear I would like to write you about the new rule that is banning the use of mobile phones on public transport and in shops and restaurants.
I am sure that the rule is absolutely outrageous.
You should not accept that suggestion.
As you know, mobile phones are indispensable in our everyday life.
We could not even spend just one day without it in this modernised world.
I know that it is annoying people when someone speaks on their phone in a public space.
However, that is because they need to do it at the time.
Besides, people sometimes need to use the phone in case that they were in an emergency situation.
In those cases, their life and death would depend on their phone.
I must say that you could not decide whether or not a person have to die.
As I have written above, it is a bad idea that banning the use of mobile phone on public transport and in shops and so forth.
Instead, you should just call on people to refrain from the use of mobile phones in some public spaces.
Definitely, you should not ban it as that is too much.
I hope that the other people who think about the ban would understand my opinion.
I am strongly wishing it.
Best regards, A citizen
I would like to say that it is basically a right thing to always tell the truth.
It is very important, too.
People must tell the truth all the time.
However, I think that there could be a moment that is acceptable to tell a lie.
For example, the time to tell a joke to friends.
It would be funny, and people like funny things.
It makes a relationship better.
Likewise, there is a time, which should not tell the truth.
We have to think about the result before we speak something.
If we could be offensive or rude when we tell the truth, then we should refrain from telling the truth.
Thus, we are able to be socially acceptable.
By the way, how about that telling a lie without any reasons?
I suppose that that could not be right in any situations.
To tell a lie is heinous.
I am sure that most people agree with me about it.
I would be terrified if all people lied all the time in a callous way.
I think that it is very important not to tell any lies.
What is more, it is also important to trust people around you every time you see them.
This is my opinion but I would like to say that people should hate someone who has no qualm about telling a lie.
