Dear Johnna, You have no idea where I've been last Monday.
To tell you the truth, I went to a music concert in Baoli Giant Theatre, actually!
March has witnessed a dramatic improvement in my career.
The greatest of all was that I got promoted in my firm this term1 Given that the former HR manager was resigned for good, I sought the opportunity just in time.
You understand that people're likely to ease themselves when they've just gone through a tough period,don't you?
That accounted for why I was heading in the music concert.
Frankly speaking, my knowledge of music is rather limited.
To be honest, it was not until I got to the spot that I eventually learned whose concert it was, since the tickets were booked by my boyfriend in advance.
Have you ever heard about Alica Frankle's name?
Representing one of the most distinguished divas in Britain, she is performing in the globe this year.
Overall I regarded this concert as an more-than-fascinating one!
Alica Frankle was not only a professional but also a gifted in engaging people during the two-hour concert.
I was at the edge of bursting into tears when she sang the bridge of Shassas.
It's was so amazing!
Never should you forget about it once you hear she singing live.
The concert is going to be a lifelong memory for me, definately.
Yours, Iris
Nowadays it is well known that much people are emigrating from small towns in rural areas to big cities.
Therefore, we need more hospitals and doctors in the big cities for the reason that they have many patients to attend.
However, the citizens who live in the rural areas are old people and they need more health care.
Owing to that fact, I believe that we should invest in those areas and as a result some citizens who have emigrated to big cities will have a chance to come back to their town.
As a result the population in rural areas will increase and this will lead to the creation of new hospitals.
In conclusion, there aren't enough doctors in the rural areas due to the lack of population in those zones.
For this reason I suggest that one of the best solutions could be to invest in those areas, so we can create new jobs and this will bring more citizens in those areas and eventually they will need more doctors.
