When people have the same teacher for several years they benefit from the fact that the teacher knows the student inside out and is able to see the study progress the student is making.
In other words the teacher is able to monitor student's growth for a longer period.
Also the teacher may relate to the students on a more personal level, enabling the teacher to more indepth understand the student.
Aspects from the student's private live can be more easily understood by the teacher, whereto he or she can more empathize with the consequences and help the student to overcome difficulties during his study.
On the other hand, a fresh pair of eyes will help the student to grow further.
So new teachers could highlight more easily aspects where the student needs to focus on improvements.
Each teacher brings along his or her special educationals qualifications.
All those aspects together will facilitate progress.
To my opinion, all students should be able to study music since this requires many skills and compentences which will help them in their lives.
First of studying music is a great example of improving the creativity skills of students.
Students will have to be creative while playing music.
Creativity is one of those competences that will bring them further in life while pursuing a career.
This competency will help them to succesfully anticipate to different situations under various circumstances.
One other positive aspect of studying music is that it provides a way to express themselves in other ways than with words.
As long as lecturers provide a safe environment in the classroom, students will be able to use music to show other students how they feel.
Music can be used as means to vent emotions.
Furthermore playing music binds people together.
Whether it is during a yam session or whether it is when studying a musical play.
It is very fullfilling to jointly accomplish a enormous task such as a difficult music piece.
This teamworking skill will have a added value in the future.
Therefore I believe that all students should have access to musical studies.
