Exicited that a movie festival is to be held in your campus, I literally have a fascinating one to suggest-----The Social Network.
As is widely known, the movie was adapted from the storyline of Mark Zuckerburg and the process of how he and his friends created Facebook.
Just like other adaptive films, TSN did a good job in keeping the balance between drama and reality.
That is to say, you can see the traditional American style of films, which is filled with sex, conflicts as well as strict plot.
At the same time, there also stood the reflections of what had happened to the characters in the reality.
What I found most thrilling when watching the movie was the engrossing acting by two male actors, Jesse and Andrew.
As for Jesse, who acted as Mark in TSN, he never failed to attract every audience with his high-speed lines as well as delicate facial expressions.
I almost cried out"That's Zuckerburg alive" when he typed in a incredibly fast rhythem on the keyboard.
Needless to say, Andrew was the one who dedicated his heart and soul to his character Edurado.
Playing as Mark's best friend, Edurado had gone through a series of tough times when they started their career.
Notwithstanding, Andrew's Edurado was a "sweetheart" from head to toe, as he's always there for his mate.
Released almost ten years ago, TSN was a phenonmenal blockbuster as well as a box-office hiter.
It's the kind of film that you surely don't want to miss.
That why I highly recommend it to you.
I sincerely hope you can enjoy it.
Yours, Iris
