I think that it is a better to live on their own when they are attending school.
Generally, most of students live at home with their family and depend on them about living things.
It is not bad for students, however living by themselves will give them advantages in the future.
I have two points about my idea.
First of all, living by ourselves develop our living skill.
There are many things to live like washing, cooking, cleaning and so on.
Then, at home, we probably rely on our families, especially our mothers.
But, if we live by ourselves, noone does them without us.
And, most of students will go out their home and live alon when they begin working in society.
So, living by theirselves while they are students will be preparation of their future lives.
Secondly, students can make a time to do something efficiently better than living at home with their families.
For example, at home, when we want to go to the bathtoom, if other family member already has been doing, we have to wait for finishing it.
This may be a little thing in a daily life, but it also breaks our plan in the day.
If we live alone, we can decide when we go to the bathroom and it makes easier to make a plan in a day.
While we are students, there many things to do such as studying, working on part time job and so on.
So, in order to use time flexibly, living alone is very effective for students.
All in all, I described two points about preparation for the future and using time effectivelly.
Living by ourselves while we are students is so difficult and hard.
But, it will give us good effect definitely.
My experience with Write and Improve.
I started using it 1 month ago more or less and I have to say that I believe that is a quite useful tool to improve my writing skills.
One of my favourite things of this page is that it has many different types of writing to choose, for instance you can write an informal letter and then a formal essay.
Besides I find quite helpful the huge variety of levels that the website provides.
You can find levels for beginners, intermediates and advanceds.
However, I'm not so happy with the automatic corrector, for the reason that sometimes it can misunderstand some of your words.
In conclusion, as I see it Write and Improve it's a wonderful tool if you want to train your written skills and therefore I would recommend it to everyone who want to acquire a better English.
