Some people argued that students should not have to study music in school.
However, I'm against that idea for some reasons.
First of all, it is undeniable that music is an effective entertaining way.
As far as I'm concerned, nowadays students have to learn a huge amount of knowledge with loads of academic subjects.
That leads to their high study pressure and overwhelming by trillion of theories in many areas.
Therefore, if there are music classes in their schedule, it will reduce students's stress and make their brain less tense.
Music is proved to have some health benefits including enhancing the memory and ability to concentrate.
Moreover, the soft melody created by music instuments can help them to calm down, soothe their mind.
It tends to decrease the risk of conflicts between irritated students.
Music also develops students's artistic talents.
By learning to play music instruments, their sense of art is more subtle and delicate.
In coincidence, it improves the right brain of learners.
As a result, students can become more creative and be interest in art area.
For students that have talent in music at the beginning, they maybe gain some useful experience and soon be expert in their pursuing of music career.
For the rest, it's likely some of them will find out their passion for music.
Then, they direct their action to become musicians, instrumentalist or even singers.
From the above benefits of music, I think that this subject should be taught at school.
It can make the significant change in students's life.
