Health is more important than wealth It is known proverb "health is wealth."
And we know human progress have been changing since years and it will continue to develop futher.
But sayings and proverb do not cahnge, and we have similar provers in most of the languages.
So, health is real wealth.
In other words, we can enjoy our money and property when we are healthy.
A sick person can not be happy by his wealth, he needs a healthy body to be happy.
We have wealthy and poor countries around the world.
Wehn we see "happy index" it does say that only wealthy countries are happier.
Infact, a poor country like Bhutan has number one place that its people are happier than all counytries and its people.
Bhutan has even no a proper democratic goverment but a kind of kindom run the countyry.
Similarly, we can notice at rural and urban area of a country in general. And we find that people in the villages are healthy than those who are living in cities.
And we know cities provide much more facility and emplotment.
Above the information says that healthy more important than a wealthy.
Nowadays, people argued about the importance of a good health compared to that of being rich.
In my view, I suppose that it is more important to be healthy than to be rich.
Firstly, a good health is considered as the most valuable treasure of each person.
When you are healthy, you have loads of energy to do anything you want.
You can climb up the steep mountains, run fast in the windy hills and do some extreme sports without being limited.
Moreover, with a good health, you will work productively.
A strong farmer can do as twice as a weak one.
Similarly, a white-collar worker who exercise everyday is able to work overtime and usually active in their work.
Sadly, some people is too self-confident about their strengh and make full of it to earn for living.
They maybe become a millionaire ,but in the long run, they will pay the heavy toll by their health.
The money you earned will be used for pay the hospital bill instead of travelling all around the world and spending time with family members.
In conclusion, I put the health first and invest in my health for further benefits in the future.
