Last Summer, I had the distinct pleasure of spending time in Italy and looking back, I recogn it turned out to be the best holiday ever.
Since Italy is a 1600 km drive, we always spend the night near Lugano Lack, luckily for us there was still a room available at one of our favorite hotels where we enjoyed the top quality service of this very charming, yet very traditional hotel, commonly known for its famous visitors like Audrey Hepburn.
The second day, we arrived at the camping in Tuscany, the sun was shining and the temperature already rose to a very comfortable 30 degrees.
Unpacking was done very quickly so that we could settle in the sun and start planning our sightseeing tours in the surroundings.
One of the highlights was the visit to the waterfall in the beautiful rural neighbourhood of Florence.
We walked alongside the waterfall and were very much impressed about the amazing nature, all kinds of plants were flourshing and the colours of the flowers were brilliant for taking photos.
The other unforgettable moment was the visit to Cita del la Pieva, an old acient village with small corridors, stunnishing views from the top of the vilage, small squares with beautiful little shops, tiny little restaurants were we enjoyed local food and of course the best espresso ever.
A very special food in Romania is fried bacon.
But it's a diferent kind of fried bacon.
We cut it in square or rectangular shape, we put it on a stick/forck and we fried it on top of the fire.
We make a small fire outdoor.
We put it on a slice of bread so the grease can cover the bread.
we serve it with green onion and tomato.
We usualy make these kind of bacon on camping or when we go at our country house.
