Dear Makenzie, How are you?
I went to a music concert last week, and it was so great, so I couldn't wait to share mu experience with you.
You know me well, so you know that I love music because music can make me feel relaxed.
I had a really hard time last week due to many exams to take.
As a consequence, I decided to go to a music cencert for relax.
A pianist from Germany was performing.
I couldn't spell his name because it was too long and complicated.
Nevertheless, I could recognize him among people, because he looked very handsome and tall, and he was very elegant.
Perhaps it was because the classic music that made him so gorgeous.
I really enjoyed music during the concert, but there was something annoying.
Many people was late for the concert, so there were many figures moving to find seats while I was listening to the first piece of music.
What's more, there were some kids in de theater.
Maybe Thae was because their parents want them to get to know more about classic music.
Nevertheless, kids could hardly know about classic music, and they couldn't understand the meanings of the music.
It was really tough for them to sit on the chair for over two hours without screaming and crying.
These made the experience not so comfortble.
I don't really think we should allow children below 10 years old to enter the concert, because they may ruin a precious journey with music.
I also think we shouldn't allow people who are late to enter the concert.
They have to take their responsibilities for not being punctual.
What do you think about my thoughts?
I hope everything is going well on you.
I think we may go to a concert together when I go the the USA.
I am looking forward to hearing from you.
Yours, Joany
