I firmly believe that living a seperate house in the university days changes thier life in a good way.
This idea is holded up by my past experiences.
In the adolecence period, to be emotionally stable, young college students build a firm network they want to belong to instead of relying on thier parents all the time.
This sense of belongings accelerates thier mental growth because they play a role in its community aside from a child.
They will be mentally independent and responsible not for thier lives but also thier communities.
This whole experiences makes him who he will be in the future.
Having said so, some people still stress that living at home is cost-efficient and confortable to focus on the academics.
I would oppose this idea in two reasons.
One is that it is true to save your money if you can go to university from your parents house but is the cost-effectiveness true reason why you wanted to attend the university?
Apparently you may go though more hardships than you imagined yet these challenges you encounter would be a medicine to intensify your growth.
The younger you are, the better it is to take through a variety of experiences.
Second reason is that if you cannot manage your time by yourself without seeking any family support, you will suffer a new life after working in a companey.
To grow yourself, you should stand your own two feet even from the college days.
