The Future of Travel changed with the arrival of the COVID19 virus and the challenging facing us with regard to the climate.
More than ever, people were faced with the most challenging and only question regarding travelling ever; is it a luxury just for the rich people or a common thing which ordinary people can enjoy as well.
COVID19 prohibited people from travelling beyond the borders, all belts and braces in place were directed to having people stay at home.
Crossing borders was not allowed during the outbreak of the virus, moreover it had been forbidden by national governments to prevent the virus from spreading unnecessarily any further than it already did.
Travelling was only possible within the frontiers of the country.
So maybe, the future of travel is travelling is not getting onto a plain for a far-away vacation, experiencing other cultures and nature, but staying close to home, exploring the neighbourhood and revisiting all the little gems in the local area surrounding us.
Future will tell if people will ever be able to travell long distance again or that it will be forbidden for ever.
Utlimately, less travelling will have a beneficial effect to the climate, because travelling in itself will burden the climate.
So maybe the limitations set by the virus will in the end have a positive effect on people as well as the climate.
Nowadays it takes a lot of effort and money to succesfully run a medical practice, especially in this competitive times.
Since the insurance companies play an important role in setting rules for medical practices, it because more and more difficult for a medical doctor to run his business at a profit.
The strictly set rules prohibit medical doctors of being creative while treating their patients to their utmost of their capabilities.
Each treatment has his own set of limitations as what a medical doctor can offer and can declare afterwards.
And in the end, it is all about business.
Rural areas represent a low number of habitants, whereas medical practices need a much patients are possible, enforcing medical doctors to set up their practice in large cities in stead of small villages.
Moreover, a small village, however charmingly pittoresk and attracting, does not offer enough patients and are in such a way extremely challenging to entrepreneurs who in general want to develop a succesful business.
Once in a while, you will still find a lonesome medical doctor, stuck away in a little village, using old-fashioned ways to accommodate his patients, thus taking all the time needed to comfort the patient, but these become more and more a rarity to today's society and are becoming distinct.
Young medical doctors are starting in the profession prefer wokr in the big cities to make a lot of money, as long as starting and they want won money, when these doctors grow up in the profession and stay stabilized, they came of rural areas.
It is more easy find job in the Big cities and in the rural areas, that is the reason why, the young doctors prefer cities.
Old doctors prefer work in the rural areas, because they are stabilized, they have a good career.
Young doctors need make networking with other doctors, and the big cities it is the best place to do, in rural areas they have more difficult to do networking with doctors.
It is a bIg problem have some doctors in rural areas, 'cause the hospital need so much doctors in all the places, and do not concentrate in the big cities, we need doctors, sometimes have a emergency and need doctors.
