In recent years, there has been a heated debate on whether the college students should be forced to physical activities dut to the fact that because of the heavy effects of modernization and industrailization, it is plausibly hard for students in universities to keep a reasonable balance between stressful schoolwork and physcial and psychological health.
While hold a firm belief that it is doubtless for schoolers, which may probably too busy to distribute some of their time and engergy in order to satisfy their basic requirements, I, to a large extent, maintian that only by taking regular exercise, be it jogging or swimming, can us students have a primary opportunity to pursue more rounded personalities as well as enhanced academic performances.
In this essay, I would like quote a few examples to support my opinion.
To begin with, generally speaking, exercising can absolutely release ourselves from feeling stressed and suffocated, which is remarkably catering for our physical needs and psychological pursuits.
What I mean by this is that under such many fierce competitions in schools and institutions, it is rather important to keep fit to ensure the success to our academic grades,which any benefit us undoubtfully and offer us valueable chances enlarge our merits and edges over other canditions for further would-be competitions.
Therefore, it is of great necessity to guarantee our exercise on a daily basis, as a consequence, start from now!
In addition, in many cases, as is known to all, making end meets has been increasingly difficult for adults, especially when during the extended period of time the whole world are suffering financial recession due to the COVID-19, it seems more essentials to every individuals, scholars in particular, to have a health condition ont only physically but also metally to prevent from being bombared by bills of different operational costs and daily consumption accordingly.
Simply put , as an old saying goes, healthy body ensure the success of the revolution, which exactly proves my mentioned piont.
To sum up, while school are allowed to enact and enforce a number of specific regulations about exercing, which might seem to be too cruel somehow, I am still convinced that it is our capability and responsiblilty to follow them, as they could make us effective and efficient somehow.
Ideally, change your against mind and start to move, instead.
