It is quite known television entertains, but there is some doubts about whether television educates or not.
In one hand we use the television to have fun, relaxing and entertains in different ways and we spend a lot time in front of it.
In the other hand, educations experts has been trying to solve this question for so long - Does the television educate?
I'm not totaly sure about it, but I know I have been watching television to learn things for a long time.
There is lots of educational channels available for a wide range of ages, from 1 to 99 years.
The major problem is all most of the time people don't use the television as they should do.
Mostly children and teenagers, they need to be supervised while they watch televesion as part of a educational program.
Even adults need to deal with the desire to watch entertains shows on television instead a educational show.
In short, I think people can use the television to educational purpose.
Nowadays, a lot of students are geting unhealth because their inactive lifestyle.
That makes some people say all students at school or university should be forced to do sports activities at least 3 times per week.
In my opinion, I agree their thought and encourage the goverment to make some policy about it.
There are several reasons for my opinion.
To begin with the most important one, from a research of Cambridge University those students who have sports activities daily can actually have a brighter future than the others.
The reason for this is simple, those people who have daily sports not only have a health body, but also have a spirit of never give up.
Which means they will have more chance in their future than others.
Secondly, there are two kind of students------- those people like sports and those people don't like sports.
For the first type, their schools or universities don't need to force them do weekly sports activites.
But for another type, it is necessary for their schools and universities to force them do weekly sports activites.
Because if their schools or universities not force them, they will never do some sports activities that can make a bad influence to their health.
Last but not least, do sports activies can bring us a lot of positive effect.
On one hand, do daily sports activies can make us healther.
On the other hand, it can also make us have a wonderful social life.
For example, you can make a lot of new friends when you are having sports activites, which can make you a better personality.
By the way, when you are doing sports activits, you can gain lots of precious memories that you can recall someday in the future.
To summarize, students should have daily sports activities.
Our schools or universities should force their students if it is necessary.
There is a question of our behavior to our own life, would you prefer a long calm life or a short intense life?
Everyone have their own answer for this question.
In my opinion, a short intense life is wat more better than a long and calm life.
There are several reasons for my opinion.
To begin with the most important one, from a research of Cambridge University those people who have intense life are actually can have a better life than the others.
They explain it with a theory, the personability of those people who have a intense life are more positive, they know what to do when something studdenly happen.
Secondly, from my point of views, a long calm life means a boring life.
But life should be exciting, which means people are wasting their life if they spend everyday doing the same thing.
By the way, although those people who in calm life can live a long life, when their old they won't have anything to recall.
Last but not least, a intense life maybe is short, but it will make you feel refreshing everyday.
For example, you can make new friends everyday or experience new adventure normally.
If you have intense life, on one hand, you can fill your own life with a lot of valueable memory.
On the other hand, when you are old there will be lots of things for you to recall.
To summarize, a intense life is better than a calm life, even intense life are always short.
In holidays or in the week-end, an outing to the zoo is always welcomed, especially among the youngest.
But are zoos suitable places for the animals kept inside ?
Wouldn't it be smarter and wiser to leave them in the nature?
I would say it depends.
Indeed, nowadays the wild life is increasingly threatened.
Poaching, mass breeding, trafics and destruction of the ecosystems are the main reasons to the dramatic plummet of the differents types of animals on Earth.
But the listing is far from being complete, and wild life today has nothing to do with the variety we could have observed 50 to 100 years ago.
And that's where the zoos can act -in a good way.
By providing the animals a living environment, obviously much smaller than the one they would have had in wild nature, but much safer for them and their offspring, zoos are helping to preserve a wide variety in the fauna.
Therefore, zoos can be an excellent way to preserve wild life.
Besides, by showing them off to public, everyone can learn about them and be sensibilized to their protection.
As long as the world will stay as it is currently, there's no way we could return those animals to natur.
It is true that they belong to it, but nature is no longer safe enough for them, whatever say the ecologists who would like them released - and therefore delivered to human madness and to death.
In this modern society, the rate of chronic patients gradually increases every year, which represents there are more and more human unhealthy.
Why does this situation happen?
It can attribute to the irregular daily routine and sleep schedule.
According to the investigation, the data demonstrated that office workers are under a lot of pressure at work, and in their leisure time, they prefer to veg out in front of the TV rather than do exercise.
It is a malignant cycle; therefore, there are more and more scientists promote to exercise which can help you in shape and healthy.
In my viewpoint, I concur to force students to participate in the PE class.
First, healthy habits should be cultivated in childhood.
Schools can teach students correct concepts about diet and sport.
This type of knowledge can be applied in their whole life.
Consequently, when growing up, they understand how to take care of themselves and maintain a regular daily routine.
When entering in the elder, they can prevent severe diseases and enjoy jubilant retirement.
Second, the purpose of having sports activities is not only healthy but also sound development of the body.
When doing exercise, individuals ought to acquire how to control perfectly their bodies to meet up the standard.
This is extremely significant for children, for they are supposed to gain the rules of each item, which can enhance the development of the brain.
Finally, having PE class can make students experience a diversity of sports.
These kinds of encounters can't obtain from the book.
Besides, when playing games, they enroll in how to coordinate with others, how to confront failure, and how to make use of strategy, and so forth.
These advantages are useful in whole life.
To sum up, forcing students to do sports activities is all benefits without harm.
It can not only reduce diseases but also increase longevity.
