Some people may cast an doubt on why suddenly this restriction on using mobile phones are put in place.
However, after observing immoral behaviors in so many public places, I am on your side.
It is because immoral behaviors in trun causes a fliction or a lawsuit between the people in our town.
This trend was suprising to me, to be honest, because I believed that our people living in this town could live a life without a specific rule in a mobile phone usage.
Yet, the reality was in contrast.
I found a lot of cases in last year just to argue an offensive behavior triggered by mobile phone usage.
To protect our life, this implementation should be welcomed by all of us.
Said that, one suggestion from my side is to launch a new educational programme for everyone to digest what is morral behavior in the public spaces and what isn't as an example via video streeming service.
While it takes time to penetrate this common understanding on how to use a mobile phone in the public place, I strongly consent that educational contents prevent our future conflicts in mobile usage, for sure.
Hi, I hope you're doing well !
Last friday, I went to a music concert with my day to attend the first-ever representation of Rossini's Barber of Seville in our town.
I was keen about going to that concert because I love Rossini's music.
Besides, it was the first time that opera was played in the music hall we went in !
For this special event, we had first class musicians and singers performing in front of us: the London orchestra and famous singers from all around the world.
The actor performing Figaro was excellent and he had a wonderful voice.
The hall was already overcrowded when we arrived.
Luckily we had booked tickets previously so we managed to get good seats.
The show has last for 2 hours.
Although it was long, I really enjoyed beeing there !
Therefore I strongly recommend to go and attend to one of their representation: I'm sure you would enjoy it as much as I did!
Have a nice day
