As my conclusion, depending on the situation, telling a lie is acceptable instead of forbidding to lie for the entire life.
The reason why I think so is coming from my personal experience.
When I was 18 years old, I bumped into a robby in a doom street.
I was threthen by a knife and asked whether you had enough money or not.
On the spot, I suddenly told a lie not to be captured and harmed.
I pretented to be a jobless guy wondering to find a food and a clothing.
I told him to give ten dollers as I picked it up on the street today as a mercy.
Fortunately, I was safe because of my wittey lie coming across to my mind.
If I were to be persistent in a principle not to tell a lie to others or less flexible, I may get injured or captivated.
Of course, on the daily occasions, keep telling a lie to others deminishes your trust in the end.
Hence, it should be better to refrain from a lie even on a tiny matter as a habit.
Yet, if you are in a crisis, I would strongly recommend you to be agile and tell lies if needed for your safety.
My experience might be extreme but the intent of quoting this example is to stress that telling a lie justifies your end depending on the situations.
