Immersion is the fastest and the most effective method to learn foreign language.
Nowadays, many young people have led a sedentary life style that means they rarely get involved in sports activities, and therefore it is suggested they should be required to do sports at least 3 times every week.
I completely agree with this method.
First and foremost, inactive life style has affected the physical health of young students.
Without adequate physical exercise, they are more likely to suffer from some illnesses, such as obesity, diabetes and heart disease, which would do harm to their personal life and study in the long term.
Thus, if they are able to participate in sports activities, these problems could be solved because their immune system and body circulation would be enhanced by doing sports.
In additon, young people who appreciate a healthy life style with more opportunities of taking part in sport activities may develop their interpersonal skills more easily than those people who always stay indoors.
In particular, through doing a team sports, they could have more chances to communicate and cooperate with others, which would be a key ability for their future life and career.
Therefore, at school, sports clubs are perfect places where people can develop their social skills by meeting new friends and interacting with their peers, and learning sports in PE classes is also beneficial for them to learn how to work in a team and sovle problems with others' assitance.
Admittedly, many opponents may disagree that young students should be forced to do sports for certain times as they ought to have rights to make plans for their leisure time.
If they are persuaded to take part in those sports activities, they may hardly be interested in those sports and build a more negative attitude to physical exercise.
However, one fact needs to be highlighted is that the physical problems caused by the lack of sports activities has been a huge concern around the world, which should be solved immediatedly.
Besides, the addiction to computer games and social network websites have impeded the enthusiasm of doing sports for many young people, and therefore this solution should be valuable and effective.
In conclusion, from my own perspective, young students in universities as well as school children should be forced to do sports regularly.
