At first impact with the question, it's too easy to answer that the truth is always the only thing to say and to listen.
Sure, this is an utopian reality, and a world without lies will not ever exist for the main reason that the human beings are imperfect.
This obvious statement drives me along the line of thought that is a skill of some people telling lies that seem truth for a personal aim, and who doesn't have this skill is forced to have at least the ability to listen carefully the sound of the true statements.
I don't think that one person can be able to tell always the truth, but there are very important differences about the way and the reasons why we tell a lie: sometimes we have to defend our bad behaviour, often it's necessary for a "politically correct" speech, in other cases it could be just to avoid that our listener could know our business or planes.
But, such as I said firstly, this is a dangerous joke: if you aren't able to cover your lies, your risk is to damage your public opinion and to seem a lier, even if you tell the truth.
However, the best way should be to choice the moments that need a sane lie, and all the others which it's better being sincere and truther.
