The school of the future will differentiate in many ways from a standard educational model.
The teachers will not occupy the center the of the class but will become a mere facilitators.
However, the importance of their role will persevere.
It is the profile of the job that will evolve.
The teachers of the future will cherish the pupils and hold them in the center of their attention, the center that has been taken by the curriculum.
All of the teachers will be emotionally trained to maintain a high level of communion with the students.
They will have a positive attitude and dulcet voice so students can feel that they are welcomed at all times.
Students will decide upon their schooling programme which is immensely elastic.
They will need to know a little about all everything, and everything about one chosen discipline.
There will be no grading system, just the feedback pointing to strenghts upon which students can build their knowledge.
However, the teachers will always be avaialble for students if they only wish to expand and amend some of their work.
