As to the school of the Future in Japan, I think it will become more flexible.
At present, basically we have to go to school physically and have to study in a class room by face to face.
But after COVID-19 pandemic in Japan, Japanese government had to lock down the cities.
And a lot of schools were closed for several months so that many children could not go to school.
As the result of this, it was very hard for children and teachers to catch up the curriculum.
Through this experience, Japanese government decided to change the way of education.
The government gave PC tablets for all students each and started to use the tables for the lessons.
I think this is the first step for new style of school.
In near future, we will be able to study on line, it will be not necessary to go to shcool physically.
To be honest, I think there are many problems to solve for on line school.
But it will be changed to go better way.
