Have you ever asked yourselves about your reasons of learning English ?
Indeed, I have and I would like to tell you why it is paramount to learn English in my opinion.
As a matter of fact, English is spoken all over the world.
Wherever you go, everyone talks in English.
Consequently, by speaking English, I am able to travel worldwide.
Besides, English is a fantastic language and not so challenging to learn.
With method and motivation, it is entertaining to discover another culture.
Furthermore, in my future career I will have to speak and understand English.
Scientific jobs are the quintessence to explain that idea.
For instance, all research reports will be in English because the USA and the UK are significant in research and development.
Also, journalism is an illustration of a job which you need to master English.
To put in a nutshell, not only do I discover a different culture from mine, but I also can meet new people living abroad.
What about you ?
Tell us about your reasons of learning English !
Should computers and tablets completely replace books in schools and universities?
I disagree.
First, I want to mention from books' advantages.
Though screen technologies improve steadily, books are still healthier than tablets and computers.
And although books can burn easily, digital books can be lost and corrupted easier.
For instance, an electricity shortage can delete all the data.
On the other hand, digital books can be stored simplier and besides, don't require that much care.
Also, they can connect the big data.
Why we have to wait for the latest version when books can receive momentaly updates?
Thus, I claim we should maintain both kind of books.
Is there a fire in library?
No problem, we have all the same datas in our digital books anyways.
Are some digital books deleted suddenly?
Okay, we just have to scan the solid versions of those books.
What do you think?
