I believe that it is better for students to have new teachers each year.
I have three reasons of that.
First, if the teacher is bad for a student, the student needs to endure for several years.
It is not good situation for an important period of the student growth.
Second, if the teacher is only one person, it is difficult for the students to judge that the teacher is good or not because they don't have the person whom they can compare.
As a result of that, if the teacher has a unfair thinking, students might be affected badly from the teacher.
Finally, one teacher has a limit of view and thinking.
A teacher might notice a student' good point but the other teacher might notice the student's good point.
I believe that each student has several different good points.
If the student can extend his/her talent from childhood, it is lucky for him/her.
