Generally speaking, people who live in rural areas fewer than urban cities.
Also, the financial basis in rural areas is lower than urban cities.
As a result of those, doctors are not able to make a lot of money because of the shortage of patients and area's budget.
However, the necessity of the doctor in rural areas is same as urban cities.
Thus, we need to find out any solutions to this problem.
Regarding this problem, I would like to propose three solutions.
First, it is natinal government support.
For example, it is to transfer the money from nation to rural areas as a medical budget.
Second, to create a new law which every doctor need to go to a rural area for several years in their career as obligation.
Finally, it is to change the government system.
Now the rights in rural areas are lower than national power.
So it is better to change the social system and transfer the power from the national government to each rural areas.
Telling the truth, for some person is always essential, indeed for them is unacceptable to say a lie, even when it is said for a good reason.
Tell the truth is good behaviour, however, I do not agree with the idea of never tell a lie.
In my opinion, sometimes, a lie can be extremely helpful and useful.
Indeed say a lie for good reasons can help you in various situations.
For instance, when you have to tell a bad announcement to a friend, at that moment you can tell him a lie, but after you must say him the reality.
Indeed, I think that every one of us sometimes tells lies, the important thing is to be sure that it does not cause any issue .
Sometimes, telling a lie can help a person.
Indeed lie to someone to help him is a behaviour that many people adopt for various motivations.
For example, they lie because do not want to harm someone or not cause and overstress him.
I think that says a lie, for these reasons, is acceptable and especially is helpful .
To summarize telling the truth is very important and especially it is essential to be a good person, but sometimes says a lie is acceptable especially when it is for a good intention .
