I understand that some people believes zoos are good places for people to learn about animals.
However, I also believe that zoos are not good for animals.
I would like to consider that I replace animals to human based on some examples.
First, animals in zoos are separated from their parents and children.
I can not put up with that.
It is very crucial.
Second, animals in zoos finish their lives only in cage or very limited field.
Same as the first example, it is very crucial too.
Third, animals in zoos are seen from a lot of people.
It is not be relaxing.
Fourth, there are no options to everything.
Animals in zoos can not choose foods, friends, lovers freely.
The situation is not fun for me.
I believe that no one has rights to control anyone's lives including any animals.
So I do not agree to existence of zoos.
I know that some companies let their employees work in enclosed workstations or cubics.
However, I do not like that way.
Moreover I believe that it is more efficient not to separate employees each other by walls.
If there are walls, it is not easy to talk to coworkers when they need.
People feel a wall in mind same as the physical situation.
If there no wall and all space are free, employees are able to sit down where they like everyday.
Under expansion of COVID-19, a lot of companies are applying remote working style.
As a result, many employees don't often get using their desk in their office.
Then needs on individual desks got lower than before.
So we do not have the needs to make walls to separate each employees.
I understand that the situation and efficiency depends on the industry.
However, if the company is able to have options, I recommend to set no wall in workplaces.
Nowadays, schools offer many extra curricular activities to their pupils which include music tuition.
On the other hand, some schools do not offer music in their syllabus.
In my concept, music and arts are crucial in all education systems, and consequently, they should be thought to everybody.
Learning music is one of the activities which develop mental skills, specially when tuiton iniciates from early childhood.
There is a lot of social research that supports the positive connection between brain development in children and the ability to play an musical instrument.
Some schools, for instance, have introduced music classes in their schedule, however, and unfortunately, only private education institutions can provide these classes because of the high cost of musical instruments that parents might no be able to afford.
Another point to have in account is that being considered a music master imply many hours of full time and dedicate study, and this obviously, is something than public schools are no able to provide, and probably students neither.
I consider that music tuition is a must in education, and as societies, we should find ways to benefit our children with something that is part of our history and culture.
