Some people might argue that all university students and school children should be forced to do sports activities at least 3 times per week because of the negative effects on health of an inactive lifestyle.
I understand where they are coming from.
However I don't agree with the argument.
First, I have a question whether an inactive lifestyle definitely affects to health.
If so, many people who don't sports often die earlier than people who do sports a lot.
I don't have related data on my hand.
Also I often see people who don't sports are long life.
So I am not able to judge the clear relation between health and doing sports.
Second, Rben though there is a obvious data which indicates the positive relation, it is not good to make people do sports as obligation.
I understand that it is important to put people's health first.
However, we should respect people's right.
People have rights to do something they like.
For example, some people might feel happiness when they are in their house all the time.
They might understand that it is better to do sports for them.
However, they want to put their happiness first.
At that time, Should we forth them to do sports ?
Third, Some university students and children have already done sports by themselves.
In that case, if schools and universities forced them to do sports more, they are tired.
I don't know the actual percentage of them because of no date related to people doing sports by themselves.
However, It is definitely not zero.
