Someone might hope that shorter life but much more intense.
I understand where they are coming from.
However I would like to live a long, calm life.
There are three reasons.
First, I would like to use a lot of new technologies.
As you know, technologies have been developing and innovated everyday.
I am not able to imagine new technologies in the further.
So I am looking forward to using new technologies and living in new lifestyle.
Those are like dream lands.
Second, If my life is long, I am able to experience a lot of kinds of things.
There are a lot of things which I want to do.
If my life is short, I am able to choose just a few things.
However, If my life is long, I do not make a limitation.
I am able to go where I want to go.
I am able to eat whatever I want.
I am able to read a lot of books which I want.
Third, the reason why is that I feel happiness when I am calm.
I like to drink black tea on sunny day with my lover.
I like to lay down on grass in a park.
I like chatting with my lovers and friends calmly.
Any way, I have naturally lived like that already.
Given a choice between a long, calm life and a short, intense one, I would definitely opt for the former for these following reasons.
For one thing, there are certain potential drawbacks of leading a fast-paced lifestyle.
That is to say, it is highly likely that you would make mistakes and due to lack of time, you tend to overlook those negative experiences, hence no lessons are learned and no adjustment are made for better in the future.
Also, when people live in a hustle and bustle pace, they tend to overly speed things up.
As a result, more accidents and errors would occur.
One case in point is the account of surpassing safety driving speed on highway, which leads to thousands of roads accidents every where in the world.
For another, adopting a lifestyle which is calm and tender could bring about several benefits.
Firstly, people would have the time to reflect on their experiences, hence improving the future outcome when the same scenario happens.
Secondly, this pace of living would allow people to avoid the probability of being stressed as well as the better chance to relax and recharge their energy.
Finally, not every aspect of life could be felt or achieved in merely a single moment.
It does take nine months for a pregnant mother till her due day or it takes maybe a lifetime to understand some one.
In conlusion, though living intensely with a timetable full of activities sounds exciting, I would choose to lead a calmer lifestyle because of several values it offers.
