Nowadays, it is undeniable that playing videogames is the most common current teenagers fondness, moreover it has given many employments to workers.
However, this activity is equally undervalue by adults, since the game is a big distraction source.
Firstly, most videogames shows players differents useful skills, such as creativity, follow instructions against the clock and coordination.
Futhermore, there are some game avaiable in a foreign language, therefore you might be forced to understand the words and, consequently, your brain will think more.
Secondly, adults are searching everyday an alternative to screens: one of them is doing exercise.
An advantage of this activity against bits world is natural light radiation, moreover muscles movements.
Finally, get a job on videogames industry is actually very easy.
By our days, young people can have a degree of Graphic Design and create their own computer games, and even a graduate on Translation could write the script of a Nintendo videogame.
As a conclusion, I argue that videogames are really important in our lives, since they have made a huge impact on our society.
So, dear parents, you should not try to hide this art to your children.
Even though lack of exercisng bring negative effects to our bodies, it is not appropriate to force students to play sports.
Indeed, there are several reports and researches about the negative effect caused by the lack of exercises.
Therefore, there are many articles advocating the advantages of frequent exercises and sports in magazines, newspaper and the Internet.
However, when it comes to force students to do exercises and play sports, it is an another story.
The following contains other feasible way to prevent students' health from getting worse, better way to encourage student to exercise more, and the reason of my disagreement.
First, playing sports is not the only way to maintain our health in a fair condition.
In other words, having a well-organized eating habits can also have impreesive effect on keeping good health.
For example, cauculating your carories of meals and make sure the nutrition you take in meets the daily requirements, avoid having meals in midnights, and do not touch fried meals.
Second, Instead of setting rules about the times they need to exercise, it is more rewarding for them if there are related events, contests, or even championships.
By helding a variety of sport events, the students will be interested in sport rather than being forced.
Last but not least, since there are different kinds of sports, it is possible for them that some certain way of playing sport do not make them excercise enough.
For instance, defensive positions in basketballs and baseballs.
Not to mention those who got no interested in these sports try to find a cozy spot for themselves and watch the whole game without moving much.
In conclusion, I do agree that one refuse to have a proper exercising habit will eventually lead him or herself to have a body with deteriorating health.
But it is also necessary to find a flexible way for student to let them enjoy sports, instead of forcing them to do so for their own good.
