My favourite season of the year.
I would say I love all the seasons, but asking me for a favourite season, I would prefere Autumn.
Autumn is a season of colour.
It's colour changes it's outlooks. Especially the red eyebrows and the yellow beard, the exquisive purple eye and a pink smile.
Actually, these are not the perfect reason that I love Autumn.
There is a story behind it.
I still remember that year in late Spring, when I was only 6, my parents took me to my grandparent's farm in the countryside.
It was very boring those days, becuase there are no Wifi and internet.
I have nothing to do for days.
One day, when I was playing in the barn with some nuts, something in the corner caught my eye.
It was a squirrel.
It was watching me.
I looked at it, it looked at my nuts in my hands.
I threw one him.
He caught it and ran away fast.
About 2 minutes later, I saw him arrived again, this time, with 2 more squirrels!
I started to have fun with them.
What brings me together with Autumn is animals.
I love animals, they are adorable, too.
