Following the recent and dramatic development of Internet, schools have to update their way of teaching.
The question at hand is: should computers and tablets completely replace books in schools and universities ?
On the one hand, substitute books in tablets could be very useful for students.
As a matter of fact, books are generally numerous and heavy.
It is consequentially harmful for students' back.
Moreover, tablets could make the learning more entertaining: there are usually many animations, it is quite fun for the students to discover them.
On the other hand, tablets are not flawless.
Indeed, they present a major impact of the student's vision.
It is not healthy to stay behind a screen all day long.
Another point to consider is whether the tablets are really reliable.
Sometimes, the tablets may cut out, Internet could stop working.
Besides, using tablets significantly increase the risks of cyber-bullying.
Of course, a contrary opinion might be that students are grown up enough to behave like adults.
To put in a nutshell, even though tablets are handy, they can be hazardous if they are used on a daily basis.
Many new electronic products are invented these days.
It is not special to see people even children using computers at home and tablets in public places anymore.
Since these electronic devices are commonly used, and network technology is quite steady, schools start thinking to let students use computers and tablets for learning instead of papers and textbooks.
In my opinion, e-learning should be totally adopted in school campus.
First of all, replace books by tablets is environmental friendly.
Books are made from paper and some contain plastic, and people have to cut off trees to make papers.
Then there is less fresh air produced, the soil would also loosen without consolidation of tree roots.
Abandon books that contain plastic will pollute the environment as it is not easy to be digested in nature.
Compare to paper which negatively affect the environment, electric device cause less damage to the nature as we would't throw device away frequently.
One must not forget that tablets and computer is more easier and effective to learn than books.
Tablets and computer can store documents as many as you need to study.
All we need to do is find the location of the document and open it.
We can also use them to watch educational videos for having fun while learning.
On the contrary, it is difficult for us to find a worksheet in a pile of paper.
Add on it, there is no video in textbooks, only print out pictures for us to take a look.
It is less interesting and effective than using electric device.
In conclusion, I think that schools should take advange of modern technology in to education.
it is a fantastic tool to learn and acquire knowlege as they can broadcase video and have huge storages.
It also save the planet at the same time by reducing deforestation and air pollution.
Therefore I agree that computers and tablets should completely replace books in school and university.
