I thing beeing healthy is more important than beeing rich.
I was sick for the last two years, all money in hole world doesn't matter when you're in unberable pain.
First, I had a benile brain tumor.
Before surgery it had hurt so badly I wanted to cut off my head.
After surgery half of my face was paralysed.
Actually, it's over two years since the tumor was cut out of my brain, and I'm still not in shape I used to be.
When I was visiting my doctor, he said that I still have something in my head.
Something else.
It turned out, that I needed another surgery.
This time it was malicious tumor, a glioma.
After I left neurosurgery department, my condition required radiotherapy and after that chemoterapy.
I was lucky that my inssurance covered all the bills.
Some people aren't so lucky and then they need hudge amount of money for their treatment.
That is the reason for spending your money.
So yes, money also are important, but health is the most important.
