Computers and tablets should take over the role of books in academic institutes.
Electronic devices provide much greater use than printed materials.
For instance, they update information faster, store greater quantities of data and permit access to the Internet for further online research which are the essential limitations of traditional means of storing information.
It is also observable that for such convenience, in modern times, books no longer retain their appeal to readers as they used to, which is witnessed by the drastic decrease in book sales.
Therefore, computers and tablets are bound to replace the hard copies of words in schools and universities.
Replacing manual with high-tech devices in education facilities is a risky choice for the fact that it requires exhaustive financial resources to purchase these appliances.
In Vietnam, a similar proposition was introduced to the National Congress but was denied for costing half of the national development budget to initiate such transformation without any definite guarantee for its results.
In conclusion, modern technological devices such as tablets and computers should not be encouraged to be present as the main storage of information in schools and universities.
For years the schoola have designed differents methods of study, many of them have included extra calsses like dancing and music lessons.
There are research which shows that these kinds of lessons are befeficar for students.
However, not all schools offer these classes for their student population.
The advantages that learning or practicing music have been exposed by many research.
For instance, it is known that if children practice dance or how to play any musical instrument, improving their academic performance.
In addition, for children in their first ages, a musical education stimulates brain zones which allow the development in areas: cognitive, emotional, motor, affective and linguistic.
Some institutions have included musical education as compulsory subjects due to all its benefits, however, not all school have the infraestructure to give this kind of education.
In conclusion, the advantage of having a musical education are abvious, there are research and evidence to support the results.
Thta is why governments should invest to improve the infraestructure and be able to offer a better education.
Television was originally invented for severing the entertainment purpose for people in the industry time.
However, the contents on the television are gradually changing and offering various choice to serve the dinstinctive need of individual.
Nowadays the contents designed to support learning purpose especially for children were accounted for 20 percentages.
Many channels embark childhood development by intervening knowledge with entertainment that displyed through cartoon charactors to attract the children attention.
To reap the fully benefit from television, children psychologist advise parents to spend time on television with thier kids to mark the imperative knowledge and observe their learning curve.
National geography is the other educated program which available on television for free.
This program broaden the biology perspective, compress it in the uncomplicated way to consume and open the whole new world for adults and children.
Television also assembles ubiquitous vocabularies and evokes the linguistic development in the early child stage.
Some researches disclosed that television is the first source of English learning for students in countries speak the least English around the world.
In succinctly conclusion, television entertains, but it also educates people in effective way.
