I think that we have same problem in Japan.
Most medical doctors want to work in cities for earning more money.
As the result of this trend, there are not enough doctores in many rural areas.
I think that there are some reasons for this problem.
One is that there is a regulation that doctors are not be allowed to see a patient by internets in Japan.
In Japan, we have to see a doctor by face to face, doctors can't see a patient by internets by the regulation.
If the regulation will be changed, doctors can see a patient by internets, I think the problem will be solved to some extent.
Whereever we live, we can choose a doctor and see the doctor by internet as a first step.
If the regulation will be changed, it will be eased for doctors to live in cities.
Second is that it costs very expensive to be a doctor in Japan.
In Japan, if you want to be a doctor, you have to study in a medical university for 6 years and have to obtain the certification by the government.
Except public medical university, private medical university's cost is expensive, I think that it is necessary to pay about 5 to 10 thoudsands dollers per year.
I think it is difficult for ordinary people to pay such high cost.
So I think that if there are more scholarship fund enough to increase the number of new doctors, the problem will be solved to some extent.
Yes, it is.
