There are some advantages of studying abroad.
Firstly, the students are able to learn a language of the other countries.
The option of jobs will expand because of the conversation skill.
Secondly, they are able to learn diversity.
It is important to experience it under globalization.
Thirdly, they are able to make foreign friends.
Those are great treasures in their lives.
On the other hand, there are also some disadvantages of studying abroad.
Firstly, it might be difficult for someone to fit in the other cultures.
Secondly, they might feel stressed.
Many of them are not able to talk with people smoothly because of different languages.
Thirdly, they need to part away from their local friends and families.
They are not able to spend students times with their friends and families instead of staying in the other countries.
That is all I would like to explain about the advantages and disadvantages regarding studying abroad.
Should computers and tablets completely replace books in schools and universities?
The recent technological changes in society have brought up an interesting discussion regarding the complete disregard of books in schools.
In my opinion, we should get rid of all the books in schools and universities with regard to learning and I will explain why.
Books are magic.
They tell stories and enable us to practise empathy.
However, the main goal of books in education is not the magic but the knowlegde they contain.
On top of that, there are some incredible benefits to using technology in schools.
The digital learning aids are able to correct the student's work, saving the teachers a lot of time.
Some technologies are even able to send students to an exercise that best fits they current level of learning, enabling personalized learning.
Therfore, I believe that books should always be in schools but not as a means of learning.
