Nowadays, minority of medical doctors want to work in cities which is not the perfect scenario for rural areas.
Let's have a quick look why it is happening and how can it be solved.
The most crucial reason for this is very simple.
In cities, especially big cities they are able to make more money than in rural areas.
Everyone wants to be paid good.
Another thing which also matters is housing.
It's a lot easier to rent an apartment or a house in city.
Also they can get to theirs office faster, and as we all know time matters.
Who would want to spend 2 hours of their day just to get to work?
There are few things which can be done to solve or minimze this important problem.
Firstly, we need to reduce the time which is required to get to a doctor.
We can achieve it by upgrading our roads and making more roads for bicycles.
This solution will help reduce the time spent at the doctor, as well as ,it will increase the number of pacients, which will boost their earnings.
It also should create new opportunities for investors, which will build new housing for doctors and other people.
Secondly, we need to show people that they don't have to wait few weeks just to get to a doctor.
By choosing a medician from rural area they can heavily reduce the time, which they have to wait.
It's good for both pacients and doctors.
Everyone benefits from it.
I think that my solutions are not enough to fix the problem mentioned above, but they should easily reduce it.
