I think there is no a hierarchy of things related at health about what is more important for our health.
That said, there is a balance between the things that are important for our health, where those things are interrelated with each other.
Besides the exercise, exist the mental health.
The mental health is essential for our diary performance and, mainly, for our social relationships.
Without a solid mental health, people are prone to anxiety, depression, aggressiveness, and poor performance at work.
Futhermore, people with a weak mental health have a negative perspective about your future.
People succumb the lack of planning and they don't can being successful in your lives.
To improve their health, people need to meet the equilibrium between mental health and physical health.
For this, people can do exercise before or after the work to improve the physical health, and people can medidate early in the morning, practice a hobbie in the weekend, or they can spend a day with your family to recharge the energies and to improve your mental health.
I think that it is better for university students to move away and live on their own.
I think that it is necessary for university students to be independence.
Different from high school students, university students have to choose what they study in a university, so they should do everything independently.
If you live on their own, you have to do by yourself whatever you live every day, such as making own bed, making meals, cleaning up own room, purchasing goods which you need.
I think that your family have supported you to live except studying when you live with your family till high school student.
But I think that university students are already a part of social members so that they have to be responsible for their own activities inculding every day life.
I think studying is only a part of every day life.
To live on their own is a good opportunity for university students to be responsibility on their own life.
But I also understand that it is impossible to live on their own because of some economic reasons.
By living on their own, it will cost more expensive compared to live with own family.
From my personal experience, I lived on my own when I was a university student in Tokyo.
Before that, I live with my family so that expect studying everything was done by my family.
But after live on my own, I had to cook by myself, clean up my room by myself, wash clothes by my self, get up by mayself.
Until getting used to do, it was very tough for me.
But I think that this experience was very importnat for me to be independence.
So I recommend university students live on their own as much as possible.
