Dear Sir or Madame of the town council as of recent the town council has been taking a bill into consideration which would ban the use of mobile phones on public transport, shops and resturants.
I believe this not to be a wise decition seeing as this may have unforseen consequentses if it would come to pass.
because of this I have decided to outline a number of them so as that the council may make an informed decision.
first of all the banning of mobile phones in public transport will not stop the use of mobile phones unless it becomes the responsibillity of the drivers to enforce this regulation.
second of all the restaurants will be put in a difficult situation. either they loose most if not all their business customers or they turn a blind eye to the use of mobile phones.
moreover even if resaurants would want to enforce the bann who would tell the customer?
certainly not the waiters and waitresses who depend on the customers good will to survive.
a similar situation is to be expected in shops.
Third of all this will drive any visitors to the town away in mere minutes.
all of the problems are related with the enforcement of such a bann.
nobody within the businesses wants to enforce this bann based on the fact that it will loose them customers and over all make ower town less atractive for outsiders.
I cencerly hope you take my points into consideration when felling your decition.
Speaking personally this new year means a new beginning for me so as to set new goals and shoot for the stars in different aspects of the life among those there's the school.
Hence I want to work on different areas in order to be a exemplary student and learn even more.
First of all, I have identified areas of my learning that I'm pleased with such as chemistry, maths and science, I regard myself really good at them.
Moreover, I enjoy learning about maths and science, as a result I'll keep my habits of study in those areas in order to get better and to be part of the honor roll, those habits are the following: do extra exercise every time that I have problems to learn new methods, assist to the science workshop which is given every semester, go to the library to do my homeworks and study with friends.
On the other hand, I have to admit I want to improve in some areas of my learning, as English and German in which I've been struggling since the last semester, to tell the truth I think languages are incredible and can open doors to awesome opportunities in life, bearing this latter in mind I want to improve and make languages a boon in professional career.
So this brings up to prepare and plan some actions to do in short and mid term so that I will be able to achieve my goals in this new year.
For me the gist of the matter is that I have to practise my speaking and listening, as the saying goes practise makes perfect then I will listen to every day a podcast and a lecture in English and a lesson from German.
Furthermore, other actions that I have to do is call some friends who know how to speak German and English, it is highly probable that they have a higher level than me, however the higher the better owing to this I will feel pressure and more inspired to learn more and more.
Finally, I will program some test every two weeks in order to evaluate my progress and to be able to evaluate my action plan, I mean if I have to modify something or implement more activities.
Overall, I have described a brief about the areas of my learning that I'm pleased with and others I want to improve, in that way I wil get the best of the school and surely I can shoot for the stars.
Although video games is not one of my favourite pastime, I know they are very popular with all-aged children.
It seems that children from the richest countries have a stronger interest in them, and the bulk of their time is spent with them.
This is an attitude that makes people worried and comprensively angry.
What parents are afroid of is their sons incapacity to socialise with others; this means that children will run the risk to be isolated adults and what is more threatened is the inability to find a good job.
I consider it a serious problem that involves not only children but the entire society.
I disagree with those who think that video games could have some beneficial effects, unless we refer to some mental diseases where video games are suggested as a teraphy.
In general they are an useless pastime, in spite of children feel video games make themselves at home.
As I see it, there some side effects as the risk to suffer from a long isolation that in the most serious cases could turn into a mental diseases like depression.
Unfortunately, there is an always increasing number of people that need a psycologist to recover from their bed mental state.
Another delicate issue that should not forget to treat is the large amount of violence that children experience through video games.
The point that all scientists agree is the children's difficulties to make a difference between reality and playing, and they think life can be a window-shopping like a video games.
To the best of my knowledge, video games have never made people more clever and the efforts of the society should be adressed to prevent childred to overuse them.
Nowadays zoos are the place where families pass the bulk of their time, because they are under the misimpression that thier sons can learn about nature and animals.
This is a false impression because when you want to learn about animals you have to aee them in their natural environment.
What I mean is that animals living in a zoo are denaturalised, and you cannot learn nothing interesting.
To the best of my knowledge. when a family gots a trip around the real animal's environment, they learn much more than they do in a zoo.
In a zoo there are only few animals and you cannot see how they behaviour for example when they stay in a herd.
Seeing three or four animals is just a drop in the ocean; you will see how more exciting is to study animals in their natural environments.
For example a herd of tigers are hunting zebras and smaller animals in a huge ground; this is something impossible to see in a zoo.
Another remarkable point stressed by environmentalists is that animals are not well treated in a zoo and they soffer living in small rages.
In other words animals need beneficials of a wildelife.
In spite of some proposals to enlarge the rages and the zoo area, this optimism-based statements do bot persuade those who want to see animals flee in a forest.
Nowadays, every comapy has an office.
Some of them decide to make enclosed workstations, while others, usually newer ones, don't even make walls separating employees from their coworkers.
In my opinion, the shifting meta towards less enclosed offices is very good for workers.
Just think about it.
Everyone wants to work in place where there are no barriers between coworkers, no matter of the position in which they are.
Everybody is easily acessable due to this.
More importantly working in such place allows people to feel like they are in their own home.
This way allows employees to feel less crowded and just more cozy.
Further going, due to reduced stress, people are more efficient and they are more likely to do their tasks correctly.
It is a perfect example of a win-win situation.
Employers are happy because, workers are doing their work right and employees are happy, because they are not stressed at all.
Unfortunately, as everything this way of arraging offices has some downsides, so it's not perfect of every office.
Some jobs require from employees to be concecrated the entire day.
They often have to be precised in thing which they are doing.
It's for sure easier to achieve when you are in an enclosed, quiet workstation.
In some offices, employees work in enclosed worksations or cubicles.
Other offices have a more open design, in which there are no walls separating the employees from their coworkers.
Both settings have advantages and disadvantages, so in this essay, I would argue that enclosed worksatations are better, because it gives more space and privacy that employees need in order to function more efficiently.
In addition, offices with enclosed arrangement can allow workers to work in a more organised manner, and it can also prevent workers to talk to each other during work time; and that will improve work outcomes.
However, offices with no walls separating employees can promote instant interactions between employees, at the same time, it could be distracting for emplyees; which may result in reduced efficiency and productivity in work.
Finally, offices with enclosed workstations are much more convenient than those with open design, because it promotes organisation, discipline and efficiency in workplace.
Unlike open settings in which workers may get distracted by each other; which may result in decreased productivity in work.
Music is plays a vital role in our wellbeing.
In some schools it is compulsory for students to learn and play a musical instrument, while in other schools, there may be no music at all.
In this essay, I will argue that music is important for students but it shouldn't be a compulsory.
I believe music is must be taught in schools, because it is a common communication language between communities around the world, and it is also known for its psychological effects such as reliefing stress, anxiety and fears.
It is scientifically proven that music can be used as supporting treatment for some neurological disorders (e.
g parkinson's disease).
Furthermore, music plays a vital role in almost everyone's life.
Some people listen to music for reliefing stress or remebering good moments in the past; such as times spent with friends and family members.
Music itself can be a gift for humanity, and we should appreciate it by teaching students how to play musical instruments; because that promote their self-confidence and allow them to express themselves through music.
I highly recommend music should be taught for school students in their early years, because it will promote their self-confidence and help build their personalities.
Some university students live on their own while there are attending school, but others live at home with their family memebers.
I think living on your own as university student is much more better than living with your family while you are studying.
I think so, because students at university level should learn to be independent in their life matters, because as we get older we sometimes tend to be far away from our families; so we need to learn how to deal with that without them.
Life is so hard sometimes, so we need to learn how to handle the problems that we face along the course of life.
As university is final stage of education, and it is said to transformational stage in which studnets mentality will grow to become more independent.
Hence, in this important stage of life, students tend to get to know different environments and form new relationship with others and interact as adults.
While living on your own as university student has diverse advantages, however, living with your family during university can be a good alternative specially for young or minor students under the age of 19 years old who are not strong enough to tackle life struggles alone.
In conclusion, I would say it is better for university students to live on their own for some time away from family to learn how to hangle life problems, but for young or minor students it is safer for them to live with family memebers while they are studying.
