Hey Chris, What going on?
How are you?
I am already seeing forward to see you next Saturday, when we will go to the local museum!
For now, I just want to tell you the basic facts about how we are going to travel to the museum, what we can see there and what you need to bring with you.
We are going to take the bus, so we can come to the museum in a proper time.
You will need a bus ticket, but you can also buy it directly in the bus by spending about five Euro.
Please also take some food and drinks with you.
The drinks, as well as the food, are really costly there.
Also take your handy or your camera with you.
Maybe you want to take some photos?
The museum, we are going to go in, exhibits colossal skeletons of ancient dinosaurs.
They also exhibit fossils and other stuff like that.
It seems to me as it is a very interesting exhibition.
I am seeing forward to see you next Saturday!
With friendly greetings, your friend Dieter.
Dear Mr Michael I am writing in reference to your plan about banning the use of mobile phones in some places.
As a resident in this area, I have talked with other local residents about their opinions and we would like that you will know our points of view.
We live in a tourist city which means that our economy depends mostly on foreign people.
Tourist people want always to be able to have access to the social media, they want to show where they are, what they are doing, what they eat and how they feel in specifics places; that is way currently restaurants, shops, hotels, parks and public transport offer free internet access.
This service has allowed that some places have been recognised worldwide; in consecuense, if you decided to apply this law, a lot of establishments will be affected seriously.
I am owner of a restaurant and we made a research about how we would be impacted by the new law, if this law is applicated our affluence of costumers will be reduced approximately 40% of the total and probably we must dismiss some employees.
We hope you reconsider not to apply this law, this in order to protect the economy of our comunity.
Thank you for your time and I look forward to hearing back from you.
Best regards. Lucy Miller
