As far as I'm concerned, I think the students benefit more from having different teachers througout the years.
First of all, having the same teacher for several years induces that the students get used to this teacher.
It can be an advantage: the students know his teacher better, the teacher gets more acceptance and respect all over the years for instance.
However, such a familiarity can have a negative impact on teaching.
Indeed, as the students are used to their teacher, they can get deconcentrated or irreverent more easily.
Besides, it depends on how the teacher works with his students.
If it's a cool, enjoyable but still instructive lesson, then maybe having this teacher for a few years can be great.
Otherwise, if the teacher is boring and his lessons uninteresting, having new teachers each year enables to avoid the problem of having a boring teacher.
Furthermore, having differents teachers each year helps the student to familiarize himself with differents ways of teaching, which can help a lot when he gets in higher education for instance.
To conclude, each teacher teachs differently, therefore a student could enjoy several instruction- all benefits to the mind then.
Mankind found solutions for most problems which makes our lives hard, however this solutiouns sometimes bring some issues with them.
Inacitve lifestyle is one of the problems that modern lifes bring our lives.
Large number of university students are suffering from inactive lifestyle, and their lives become more vulnerable constantly.
I believe that every university students should make sport suring the university.
First of all, making sports improve students learning skills.
Most studies that have been done on university students indicates that students who make sports have more developed brain cells those who don't make any sports.
Having strong cells is essential to learn more quickly and effectivelely.
Furthermore, making sports, provides relief and it reduce stress.
Less stress means more efficent learnign.
Secondly, making sports gice to student another important opportunity: team work.
Students can learn work with each other if they make sport.
There are 2 students, one of whom is making team sport and the other is don't.
Acording to most statistic, the former student tend to work with others more than the second student.
Those who say that making sport is only waste of time and it makes you only tired are wrong.
Because making sport has varous kinds of opportunies, it is essential for student.
It is not a waste of time.
While students make sport, they learn and share.
It is not also make you tired because when people make sport certain hormons make you more energic and also happy.
Therefore, making sports has more beneficial features than we thought To sum up, Modern life is forcing us to unactive lifestyle.
Making spor is the most logical solutioun to solve uncaticvity.
And it is also essetnial for university students.
Thus, every universty students should make sport if tehy don't want to make, then they should be encouraged to make sport.
There are different reasons why medical doctors don't want to work in rural areas, I could just list a bunch of them right here, but I'll try to show the ones I think are the main resons for this phenomenon.
In my point of view the poor wages can be seen as the main reason as all the process to become a doctor involves a lot of money and effort, so it's normal that someone who pass through all these challenges expects a life with the benefits of money in a good place to live.
Another important point that sometimes is neglected is that, as all of us, medical doctors are also humans, they have the right to have this sense of belonging to a community, and to just expect they have to go to a remote place because that place needs a doctor is a naive thought.
These people have families, friends, relatives, relationships that are entangled in the cities they live.
This problems can be seen in different countries, poor or rich, but I believe there're some ways to help solve it.
A short term solution could be more incentives so doctors can be attracted to work in these places.
Another idea that comes to mind is a rotation among doctors so some of them would spend some time in these areas and return home after that.
However the main and lasting solution would be an education system that gives everyone the same opportunities, so this rural areas could have doctor of their own, professionals atached to their communities receveing what a doctor deserves for the work of caring for lives.
