Dear Mr. Stark, I am writing this letter to the council of our town, because I want to give my opinion about banning phones in some places.
In my honest opinion banning the use of mobile phones on public transport and in shops and restaruants is both not good and not wise.
At least from my point of view.
As you know we are living in a free country, also in a free city.
You, as the government of our town, should not ban mobile phones.
By doing this, you are taking part of our freedom in places such as public transport, shops and restaurants.
Further going, I think that most citizens of our town would not enjoy the ban, so would I.
In those places people should be allowed to do whatever they want to.
Some people work remotely from our restaurants.
No one would enjoy losing their job, you or I would not too.
It will for sure be a big hit in those people.
There are more things why this decision is not correct and optimal for the town.
One of them, is that a lot of people are learning or even surfing the web when they are traveling by public transport.
They can learn a new language, read books, messages their friends, etc.
Summarising all the things which I have mentioned I strongly believe that you will change your opinion about this ban.
Your silecerly, XYZ.
In my opinion, for students is better to have the same teacher for several years, especcially for foreign languages.
The reason is very simple, change teachers each year change also the study mode, the teacher pronunciation and so on.
Another reason is, especially in primary school, the relationship between teacher and child is the first step of student grown, and if every year change the teacher, the children don't make a strong relationship with the teacher.
If a child has the same teacher every year, he feels less in awe if he needs help.
Now the teacher situation is more complex than past, because schools haven't the equipment for start a school year with teachers for all subjects, and quite all teachers have a regual job contract.
Every year 50% of the teachers didn't teach in the school where she have taught last year, maybe because they prefer take lessons in a school closer to the long where they live.
