Nowadays it is well known that computers and tablets shouldn't replace books in schools and universities but I firmly believe that they should for these reasons.
Firstly it is highly essential to say that computers and tablets provide students by more amounts of knowledge than books as tablets and computers have Internet so pupils could have access to various sources of information.
As a result of that they can learn more things than reading books.
Furthermore, computers and tablets has videos in which information is better explained than it is in books.
As a consequence of that, children could learn new things in astonishing ways thus they will have better marks.
Last but not least, the information by which computers and tablets provide students are always updating so pupils aren't going to study same things all the time.
Therefore, they will find studying as a rewarding activity.
In conclusion, I absolutely believe that computers and tablets should replace books in schools and universities as it brings more amount of knowledge to students than books, it has stunning videos in which the information is explained better to students and the information of computers and tablets are always updating thus students will find studying as a pleasure activity.
Dear Sir or Madam I am writing this letter in response to the ban the use of mobile phones in public places which the town council is considering.
I believe that it must not be implemented but some rules or law should be necessary.
It is common knowledge that mobile devices are an essential component of people's lives in this modern world and they use it almost everywhere.
It is indisputable that some of them use those with a lack of morality and show disrespectful behaviour.
One of major issues is noise, which is caused by people who talk on the phone loudly on the bus or train, and other passengers are bothered and frustrated.
Although this kind of drawbacks are paramount and should be addressed, using gadgets in public spaces has some advantageous aspects.
For instance, people can do their work, check up their children, read emails and study, which can people's daily lives better and productive.
For this reason, in my opinion, texting, reading and other fanctions that do not make any sounds should be allowed, in other situations, such as in a public library, shops and restaurants should also be considered.
In conclusion, I object to the total ban of using mobile phones in public places.
However, it would be acceptable to control the use of them with some restrictions in order to maintain public morals.
Your faithfully, A citizen
