Dear Sir or Madam, I am writing with regard to the possibility that the use of mobile phones on public transport and in shops, and restaurants wil be banned by the town council.
As a citizen of this town I would like to give my opinion on this matter and give my arguments against this regulations.
First of all, banning the use of mobile phones on public transport is not so good an idea.
Some people have time to talk only when they communte.
What is more, our town is a really popular place for tourists.
I am afraid that this ban will negatively affect our town's economy.
As I have been talking with another citizens, they all agree that banning the use of mobile phones in shops is a very bad idea.
Some pople are very indecesive and they need help to choose the right products.
Usually, there is not enought staff in the shop so, as a result, they phone their relatives or friends.
Banning the use of phones in shops will also negatively affect the economy.
Finally, I do not agree on banning the usage of phones in restaurants as recently there has been a massive interest in food blogging.
More and more people film their food and earn money because of it.
Our town is famous for its restaurants that are friendly for bloggers, YouTubers, and other influencers.
I strongly believe that banning the use of mobile phones is not a good idea.
Overall, it will not only badly affect our economy, but it will also have a negative impact on the citizens' happiness.
Yours faithfully, XYZ
Nowadays, more and more medical doctors desire to work in some cities for handsome salary instead of working in the countryside.
That leads to medical employees deficiency in many rural areas which is a significant issue need interferencing by government.
To solve the problem radicaly, we need to know about the its reasons.
From my perspective, many doctors incline to give priority for big cities as their workplace by virtue of the financial benefits that rural areas can't provide them with.
It is undeniable that doctors in the urban areas could be paid as three times as those in the rural places.
It means that they have handsome incomes to pay their cost of livings and meet their entertain needs as well.
Moreover, working in these cities bring them much opportunities to develop their careers.
Many experts, prestigious hospitals and medical research centres all gather in the big cities all over the world, so it facilitates the medical doctors to develop themselves and take advantage of these benefit conditions.
Another reason is that there is not many up-to-date devices in the medical facilities in the countryside.
However talent the doctocs are, it is hard for them to cure their patients in these poor conditions.
So, what is the sollutions for that issue?
I think there is always need of goverments interference.
