Music class tend to be eliminated in schools gradually because more and more teachers and heads prefer their student learn academy than art.
They think they're right with their ridiculous reason that learning music cannot makes their student pass into a good university.
That's a lie.
Honestly we should add music classes into every grade in school because of wonderful advantages of music for people who have connection with it.
Playing instruments, singing, and even just listening to music are good ways to relax after all depressions that student get in school's academic class.
And we cannot image completely about the power of music in connecting people together.
A shy boy may not feel confident in crown or normal conversations, but he will be a different one with music.
No crimicisms, no ego, just music.
There are so many reliable researches show that music is good for improve our brains and mental health.
According to scientists, playing instruments is an amazing way to develop brain functions.
In other words, we will more intelligent, clever, and reduce Alzheimer disease's risks when we get older if we can play at least an instrument or even just learn how to play it.
We don't need to discuss or demonstrate about the benefits of music for mental health because it's totally clear.
Every single people from the young to the old feel the same way when they listen to any kind of music.
Rhythm can touch all conners in our souls.
Music is a significant treatment to patients used by psychologic doctor.
How can we ignore its benefits to student just because some people think it's not necessary?
Schools should balance academic classes and art classes in student's timetable to get the best effect in teaching and learning.
