As a student who has learnt for 12 years includes living at home with my family for 9 years and living on my own for 3 years, I think that living independently is hard but the better choice.
When we move away and live by ourseflves, there are various problems will appear such as money, time management, balancing learning and working and security.
Money is a first and biggest issue when we live without family.
We have to pay for everything, even something we didn't think about when we were living at home like toileties, ingrediants, cleaners, etc..
In fact, some little needy things in a house for a normal live cost very much in total.
And when you have more things you have to do than just studying and working since you still lived with your family like going for grosceries, cooking, cleaning, etc.,
it takes so much time of you and one important thing is that you have to learn how to manage your time and balance your studying at school and working for your living.
Living independently is really hard and challenging, but if you can do it well, you will realise that you are more mature, independent, confident, responsible than an old version of you when you lived with your parents.
You know how to order your life, and be a reliable and decisive person.
No one can live with us forever, even our parents.
Instead of try to live with family as long as possible, living by your own to develop yourself and make your parents believe in you.
