There are two chief types of office design nowadays: seperating employee's workstations into different cubicles and putting no divider between them.
From my perspective, I would prefer to the first one rather than the latter due to its prominent advantages.
First of all, enclosed workstation tends to enhance focus abilities of white-color workers.
They could not be distracted by externalities such as a coworker's action when there is a divider between them from other employees.
As a result, their work quality will increase and improve a lot.
Moreover, the workers can be insured about their privacy in the office.
The walls separating employees from their coworkers play the role as the wardens for their own houses.
There, they can freely do anything that comforts them without being afraid of anyone else.
A real life example, a man who is forgetful can stick some sticky notes on the one side of wall although his colleage like them or not.
That also helps them avoid some embarrassing situations.
So, workers can work in a good mood which has a positive effect on their work performances.
Another reason is that the walls make the office look more tidy and aesthetic.
They keep employee's workstations in the right order and lessen the risk of taking the wrong stuff of other people.
Bottom line, the enclosed workstations facilite the employee comprehensive.
Making them more concentrate on their work, insuring their privacy, keeping the workplace formal is the things that make this type superior than others.
