When I was a child, my relatives used to ask me what I wanted to be when I was older.
My answer hasn't been what they wanted listening to.
As I said "biologist" or "volleyball player," my cousins answered "a medical doctor."
It is obvious which one had the more attention later.
I think this episode might help us to understand the first question.
A lot of medical doctors don't do what they do because they love this.
The true is: they love the money that working as a medical doctor can offer for them.
From this logic, although we found the key of the problem another questions are formed, such as "how it can solve it?."
Sometimes, I think what kind of society we had if every career earned the same salary.
Would we have a lot of people wishing to become medical doctors?
I'm sure we don't.
To other hand, inside this same logic, I'm also sure that all medical doctors who have still chosen this career would be the ones who would work in everywhere, because they love what they do.
Although this problem seems easy to be solved, it's not.
Changing the society's thought for we could finally have a fearer world where we might work doing what we like, make us changing our way of life (what means our perception about money and happiness).
The medical doctor's problem is just a piece of the hole problem in the modern society
The school of the Future The school system is significangly rigid in comaprison development of our world.
W can think for example about the means of transportation.
It developed from bare foots to shoes, horses, trains, automobiles and the automobiles developed from steam cars to todays hybrid cars.
And what changed in the school so far?
When I was studyiing it looked like this.
I was sitting with my class in a classroom and in front of me was our teacher standing beside a blackboard from there he was lecturing us.
By my knowledge it is not much different from memories of my parents and I think that it ain't no different from memories of their grandparents.
They had been sitting in a classroom and in front of them had been their teacher lecturing.
Ofcourse there are some differencies.
Teachers can use projectors and televisions and maybe students can type their notes on their laptops.
But the princip is the same.
So I don't expect much differencies. I am afraid just about the content of the subjects.
I fear todays cancel culture because it leads to the totality.
