Hello everyone. I am writing you concerning your question about workstation building types.
I think there is no need for any emploee in any carier to have noise during his work.
In other words. If the emploee has noise, he will have a disadvantage at his work and he won't be able to do his work properly as well as if he has a quiet working enviroment.
It might be better toward the employees to move from section to another one to bring or to get something form other company sides but it is such a tiny advantage in comparison to the disadvantage by having noise at work.
In the case to have independence from others desires to listen to the radio or speaking with each other.
It can be devoided by having walls between the rooms or between the workstations.
If the fabric has walls between the sections, the doors can be opened or closed.
However if there are no walls, the space must be always opened and the noise can easily be heard by the coworkers, who work relativ wide away from the noise resources.
I thank you for giving me a chance to express my opinion.
