Hello everyone. I am writing to you concerning your interesting question about the music class.
I have asked my self several times, what the music class gave me during the primary and the secondary school?
I unfortunately always answer the same answer.
NOTHING.
Realy nothing.
If I were allowed to go home and rest, it would have been an encouragement for me to learn more or to finish my homework early.
If the music class were a class, during which the student could utter question, the student would not have wasted long time to ask their parents to solve some complicated issues in the evening.
