The transport sector has started to radically change the way how people will move from point a to b.
Analysing the last decade, the automotive sector started to push electric engines and all the infrastructure to support it forward.
We can expect in close future the ban vehicles powered by carbon fossils and the circulation of cars powered only by electric motors.
We should not expect drastic changes such as flying vehicles for everyone as shown in science fiction movies, but we can expect a more affordable way of transportation between planets instead.
Nowadays the transport between planets using space shuttles is only for astronauts and meant only for space exploration.
In the close future, we will be able to use space transportation also for vacation and work purposes, but probably won't still be affordable for almost everyone, but we should expect a decline in prices year after year.
