There are plenty of aspects to consider when deciding whether always telling the truth is something positive or negative.
Among these, might be the situation we found ourselves to be, the level of trust with the other person or your own sake.
To start with, it is undeniable that everybody has at least once in their live told a lie, nevertheless, besides common situations such as when a friend asks you if you like their T-shirt, not saying the truth could end up as you least expected it.
For example, and most likely, when the other person finds out you have lied to them, and it only gets worse if that person is a techer, your family, or another authority.
On the other hand, liying is almost always the key to lose the trust and respect of someone, as a result, being aware of the consequences of your dishonesty is an important point to consider before acting.
Although it should be said as well that sometimes we do not have a choice.
Last but not least, our own wellness and safety should be mentioned too since we also should bear in mind the impact that telling the real truth might have on us.
Inevitably, now and then we need to look after ourselves and tell some lies to protect us.
As long as that does not become a habit or your intentions are not two-faced.
After those reasons have been exposed, in my opinion, I do think that liying or hiding things is acceptable in certain scenarios.
