As far as I'm concerned that somebody tell a lie is very terrible.
There are many reason that it can bring this answer to me.
The first, the person who often tell a lie will lead to that his or her friends are hard to believe him or her.
For a classic example, it is a fable bewteen the boy taking care for the sheep and the wolf.
The naughty boy thinks that it is very funny to say there is a wolf comes to eat the sheep.
Because of that, all the residents living in the village will come out to pretect the sheep from the attack of wolf.
After the boy pranked the residents for many time, residents heard the boy calling for help again but all of they consider it as a joke and nobody go out to give him a hand.
In the end, the sheep was attack and the residents are very angry.
So the trust between people will be exhausted by the lies.
The second, when a person tell a lie, the person usually have to tell more to let the first one reasonable.
For instance, my friend ,David, hand out with me but him didn't get his Mom's assent.
He also have a clam school need to go in the same time. Therefore he took a phone call to clam school and took a day off. Unfortunatly, the clam school called for his Mom and his mom known that too.
Then him receive the phone call from his Mom, so he made more lie to convince his Mom.
But the truth will emerge in some day.
And he got a guite scolding.
To sum up, being honesty will the best way to live in the world.
