telling the truth is a favourable thing is the value and moral system of all communities around the world.
In addition, telling the truth is an important element in all religious scriptures in which people believe in.
Telling the truth is the centre on which all other human values are based on.
We teach our children to always say the truth no matter what; because the contrary, which is telling lies has very damaging conseqeunces.
Telling the truth can sometimes save lives of others as well as achieves justice for people who are oppressed in the crinimal justice.
Nevertheless, telling the truth is always a good thing because it allows to respect others' rights and maintain their dignity.
In medical practice, it is part of the medical ethics to always say the truth no matter what consquences that might arise from it.
For example, if a surgeon makes medical mistake while performing the surgery, he or she, must disclose the truth of what happned during the surgery with complete honesty even if it will pose them worse consequences.
Similary, telling the truth is part of every other career environments.
People sometimes find themselves in a situation in which they have to tell a small lie; such as making a friend happy by telling little good lie.
I think that may be acceptable as long as it does not hurt anyone or affects anyone's dignity and wellbeing.
