The teacher is a critical factor in the process of education; if we had a bad teacher we may be hurt by him, and if we had a good teacher he will help us, but if we had a great teacher then we will be inspired by him.
The question of what do you prefer a teacher for several years or having a teacher every years is complicated; we can't just answer yes or no, it is not that simple.
My opinion is that it depends on two things, first and foremost, is he inspiring and compatible with the students?
If yes, we can move to the second question, is he able to teach one class for several years?
if the answer to the questions is yes too, then I think he can teach the class for several yeas.
But to be honest; I believe that having one teacher every year is the best choice, why?
Because I had many great teachers over the years, if one of them taught me for several years then I would not be able to know the others, which would be a disaster, because I had learned something from each and every one of them, their words still in my mind, I can still hear them.
To summarize, no, I do not think that having one teacher for several years is a good idea.
Hi my names is Vinicius, I'm a mechanical engeneering student, I'm 26 years old and I live in Brazil.
My profession requires fluency in the English language, I use the website "Write and Improve" to improvement my english.
The program has many question that are divided between beginner, intermediate and advanced.
The user must answer the question by writing on the topic suggested, once completed his answer is automatically corrected with feedback.
My study strategy is to answer at least one question every day.
I have been using the platform for almost four months.
I started witch beginner level questions and answered about 80 questions.
During the time I have been using the tool, I noticed incredible advances in my writing.
Today is my first day at the intermediate level and I'm very happy.
I highly recommend the "Write and Improve," it's an excelent tool to improve your English.
But, in order to be efficient, the user must have discipline to answered the questions during the week and not procrastinate.
That's why I recommend the user to organize their time and do the tasks according to their language level.
Hugs!
