There has been an argue about video games, some people think that it is helpful and fun, while others think it is harmful and may cause addiction.
The truth is actually mix of these two opinions.
If we considered the first ponit of view we see that it is true. Because according to recent studies surgeons who play video are more likely to be skillful than surgeons who do not play video games.
The other thing is that it can be a way to soclise, especially when played as teams.
But let's take into account the opposite point of view.
Video games especially the ones that include violence affects negatively on its players brains; and it reaches its maximum harmful effect when played by children.
The second bad influence video games may have is addiction.
Addiction to video games is called behavioural addiction, it is similar to addiction to lottery or masturbating, which makes the video games a real danger especially for the children and young boys.
My personal opinion is that video games is fun, but we should take care of what we let our kids play on it, and how much time they spend playing; because kids do not know what is harmful or what is not, and that is our reponsibility.
Because of the negative effects on health of an inactive lifestyle, all university students and school children should be forced to do sports activities at least 3 times per week.
In my opinion, this idea is absolutely reasonable.
No one can deny that sports activities can undoubtedly do good to our health.
Appropriate exersice can boost immunity.
Regular physical exercise is not only good for physical fitness but also good for mental health.
Research has found that students who exercise regularly are more positive and optimistic than who don't.
To all school children, doing sports frequently can help us improve concentration, which can help students gain better grades.
What's more do sports activities can improve students' ability of team work.
It can also enhance the relationship between students.
So it is of vital importance for students to do sports activities.
But there are different voices about whether exercise takes up time for study and leads to a decline in academic performance.
From my perspective, it is reasonable to do sports at least three times a week.
Doing sports activities three times per week is understandable.
It can definitely help students resist the inactive lifestyle and form a healthier life habits.
Although not every student is interested in work out, they still should get regular exercise and get used to it.
Take myself for example, I was a people who hate doing sports.
Also, I am extremely found of eating junk food, which led to my terrible health condition and bad grades.
But everything changed when I started exercise.
I work out more frequently than three times a week.
Consequently, both my study and my physical health improved.
Above all, it has been proved that doing sports activities three times a week is of great benefit to students.
And it is Students' duty to take care of their own body and resist inactive lifestyle.
