Nowadays, more and more rural areas are beginning to experience an incredible disagreeable issue: the lack of medical doctors.
This void is due to the fact that many doctors are convinced that the salaries working in remote rurale areas are too low and not enough satisfying.
Thus, the most of them prefer to begin their career in large cities, where they have got the possibility of earning more.
This choice is understandable.
Becoming a doctor is anything but easy: you have to study and commit hard for long time.
As a conseguence, it is just that doctors receive a huge income.
Were I to be a doctor, I would not accept myself less than a $5000 salary.
Therefore, the unique solution is the following: raising the wages of doctors in rural areas, toom, taking them to the same level of those of doctors who work in cities.
Moreover, doctors who choose a rural area as their definitive workplace should get some extra money for that, because the choice of living in a village to help people renouncing to all the comforts of the city is a rewardable.
This was just my humble suggestion in order to solve a problem which is spreading fairly fast and which has to be urgently overcome
