In my opinion, the office where an employee works every day is crucial for his mind and for the results of the company because the environment could influence the employees and the increaseas or decreases of the business depend directly on their productivity.
I think that it is very important to have an open design office in which there are no walls separating the workers.
A satisfactory office could influence the employees\u2019 energy, their focus capacity and mainly the teamworking.
First of all, the workers need to feel strength, willingess and the desire to help the teammate from his team.
An open design of an environment could influence people to establish collegial relations.
When an employee sees all the time the others he could be more motivate to work hard because the competition for the best results would intervene in this situation.
Moreover, owing to the lack of walls which separate the employees they could create a happy workplace with their capacity to make friends or to become colleagues with closed relationships.
On the other hand, enclosed workstations create stress, anxiety, nervousness, tiredness for employees because they spent all their time alone in their office and they fail to exchange stories, opinions or experiences with their collegues.
They don\u2019t have a motivating environment because they don\u2019t have enough time to know each other.
As a consequence, the employees will come to work without enthusiasm and they will not be productive.
All of these should influence their mind and their capacity to work.
In conclusion, an office with a more open design is defining fot the positive trajectory of an employee and it could transform a stressfull and displeasure experience at work in a motivating, lovely and friendly one which influences people in a good way.
