Do we need music in our lives?
The simple answer to the question above is yes.
I cannot imagine a life without music at all.
Without music, life is meaningless and has no color.
Music is very important for me in many occasion, for example, when I am driving my car from home to work and vice versa, or when I am studying or doing exam preparation.
The music has become very crucial when I feel sad or demotivated.
Music lifts me up and reminds me that I am not alone.
Life without music would be so boring and we would be depressed so easily because according to some scientific research, music could bring peace and tranquility on people's minds.
Help us to stay sane when we are at our difficult times.
Music brings a positive emotional brainwaves to our mind which help us to stay calm and relaxed.
That is why in every spa center, you will hear music playing in the background because it can make you calm.
I personally live my life with music.
I cannot live without it.
My favourite season is autumn.
For me, it's the most special season in the year - the leaves are falling down and it's getting colder.
But I would like to tell you a bit more about it: First of all it's good to know that the autumn is also called \u201Cthe golden season\u201C.
Why?
It is really easy: In October, all leaves which are brown and gold are falling down from the trees.
The second fact is, that these days are the last days, where the sun's shining with her whole power and the sun is golden too.
That are two facts why it is called the golden season.
Why I like the autumn?
Well, especially in october, as I sad the sun is really nice and all the leaves are falling down.
I really like it to went trough the park and play with all the leaves.
In my opinion, a second reason is that the temperature is really nice.
It means that it is not to hot like in the summer, but it not to cold like in the winter.
So for me, it is perfect!
In contrast to the previous decades, today's technolody are evolving and widespread computerisation is happening all around the world.
Therefore, many people suggested that the books would be replaced by the digital devices.
In my opinion, it is a good change for the world and will provide so many benefits.
The first and foremost benefit is that it enables to make less of tree logging and deforestation.
As many forests have been knocked down for the production of paper, using computer or phone will reduce the rate of logging.
As a consequence, it can totally give a good impact to become sustainable environment.
The second advantage of using computers or tablets instead of books is that it can provide tremendous information through the internet.
Moreover, not only computers are compact and portable but also it will give a good access to the different kinds of the e-books.
Therefore, it is really easy and convenient for the students anf youths to study every subjects by themselves through the digital platform.
In conclusion, replacing computers and tablets in the pace of the paper-based material would be a good solution for both the environment and all students.
