I certainly think that doing some volunteer work is really good for society in general.
Everyone should spend a part of life of doing that.
On the other hand, I do not think doing volunteer work is someting I should receive graduating for.
I think when you graduate it is important to focus on your knowlegde or you work.
Doing your own project or things like that are more important for graduates rather than being a volunteer.
Being a volunteer is really good, because you help the people or some company and that's a really generous work.
However, you have to devote your time for it and when you study hard it is not that easy.
The time is fundamental for studing and doing your work at school.
As you have to do homework, write essays, learn for passing a test, study to get to another school, you do not have much time.
And the year of graduating might be a bit stressful.
In conclusion, I think that completing a certain amount of volunteer work should not be a requirement to graduate.
And that is because it takes your time to really focus on graduating itself.
People are divided in the purpose of information resources.
