A long calm life or a short intese one.
I think that live a life that worth is the principal goal of any human being.
So, I would prefer a short intense life that worth instead of a long nonsense life.
The principal reason is that I want to travel to a lot of different places and knowing the culture and life there.
I also want to learn as much as I can and create precious moments during my lifetime and if these reasons mean to live a short life but intense, I prefer create memories and live the day, everyday.
I have always wanted to know different parts of the world because I am really interested in cultures and customes from different parts of the world and how behaviour or way of living from one city to another or one country to another change is fascinating for me.
Thus, I would love to live travelling and living experiences in my life.
Another reason why I prefer an intense short life is because I like to learn and knowing a lot.
So, I would like to learn as much as I can in different fields of science or life.
I do not mean how longer I can learn, I just want to learn and try to comprehend the world around us.
In summary, I definitively prefer live a worth life than a long life.
I want to live a life that can be an inspiration of everybody or at leat to people around me.
University life is different when you live alone or you live with your family.
Both cases have pros and cons, but, to me, the better options are living with family.
In my experience university could be stressful and you most of the time don't have enough time to do many activities so, if you live with your family, it facilitates a lot of things such as you don't have to pay attention to expensive bills or making food.
Above that when you live with your family you have more time to focus on your studies and you don't have to pay much attention to other things.
When you live with someone who cares about you, university life is easier to deal with.
In conclusion, if you have the opportunity to choose among go or stay with your parents during your university degree, you definitively should choose the second option because your university life becomes easier.
