As members of a society we sometimes are asked to step up and help other people or the comunity around us.
In some intitutions, like our high schools, it's done by mandated volunteer work.
Is it right?
Must students be obliged to do volunteer work to graduate?
The problems of our society surround us in our everyday lives, when we turn on our tvs or connect to the internet we se a lot of people strugling to have something to eat, places devasteted by storms and flooding, the famine in Africa, etc.
Seeing all that is happening its obivious that something must be done, so it's our responsibility to give support for those in need and sometimes the best way to do it is through volunteer work.
We have to find ways to incentivate volunteer work and our educational sistem have the places where we can nurture our individuals to care for the problems of our society.
Since kindergarten our children must be aware of it's complexity, respecting their ages and undertanding capabability of course, in order to be ready to take action when it's needed.
Conversely, of course we need citizens willing to help our society, but this envolviment must be achieved with education and not obligation.
The obligation is in the hand of our institutions that can incentivate students using win-win solutions that connect those in need with those with the resources and responsibility to help.
