More and more learners have got involved themselves into tackling to acquire a various types of language skills these days, compared to the past days.
Some argue that studying foregin language is simply a waste of time.
However, in my opinion, learning new things such as language generates an essential part of the person's life.
To commence with, not to mention learners can have easy way to contact diverse culture as well as people from walks of life.
If they are familiar with the local language, they can try to understand such as mannners, rituals and etiquettes and so on.
Following on from this, to give an example, tourists who already have knowledge of the local language and destination in advance can make the trip more enriched.
Additionally, one's career chance would be broaden.
It is likely that people who have particular knowleage of language can make effective use of it.
For instance, they would be surprised a number of things that they can expect even if they go on a business trip to another area that they are not willing to go.
That can lead to gain their life experiences and they could accomplish it without the skill.
What is more, practioners can spend productive life.
Largely, learning language will never end and make easily learners give up.
On the other hand, once they keep chellenging the task that would not be necessary, they can be more confident in themselves.
To establish the time schedule to study, they can be more self-discipline.
In conclusion, although there would be no point of learning international language to some people, I am convinced that the way provides us with valuable chances to make one's life more effective.
Therefore, it would be advantageous to learn language.
Dear Sir/ Madame I am writing this letter to you because I wanted to express my opinion on the new decision you will be trying to implement and with it I hope to change your settlement of banning the use of mobile phones in some public places.
As we all know, our phones have become a part of our everyday life, an object most people cannot live without, I am not judging because I also find myself in that category.
I certainly understand why the town council has decided to ban the use of mobile phones on public transports, in shops and in restaurants, but I also consider that it is a bit of an exaggerated decision.
I opt to believe that the main reason why we use our phones so much is because we try to make the best out of our precious time, and our phones can be of great help for reaching out to our close ones which may live away from us, so the only time we really get to talk to them is while on a bus or when buying groceries.
Furthermore, I strongly agree with banning the utilization of our phones in restaurants due to the fact it might be a great change and people will have no choice but to socialize with their date, coworker or family member rather than using their phones more than half the time they spend at the restaurant waiting for a incredibly short dopamine rush from a notification they just received Thank you for your attention and I hope you will take my letter into consideration.
Yours faithfully, Florin
