Health is the most important thing in our lives.
If our health was poor then we will not able to enjoy life anymore.
Many wealthy people had untreatable diseases and died.
Their money couldn't help them.
Exercise is a huge part of healthy living.
It is crucial to do sports on a daily basis, or at least on a weekly basis.
sport is vital for our bodies in so many ways.
But, is exercise the only thing that we should do?
The answer is: absolutely not.
Sport is essential, but it is not enough.
Cutting unhealthy habits might be more important than exercise, also eating healthy food is critical.
The worst unhealthy habit ever is smoking.
The problem is that it does not just effect the people who smoke.
It also affect their surroundings.
It is proven that smoking kills millions of people every year, so we have to cut it out of our lives.
Healthy food is necessary to keep our bodies and minds healthy.
It includes fruits, vegetables, and grains.
Eating healthy food also means that we should not consume junk food a lot.
Learning to play on instruments can be a wise way to spend your time - it improves memory and exercises your brain to focus better.
Studying music, combinated with testing your abilities to play have quite a few positive outcomes.
To start with, majority of students like to complain about lack of enthusiasm and action in schools, as well as no place to expand your creativity.
What could be a better place than a music class?
Music itself have power to form new passions or even relationships.
Studies have shown listening and playing have amazingly surprising impact on one's brain.
In a music class, when you meet new people and share your interest, you can not only make new friends, but also develop better understanding of how sound works.
It can be useful for physics students!
Moreover, having a music class in between other lessons can cause you to feel more focused after.
After all, music class should be about discovering new genres, artists and instruments, which is not only developing for a brain, but also relaxing.
With more stable and quiet state of mind students are proven to perform on other classes much better.
Thirdly, learning to play new instruments can cause one to uncover new passion, which, in the future, can result in finding new job or just impressing potential partners with one's abilities.
All in all, I think music classes are a perfect opportunity to try something new and come upon people sharing similar interests.
Nonetheless, I understand how some of the students are against it, arguing they already don't have enough time for basic classes.
My opinion is that the classes should be extracurricular, to actually gather people who want to learn new skills.
