Concidering the globalization of the world, learning to speak a foreign language is important than ever before.
Firstly, most international businesses are done by the global language, namely English.
With the help of technology and transportation, the market is now expanded from the nation to the world, which means that there are greater needs for people to be able to communicate with those of forein countries.
Since language is the only mean for people to convey their thoughts, learning a foreign language is significant in order to succeed in business.
Another point is that more cooperation with other nations are needed to solve the global issues.
Currently, the world is confronting with global warming, overpopulation, and numerous other problems.
These are grave enough to threaten the whole planets and all living creatures.
To deal with such immense issues, nations should have constractive conversations which can be possible with smooth understanding available by a common language.
Given that immediate actions for the planet are neccesary, neccesity of learning new language to disccuss the solution is higher than the past.
Overall, importance of learning a forein lanuage is higher than the past.
Medicine is a noble specialization, it needs considerate, kind, and nice people to work within, but they are also humans like all of us, and they need to earn money, in order to implement that; they work in cities, leaving the rural areas with a limited number of doctors, causing a problem, what is the solution?
Before we dig in the solution, we should understand the reasons.
It is obvious that cities are more profitable for doctors, and we can not blame them for their desire to earn money.
Yes, medicine is a humanitarian job, but that does not mean that they should earn less money than everyone else.
If we thought about it, we can see that it is not just about the docotors.
Rural areas are less profitable for most of the other jobs, because there are less people there, which means less demand on everything.
Now, what is the solution?
Actually, solving the doctors problem in rural areas is part of solving the whole rural areas problem.
Government should make legislations which encourag the docotors to move to rural areas.
They also should give them monthly incentives as a reward for their effort in solving this problem.
We can not blame doctors on this one.
It is the government's duty to solve these kind of problems.
