The shape and design of our work spaces is critical.
It is proven that those two things affect our productivity and psyhcological status during work.
Now, some offices contain cubicles, which are an enclosed workstation, while other offices work in an open work spaces.
Which is better?
I believe that the worst design for an office ever is the one including cubicles.
Cubicles make the employees feel like they are arrested and their cubicle is their own cell.
When the employee feel this way, you cannot expect him to do a superb work.
In order to make your employee more productive and concentrated you should make him feel like he is still have some of his freedom.
Even though he has to work seven of eight hours per day.
I think it is obvious that I do not prefer enclosed workstations.
Instead I love open ones, because It is gonig to give the employee a better feeling about his job, rather than him thinking about it like jail.
So within the design of our offices we should send a message to our employees that this place is theirs, this feeling could help them be more productive and invested in their jobs.
