Truth is considered a vritue in many clutures and religions, and I believe it is a virtue too, but each rule has an exceptions, therefore, there are some specific situations, in which, lying would be a viable option.
The first situation is war.
Imagine yourself taken a hostage by your country's enemies during war time, and they investigaed you, and asked you to tell them about your country's weapons, numbers of soldiers, and secret matters.
It is a foregone conclusion that telling the truth here is wrong, it is deemed as betrayal.
Lying in war time is necessary in order to protect your country, you family, and yourself.
The second situation would be in marriage, and I do not want to be on the wrong foot here.
So, I do not mean big lies or twisted lies like cheating on your wife and lying about it.
Instead, I mean lies that would make her happy.
For instance, if your wife was not attractive during pregnency, and she porbably will not, It would be really wrong to tell the truth to her face, even if she asked.
Lying in these kinds of situations is also crucial, because the truth will not be beneficial for anyone.
instead it will hurt her feelings and make her feel less confident about her self and her body.
In my book, I believe that these two situations are the only ones that the person should lie in.
Other than that, it is wrong.
There has been some rumours about a legislation that ban the use of moblie phones in public transport, shops, and resturant, basically, any public closed place.
I am writing you today to express my thoughts about the matter, and to give you some suggestions.
