Even though it is one of the most searched and studied subjects, we can never know what is going to happen in the future, we can predict, but we can never be sure about it.
Although it is unknown, people try to plan their future, and every one of us have his own preferences.
Some people feel that it would be better to to live a long calm life while others consider a short intense life to be more appealing, so what is better?
It is the kind of question where there is not right or wrong.
If you asked me, I would not have a definite answer.
Both of the choices are tempting, and have its own advantages and disadvantgaes.
The first choice is tempting because it is a satisfying kind of life, you study, graduate, marry, have kids, then you probably see them entering the same cycle that you were in it, except for some minor changes.
Maybe it seems boring, but it is nice to be able to live calmly, and get old while watching your grandkids play and have fun.
The second choice is a nice one as well.
You just live twenty or thirty years, you do the things you love that cannot be long-term, then die calmly after finishing what you wanted to do.
I believe that I would choose a mix of those two, even though I cannot really choose anything.
Simply because fate happens.
