Most of the people work for the money.
If there is a chance to have a higher income when doing the same things, then who will give it up?
Nowadays, most medical doctors choose to work in cities rather than work in the rural areas which don\u2019t have enough doctors.
It is all because of the difference of incomes.
As we can see, some people who live in the rural areas don\u2019t have enough sources of medical.
When they need to go to the doctors they have to go for a long distance, that is okay when it is not urgent.
But what about the urgent times?
We can not predict all the accidents, and many people died because they can not get their treatment immediately.
After saying that much, what is the solution for this problem?
Someone might say that governments can distribute more fees to the hospitals which opened up in rural areas.
But I think that do not make sense, the people who live in there are absolutely not as much as the people who live in the cities, if the government distribute more fees, that might be not fair to the others.
Then what should we do?
I think that we can improve the transportations there.
By shortest the time they have to spend to go to the hospitals, the chance that they can get treatment immediately will be higher.
At the same time, people who live in the cities won\u2019t feel unbalanced because they can use those transportations too.
Not only the medical problems, there are actually lots more problems in the rural areas like this, and I think our governments should face the problems or not just keep ignore them.
There are lots of solutions actually, and it only decide by what they want or not.
The government definitely knows these solutions too, but they don\u2019t care because solving these problems can not bring them much benefit.
Reality is cruel, the problem like this will only be solved after a long time.
