To talk about the volunteer works that have to be done to graduate from some high schools, we have to figure out what is volunteer work at first.
In my opinion, volunteering is to work but not for the pay.
Maybe for leaning some experiences or just because of their passionate.
No matter what is point of departure, volunteering should be good for everyone.
But actually, something went wrong now.
Volunteering should be done because they want to do, but some schools made up rules that require students to go volunteering compulsory.
In that case, students will go volunteering with a different attitude.
They are not really there to help, and they just want finish their job as fast as they can.
Absolutely, the most of the quality of their work will not be well as we expected.
It is a difficult question to solve.
If we change the compulsory rules to some rewards, the quality will not get higher because the most of the students will still finish their work at the lowest requirement.
And if we make the lowest requirement higher, their parents will start to argue that it took too much time doing some meaningless things that their kids can not study well or something else.
The best way I think to solve this problem is to cancel the rule that requires students to go volunteering.
The students who really wants to help will still go by their selves and the others who don\u2019t have that kind of passion will not have to waste their time.
There are lots of things that can not be done well by setting up rules.
Many factors have to be considered, no matter the psychological problems or something else.
If we make everything compulsory, nothing is going to do well.
