Motivating children to do regular exercise Today\u2019s biggest challenge is in child education and parenting, how to motivate children to do regular exercise.
In recent years, the number of doctors reporting children with health problems such as obesity has skyrocketed.
The amount of youngsters doing sports is also ever decreasing.
So, schools should give their students sport classes three times a week.
Firstly, parents most of the time are not able to bring their offspring to the soccer club or tennisclub.
They are to busy with their work and come home after diner has already been served.
Undoubtedly schools are the perfect solution for this, their students could simply stay at school three extra hours a week and follow sport classes.
This will help enable children to exercise regulary.
Furthermore, it will not cost any extra effort from school or the parents; The students were already on school, so they do not have to be brought or something.
Secondly, as already mentioned in the introduction. There is an increasing number of teenagers who suffer from health problems, because of their lack of exercise.
They may not be motivated or empowered by their parents, but this is the part where college comes into play.
Similarly to the first argument, schools should just force and motivate their pupils.
This could simply be done by giving gymnastics three times a week.
In conclusion, schools should enable their students to participate in sports activities, since there is an ever increasing amount of young persons who suffer from health issues, because they do to less sport.
Furthermore, not every child is able to do exercise reguarly.
Schools could simpy help these youngsters by giving sport classes three times a week.
Students should not be stupid and doop it.
As an actual pediathran who look after the health of all the kids, I couldn't agree more.
During this lately years junk food and gummies have became the most crucial food for kids, and because of the big amount of restaurants of fast food, this habit of eating unhealthy food has became more bigger.
Now that there's more technology that sorround us and that a lot of kids are into videogames all the time, the best we can do for children is put sports activities at least 3 times per week, 'cause if they keep having an inactive lifestyle and still eating junk food, the amount of problems and illines they can have in the present or carry to the future are extensive.
I think that the fathers of this kids are not very conscient about the type of life are living their kids with such a bad habits of health and food.
If the parents are worried about their children, they can do some things to avoid the problems that a younger kid can get a heart problem once he's older.
Some of the things that I recommend is put the kid in an extracurricular sport, or if you have the possibility to do an sport that you can do at school after classes you could choose that option.
Doing an extracurricular sport helps the kid to have a more active lifestyle - in adittion of the sports activities 3 times per week - and to become more healthy.
Although we want children to start having a more active lifestyle, I would also recommend for them to change the type of food they're constantly eating and that aren't healthy for their body.
Food as juice that has a lot of preservatives and sugar, chocolate that is in almost every cookie you find, etc.
