Human always keep developing every second, that's our instinct that since our ancestry's era, we've already possessed that feature.
Our ancestry have an intense life because that's survival instinct, they have to forage, find place to sleep and hunt or would be hunted.
Today, some people presume that we don't need to do so anymore as we've had everything we need already (foods, stable accomodations and even places to entertain) but I don't think so.
We're human and human always want more in a positive way.
Personally, it's not wrong as curiousity is good, learning new things is good,..
I love an intense life more than anything else.
That's why if you ask me, I will definitely choose a shorter but much more intense life rather than a long, calm one until 100 years old.
As I have said, keep moving forward is our instinct, I belive that's a special feature that God makes specially for human.
Furthermore, I love the intensity of our life, I always think it's the gift which life gives to us.
Everytime I come up against a challenge or sticky situation, maybe I would feel sad or some other negative feelings at first, but after that I know it was a positive experience and felt very proud of myself.
After all, challenges help us grow, I learn a lot from those hard moments.
In summary, I couldn't live even a day with a life that is so calm or monotonous, everyday is the same, I prefer an intense but short one.
