Chosing a University and a course to enroll is one of the most important decisions in life.
Students have to decide it taking in consideration a lot of reasons, among them whether living on their own or with their parents.
I personally believe that living by yourself is one of the best choices for a studente.
I feel this way for two reason, which I will explore in the following paragraphs.
To begin with, I think is crucial for students persuing their own independence in this period of life, for many times before college students are living in a comfort zone in their parents house with food, housing, and clean clothes available.
It can make them used to a lifestyle that is not real, and for that reason a period living alone far from home can be really helpful for their development.
I am a compeling example of this, the best decision that I made in life was to leave my mother's house to go to college in another state, It helped a lot to delevop skills and habit that come in hand nowadays.
Secondly, living alone provides an opportunity to connect with other people and build lifelong relationships.
Moreover, It can also lead to building a powerful networking that will be important in a professional level in the future.
For instance, when I was living alone in college I made a lot of good friends, they help me a lot with to pass through that new phase and become really close.
Furthermore, for being with me everyday they became my second family and I can rely on them until this day which definitely come in hand in a personal and professional level.
To conclude, I strongly believe that living on their own is good thing for students, It will help them to grown personally and to build great relationships.
I think music is necessary for everyone.
Even if you do not like some styles, I bet that you have a song in your mind that helps or helped you somehow.
When you are sad or happy, your playlist can tell, I am sure.
And this is the thing, music has a great impact in our lives.
The best romantic song was written because of someone, the person put all his feelings in a way to express how they felt.
And, somehow, when we listen to that song, we think about someone too.
Or at least feel something.
But why?
Because music carries more than lyrics, carries feelings.
Another interesting thing, some studies reported the effects of music in neurological and mental diseases, showing that songs could affect our nervous system and memory.
This is an amazing thing to search more about diseases like Alzheimer and dementia.
So, somehow, the songs that you like and listen to has a permanent effect in your brain, even though you think about music like a random way to pass the time.
And because of that, I am sure that our lives would be harder without the feelings express through beautiful lyrics.
It would be harder to charge ourselves with the beauty of melody and composition.
Music makes us feel alive.
When talking about university life, the first thing we will think of is being independent.
Most of the students are of age and it is just the time to face some problems by themselves.
But, is move away and live on their own a good choice?
Here are some points.
The most simple problem is about money, there have to be a place for them to live, and a place might took some money.
So where should the money comes?
Some family can afford another expenditure like this, but what about the others that cannot afford?
Of course the students can go have a part-time job, but the college life is very busy, and I think it will effect their studying or their socializing.
And that might be putting the cart before the horse.
And another problem is about time.
When we are on college, there are lots of things to do, no matter the studies or the clubs or the relationships.
Those are all very important for the college students and will take a lot of time.
So, do they actually have time to do all the housework and do some dishes?
In my opinion, they have to learn how to control the using of their time and it is possible to handle everything.
So if the family can afford the money of living outside, maybe we should give it a try.
Actually there are many other things to worried in college life, because it is a big break of life.
We start to learn things not only for tests and we start to plan our future, maybe start to feel stress out but those are just what we have to face.
My favourite season of the year could not be other than winter.
