In the winter, staying close to the loved person is simply amazing...
I only appreciate the summer if I can walk along the beach.
Then, if there's no beach where I am, I hate the summer.
The other side, I prefer winter in all occasions.
Most medical doctors want to work in cities where they will make a lot of money, yet in many rural areas there are not enought doctors.
I believe medical practice is based on humanitarian values; and Medicine is always in the front lines in the fight against health catastrophies such as pandemics.
However, doctors often want to work in cities where wages are higher than in rural areas, and the reason is that doctors may have spent several years studying medicine; so they want to compensate the years wasted by financial profit from their work.
Furthermore, nowadays studying medicine is quite expensive, challenging and takes long time; so all of these factors contribute to why doctors want earn a lot of money for compensation.
In my opinion, this problem can be solved by strengthing the healthcare sector throught enhancing the healthcare facilities in rual areas, and increasing the salaries for doctors who wish to practise Medicine in rural areas.
In addition, we can also encourage doctors to work in rural areas by promoting living conditions in rural areas where doctors can find suitable environment to live and work so that they can feel satisfied.
On the other side, in adavnced countries rural areas are well equipped with hospitals and medical centres; making a little difference from big cities.
However, in developing countries rural areas have a very bad healthcare system compared to cities; and that is what makes most doctors in developing countries prefer working in cities instead.
Finally, strenghting the healthcare system and promoting the living conditions in rural areas can bring about a hope for many doctors to practise Medicine in rural areas.
