Some high schools have a requirement that students must complete a certain amount of volunteer work in order to graduate.
In my opinion, it is a good thing because students at this level of education need to engage themselves in volunteer work in order to understand the meaning of humanity, collaboration and sense of collective work by which they can build their character and self-confidence.
In addition to that, vounteer work inspires young people to learn about social responsibility; and I think that how we build our communites.
Making volunteer work as compulsory requirement for graduation can be compelling for something people and not for some others, but I believe it is a good thing.
Moreover, through volunteer work high schoo students can learn valuable skills that will help them gain work experience.
Working as a volunteer would help students to develop inter-personal skills; because they will work in an environment that bring together people from different backgrounds and expertise; so it is a very amazing opportunity for students to explore the world of volunteer work!
