In my opinion, nobody has to be forced to do nothing they don't want.
It is very important each person develops his conscience to have a healthy life.
Nowadays, it's obvious that so many people are not afraid with their health.
Considerable part of the people has acquired bad habits, which include fastfood, processed foods, not to go gymming, low quantity of water...
and all this is enough to make people have bad life's quality.
It's absolutely necessary this: To put inside the head of each human being that is very important to care about the body.
Mental, psychological and physical health.
I think that it will not be a recomendable thing forcing all university students and school children to do sports activities 3 or more times per week.
More than to force them to act this way, it is important show them how a good lifestyle can contribute to raise the level of the productivity of all in daily life.
Not only the professional or schoolar sides will get better.
Maintaining good daily habits will improve several areas in the life of the people.
When we put together good food, sports, inter relationships, smoking abstinence, alcohol consume's control and many other things we must to do to have a pleasant life, it's possible to live during much more time with good health.
So, I think that it is not necessary (and it is not pleasant, too) to force somebody to do something that they don't want.
Life always show us that in many occasions, when we try to apply some habits in people when they don't like them, the results are not too good.
When the time passes by, some of these people goes back to old bad habits, and all the work will have beeing lost.
It's better to bring solid, good argumentations, which will make people re-think their habits, and, so, they will can to change her in a voluntary way.
