Dear town council, I am writing to express my disagrement with the current idea that is being thought to be implemented regarding the usage of mobile devices on public transport and more facilities.
In first place and above all, using electronic devices in the previously mentioned places does not affect anyone in a negative way, in fact, people that take public transport for work or education displacement often use it for helpful pourposes or entertainment, which should be taken into consideration as well since some travels are long and dull.
Furthermore, regarding shops and restaurants, people using electronic devices can be anything but harmful or disrespectful.
For instance, people taking pictures of their meals or clothes could attract customers or advertise these places in some way, which in light of shop and restaurant's owners will not be seen as something needed to be banned.
Last but not least, I would like to mentione too that the attempt of preventing people of using theses devices, might only make the situation well worse due to the fact that people may rebel against it, it would be needed to implement new regulations and punishments...
And if we balance the consequences, and knowing that it is not one of the pressing issues in our city, it's eficiency may be sparse at best.
I just desired to express my opinion and foremost help with the problem.
Please do not hesitate to contact me if I can offer aid with anything.
I hope it was relevant information.
Yours sincerely.
Some activities requested by schools to their students in order to graduate are very important because it introduces some values to students, and more, depending where these students are studying they would have chance to interact with their community or do anything relevant to contribute with their cycle.
However, the way that it is presented and requested to students is not the best way to do that.
Broadly speaking, I guess schools that apply this philosophy to its educational system, should think in other approach to justify and motivate students to creat and develop this feeling of responsability to their community.
Although it beconsidered a requirement in some schools, in other words, that activity is mandatory, there are another ways to teach these values its importancy.
A great example of that are extra curricular activities where students immerse in aspects that are proposed to them.
I could list some of them here, to begin with students living with other family, for instance, in a farm or in a fishing area, and them helping these families with their daily tasks.
Second, students could spend some days helping in parks that are destinated to preserve natural wildlife and forests.
It is possible enumerate lots of different activities, whereas it is not necessary, because the idea here is the same, only shows that are another possibilities to show studensts that volunteer work matters, even when it is not a requirement.
So, to wrap it all up, I strongly recommend students and people in general do volunteer work.
As a result of that effort we can experience a better environment.
