Nowadays, video games are very popular among the children.
These games are very interesting.
As a result, the children addict to it.
However, some parents believe that these games can have a negative impacts on their children.
On the other hand, the other parents think that it may have some positive effects.
As for me, I don't think it may have good effects.
There are many reasons why I say this.
If the children play the games, they have to sit for the whole day because these games are interesting.
So, they don't want to stop anymore.
It is not good for their eyes and their health.
In addition, when they are playing games, they forget everything like to eat, to drink and to sleep regularly.
In the long run, there may have many bad things on them.
Moreover, if they play games all the time, they don't want to do anything. For example, to help their parents, to do their lessons regularly, to communicate with other friends.
Therefore, I agree that playing games can have a lot of negative impact on the children.
Some people think that zoos are good place for the people to learn about animals.
On the other hand, the other people think that animals should stay according to their nature.
So, it is not good to keep them in zoos.
However, different people have different point of view.
I don't want to judge exactly which one is right or wrong.
However, to be honestly, I think that it is better to keep animals in zoos.
There are many reasons why I say this.
In doing so, the animals don't need to worry for their meals because people feed them regularly.
Moreover, they can stay for their whole life without any dangers.
In addition, they don't need to worry their health because the doctors come and take care them very often.
And then, the people who come to the zoo feed them too because they love them.
May be some people will say it is not their nature and they should stay freely in the forests.
It might be true but it is not safe for them because of the hunters.
Thus, zoos is the best place for the animals.
There are many advantages studying abroad.
The students can learn new experiences, new cultures and can get a lot of friends from different countries.
Moreover, It is exciting and challenging. Because they keep in touch with different people.
So, they can share their experience with the peers and they learn learn different things from them.
In addition, they can improve communication skills by studying in foreign countries.
And then, they are way from their parents so they have to do everything by themselves.
It helps to improve their skills.
However, living in another countries might cost a lot in comparison with your native town.
And they can have difficulties to communicate with the other people with different cultures.
Another thing is that they may be homesick when they are away from their home.
If they are ill, there aren't anyone besides them.
So they might be lonely.
To sum up, there are both good points and bad points by studying in another countries.
Sport is, with no doubt, essential to everyone, both to young and older people.
Especially to students, doing a sports activity is very important because it allows them to distract from the long hours of study and to free the body from the accumulated stress.
Students spend lots of time sitting in a class listening to professors or sitting in their own rooms or libraries studying or writing.
Therefore, they need to move, not only in order to stay fit but also to recharge themselves and gain the necessary energy to face the day.
Many high-school and university students may think that training make them lose time they could use to study or to relax, by hanging out with friends or watching television.
Anyway, watching a tv series, for example, does not help them to disconnect the mind and recharge the energy, it simply gives them the impression of relaxing, which is important but not so beneficial as training.
Regarding younger students, such as those who attend the primary or the middle school, I think parents should make them understand the importance of sport, but without imposing them something they like.
Every child should be free to choose the sport he or she most likes and feel comfortable with.
Going to the gym, attending fitness courses, doing a team or an individual sport, instead, helps them staying fit while having fun and in many cases also making friends.
Despite the temporary fatigue, both the body and the mind will benefit from that.
They will sleep better, they will study better, they will have, in short, the necessary energy to face a normal weekday.
For this reason, many schools and universities are thinking of forcing students to do sports activities.
Even though it might seem too much, I think it is a right choice.
Students, however, have to be free to choose the kind of activity that most suits them in order not to feel discomfort.
