Which is better that university students move away and live on their own they are attending school, or they live at home with their family while they are students?
I think it is up to their parsonalities and condition of their family.
Each of them has different merits and demerits.
Therefore, there is no absolutely correct answer.
Independence of a university student from his/her family may lead to growth in his/her personality.
This experience helps him/her to live after graduation.
However, it costs many financial burdens for them and their family.
Some need to help of their family, and it may make them to be difficult to study in university.
If the students can't afford to live alone, they perhaps should live at home with their family.
The less concerning about they have, the more they can live freely.
It may lead to their growth.
For the reasons stated above, I can't choose which is better, but I think they should select what they think better so that they can study well.
