Do you have any advice for me?
Exist a list of conditions which I usually want they should stay present in my workstation.
One of them is silence.
I often rather be alone to develop my tasks.
I don't hate my coworkers, absolutely!,
but, when it comes to choose a type of workstation, if I could, I actually prefer stay alone.
When I am doing my activities and there is no one next to me, my mind works smoothly and the results become better.
So much voices at same time around me take my concentration, and I run the risk of don't pay attention to what I was doing.
More than this: Great part of the people don't get talking in a low sound...
they almost do this in a high voice, and they ignore the moment to stop the speeches and return to their own activities.
This make me feel annoyed, and I need to control myself: I almost always have the impulse of being uneducated.
In a nutshell, these are the reasons I do rather work isolated.
When I am alone, in a cubicle (not too small, of course!) 
or separated by walls, I feel myself more productive, my mind works better and staying far from the amount of coworkers' voices takes me to more tranquility.
When I am alone, I even may listen to pleasant music while I am developing my tasks.
 (You must agree with me: Working this way is much more difficult if the place where you are laboring is full of people talking about several subjects non related with your tasks, right?).
So, I will ask you a thing...
if someday you want to give me an opportunity to work with your employees, please...
let me do it in a cubicle, or in a place with walls separating me of my coworkers, ok?
I promise I will have friendship with them, but, in the moment of the work, I need silence, peace and maximum concentration...
And my results will be the best!
