Dear legislators, Recently, I have heard some news that you are going to pass a law of which people can't use phones on public trasport and in sjops and restaurant for safety reason because the government hope people can care more about their environment they stay.
Besides, the government also want to enhance the interaction with others among civilians so that it can make the town become a more harmonious and warmful town.
Well, as long as I know the detail of this act, I have some suggestions for you who are on behalf of us to make a approriate balaced point between safety and practical side in the future.
First, I'm agreed with the purpose of banning peolple using phones on public transport for safety reason.
While I'm opposed to put this act in practice in the ocassions such as restaurants or shops because the probability of security problems like killing, robbing, rowdiness is far less than that in public trasport.
For example, if someone got robbed or hurt on public transport, because everyone are phubbing so that no one noticed that someone has got hurt then it may cause more casualties in transportations.
Contrarily, in the restaurants or shops, it's obvious that anything but robber will try to help victim suppress the bad guy, because barely each person will looking around the environment such as stores and goods, even if some people are still looking at their phones.
Thus, the security may be safer in the shop and restaurants than that in public trasport, which is not to the extend that the government mandates not to use phones.
Second, I'm averse to banning phone in restaurant and shops just merely because the government hopes that civilians can have more face-to-face interactions so that everyone will not be indifferent to each other even strangers so that the meatures can invrease the reputation of hospitality among states.
Nowadays, phones have become a medium to communicate, show concerns and express opinions.
People will be connected closely than ever, and still, most people will have interactions if necessary.
Therfore, the government is overthinking.
