In my opinion, always telling the trutht is not a proper way to go along with others in any occasions as we are usually be taught to be honest to everything when we were children.
Somtimes, we need to tell some sweet lies to achieve a future positive results or harmonious atmosphere rather than become embarrassed and tense ramifications.
Firstly, sometimes if we are too honest, we may have some straight words to others especially for some who are sensitive to others' words or inlcined to be negetive, then we will have more bad consequences in both social and personal life.
For example, if someone is a little obses than before since you met last time, we couldn't tell the truth to him/her, contrairly, we should decorate our words to be more euphemistic lest he/she feels that their esteem is been hurt.
Second, to have a positive consequence, there are some situations in life are not appropriate to tell more details to others in case that they will lose hopes or even be killed.
For instance, if we were doctocrs and facing a patient who have got a worsening stauts and may pass away lately, we have to inform their parents that it still has hopes to cure only if they can abidy by the directions, of which the purpose is that giving some hopes to patients and their family so that they will not feel like fall into the abyss of dispairity.
In conclusion, althougth not telling a lie is a virtue, we need to learn when should we decorate and pack our words in a little polite way and will not hurt someone's heart stikingly.
Therefore, telling a lie can be accepted in some situations.
