Many people consider telling the truth is always beneficial instead of telling lies.
However, tell a lie sometimes is acceptable if the lie is not harmful to anyone.
For example, telling a kid that Santa Claus exists to let them improve their imagination or keep the spirit and innocence in them.
The first thing to consider is that people always lie for different reasons.
Some lies have sincere intentions of not harming anyone, and some others are the opposite of this.
Nevertheless, White lies are unavoidable many times to maintain order.
For instance, tell someone, you fell asleep, and that is the reason to arrive late to a meeting is a lie to avoid memos or penalties..
Hence that is why the difference between white lies and harmful lies is the key when people say the truth or a lie.
Along with telling a lie when is required, it is acceptable to tell a lie.
It is my view, truth is always important on account of the fact that people needs to know what happens around them.
Whereas, it is also acceptable to tell a lie when the situation requires.
In conclusion, a lie is not an act of evilness if the purpose of the lie is to avoid harm or damage.
Therefore, a lie is fair if the purpose of the lie is to protect people from the truth.
We cannot dis-prestige the importance for people to know and grasp important facts and situations in their lives through the truth.
