It doesn't exist the better or the worse way to live.
When it comes to live on your own, we can stand out some good points like building up your survive.
I know it's strang, but you learn how to choose according to your money, if you don't have a lot, you learn how to solve the problems when there's nobody close to you to help you to solve it.
Unhappily, you'll notice that you won't have much time to spend with your friends because you'll dedicate that time with other things like doing shopping; clean up your house at the weekend besides you'll have to prepare your food.
When you live with your family you'll realize that you'll have more time to spend with your family because your parents will clean up your house and prepare your food.
Other main sthrength is that you won't have lots of expenses like bills.
