When we become adults, life change forever.
And all the things around us change, too.
When we are children or teens, we almost always depend on our parents to do everything.
We depend on even their money to buy simple things we want, or to go out at weekends' night.
So, when we become adults, we have to look for situations which allow us grow up in every directions.
Then, it's very interesting that university students, for example, already start walking by their own resources.
Some of them move away and live on their own when they go to university.
At same time, there are others who live at home with their family in this periodo of the life.
I think that after a person get older, it is better for her not depend on anyone.
People need to understand that they will not have parent's protection for all whole life.
Protection is very good (and even useful) during some years of the childhood and teenage, but there is a moment in which we must learning to guide our own steps, because we won't have other adults to protect us for the rest of our lives.
So, I believe that the best choice to university students when they go to University is trying to build their own academic lives for their own.
If happens some extreme need situation, these students may ask to their father to help them, but in my conception, this only may occur if extremely necessary.
My idea about this has nothing to see with becoming difficult students' lives.
Never...
my idea is about to do they can see how hard is the real life out of our homes when we are older and we decide having our lifestyle.
No always children and teenagers imagine how is difficult working and getting things which parents do... It seems that every things our parents acquire fall from the sky.
So, may they begin to understand soon that life is difficult, and the first difficulty starts when we go to university!
