In my life, I have been studying English for almost twenty years.
I sometimes wonder why I am obsessed with learning English.
The answer is simple: I still need to learn English.
When I started studying English, I was a junior high school student.
Since then, I had studied English for three years in junior high school, another three years in high school, and four years in college.
During these ten years, I have become able to read English essays with a dictionary.
However, I am still not good at speaking and listening in English.
Since graduating from the college, I have continued to practise listening to English.
Every day, I listen to English news and shadow the news in a whisper on the commute train to work.
If a simultaneous translation tool became available, I wouldn't need to learn English any more.
I hope that day will come in the near future.
