Speaking truth is indeed a great life skill, and it plays an integral role in the life of several individuals.
It is recommended to be honest in life as it defines the character and moral values of each person.
This essay intends to highlight the reasons why I think it is absolutely necessary to speak honestly throughout the life.
To commence with, to be honest is an excellent virtue of life, and some people are born with this innate quality, whereas, the others learn this skill from family, or, teachers.
As this quality describes the social image of a peson in the society, therefore, it is essential to tell the truth at all circumstances in life.
To demonstrate, since I absorbed various moral values such as honesty, and punctuality from my father, it has always helped me to deal with challenging situations in a stronger way.
Even though it is hard to not to lie during tough times, it is recommended to communicate in an honest way as one can develop a bad habit of lying, which can have several dertrimental effects on individuals, and society.
Moreover, people can get involved in several troubles when they cheat on others.
To illustrate, a close friend of mine was habitual of speaking lies, which negatively impacted my image in the college, and eventually I decided to end my friendship with her.
Hence, it is advisable to tell the truth at all occasions as this trait is a buliding block of ones personality and image in the community.
To conclude, it is absolutely vital to communicate in a fair and transparent way for the well-being of society.
Furthermore, it helps people to be real and natural in their own ways.
Life expectancy is unpredictable and destined.
If I was asked to choose between living a long calm life until 100 years old and living a short lifespan but much more intense, intersting, and fatigue, frankly to say, I will choose the former for some reasons below although some people like me in the phase of teenagerse would like to have a tense life now.
The first reason why I will prefer to live longer is to learn more knowledge about this world.
The world is full of many interesting phenomenons and principles, which deeply lures me to observe the change of the world with respects to politics, economy, artistics, science, cultures, etc.
Besides, the process of change of knowledge and cultural and scientific phenomenons may last so long that I have much time to learn much more about the principle of this world than the ordinary if I could live up to 100 years old.
Additionally, the second reason why I prefer to live longer is related to my charateristics.
I'm a little conservative, quiet, and slow-paced person compared to most of my peers so that I'm usually inclined to live in a slow tone of life like taking a stroll on the road for one afternoon, sitting on the balcony leisurely and seeing the pedestrians crossing by the roads, and having a tasty drinks in a coffee shop while reading the traveling magazines.
Moreover, the most critical reasons for me to choose live longer is my lovely family.
If I have my ownw family, I 'm eager to accompany with my dad, my mom, spouse, wife, children as long as I can.
I would like to spend my rest of time taking care of them, watching them growing healthly, and allowing them to have their own families finally, which is the biggest satification for my life.
In general, after considering the above benefits compared to living in a short lifespan, I would prefer to live longer even though it may not be imaginable in my destiny.
