Dear Sir/Madam, I am writing to express my dissatifcation regarding the new policy of the administraion which abstains the usage of cellular phones on public modes of transport such as trains, and busses as well as in stores and eateries.
Since digital phones have become a necessity of life, therfore, it is not recommended to ban the usage of the same in all the above-mentioned places.
As we all are aware, that smart phones have proven helpful to people in several ways such as tracking known people namely family members and children, and for ordering commodities online, hence, utilisation of this gadget should not be banned in public places.
Moreover, this invention has helps individuals to perform their daily activities with less efforts.
Not only mobiles have been helpful in reducing distance-related issues, but it has also been helpful in overcoming time-related problems.
Although society has become habitual of using cell phones, which can lead to many detrimental effects, it is important to understand that this device can assist the human-race in many ways if it is used appropriately.
Considering the above-stated points, I request you not to disallow the usage of mobiles in public transports and common places because this device plays a key role in the life of its people and assist society to deal with their hurdles pertaining to time and distance.
