In the contemporary era, pupils, particularly the undergraduates, and students studying in schools are seen consuming fast food on regular basis, and following an unenergetic style of living, which leads to several detrimental effects on their well-being and fitness levels.
The essay intends to describe that how health and wellness can be maintained by adoptiing a healthy, and an active routine.
Moreover, it empasizes on the role of exercise and physical activities in improving the quality of life, hence, I concur with the idea that the youngsters should be urged to perform physical exrecise at least three times in a week.
As students are the future of our country, therefore, not only should they look after their physical health, but should also maintain their mental health.
Furthermore, playing outdoor games such as cricket, and tennis, or performing physical exrecises namely yoga, aerobics, and running can help youth to overcome several health-related problems.
To begin with, it helps the children to be active and enegetic throughout the day.
As a result, they do not feel lethargic while studying and they perform their daily tasks with enthusiasm and energy.
To illustrate, as I started to exercise since my childhood, it helped me to loose weight, and to concentrate better on my studies.
Secondly, a healthy physical routine assists youngters to overcome health related challenges namely obesity, diabetes, and asthama.
In comparison to medicines, to exercise is a better way to build immunity and fight against diseases.
To demonstrate, a recent study by Times has revealed that 70% of people suffering from diabetes can be cured if they imbibe a nutritious diet and perform physical activites on an average of three times per week To conclude, it is undeniably true that playing outdoor sports and performing physical exercises can support youth to overcome their health problems as well as to focus on their academic career in a better way.
In my opinion, to exercise is a great way to boost immunity; in fact, it is the best way to be phsically and mentally fit.
As life is important to all, their are some individuals who prefer life to be short and full of energy as well as intensity, whereas, the other class of individuals believe to live a long, and a peaceful life.
This essay intends to highlight the reasons why I think a serene and a calm approach is integral to live a healthy and a long-lasting life.
In the contemporary era, people not only are seen runing after money and wealth, but are also seen becoming competitive against each other, particulary, against their friends and family members.
As a result, they also let go off their relationship and friendship with their near and dear ones as they give more priority to their economic status in society.
Therefore, it is sensible to live in a serene environment such as in the countryside, where people show respect and gratitude towards each other.
This, furthermore, helps them to develop strong bondings among themselves, and to help one another during emergencies.
To illustrate, since my parents lived in a small town, they believed in simplicity of life and valued their relationships with others.
Moreover, they learnt to be contented in their lives, and not to become money-minded.
Sencondly, adpotiing a calm and a peaceful lifestyle helps individuals and society to be healthy in terms of their physical and mental well-being, and to enjoy a long-lasting life.
In my understanding, it is better to live a stress-free life beacuse stress, and anxiety are the two main factors for all types of health-related problems namely heart attacks, diabetes, and high cholestrol levels.
For example, a recent study by Times has revealed that 70% of youth living in the metropolitian areas are suffering from hypertension due to their intense and busy lifestyle.
Thus, it is important for people to adpot a passive lifestyle, which is benificial for their health, and life.
To conclude, as a complex and an intense lifestyle could lead to several detrimental effects such as health and social problems in society, therefore, it is prudent to adopt a passive lifestyle to safeguard the interest of human race.
