Should computers and tablets completely replace books in schools and universities?
I don\u2019t think so.
Of course, the tablets and computers are very useful.
Think about it, all your notes and your information are in the cloud or your computer.
All our data one way or another is part or completely in the computer\u2019s memory.
But they will completely replace books made paper I doubt it.
Because the books you can read any time, any place include without electrical energy.
You can make your notes in your books, so simple, just write.
The advantage no one can see your notes and your notebook no need upgrade constantly.
Anyway, in my opinion the best of reading books is that no hurt your eyes.
If you read the screen after a few hours your eyes will hurt.
Never my eyes hurt when I read a book, obviously with adequate light.
