There is no shortage of opinion on educational methods.
Some people believe digital devices, such as computers or tablets, should be used instead of paper books in schools and universities.
As far as my perspective is concerned, I agree with this statement.
This is my firm belief based on two plausible reasons.
In this regard, I will discuss how new educational instruments could contribute to a better educational comprehension; and also, how it would have significat impacts on protection of the environment.
The aforementioned justifications will be elaborated in the subsequent paragraphs.
First and foremost, technology have constructive results on quality of education.
By using new devices, like tablets, students can have a great access to various databases whilst they are attended in a class room.
These databeses can provide students with holistic information on every possible topic that could be presented by a lecturer at a class room.
If they had not had this possibility to use such useful appliances at a classrome, they would have been deprived of an opportunity to gain deep and asymetric knowdelge of issues.
Besides, these instruments make the teachign process more accurate and comprehensive.
In other words, learning through new tools presents better pedagogical outcomes.
Secondly, a shift from using traditional books to take advantages of new digital devices means that the number of tree should be cut every year to produce books, will be lessen dramatically.
In other words, if we increased the number of the electronic devices in schools or universities, it would result in a fact in which we will consume less papers.
This fact reveals that there is a nagative correlation between this two things: more digital devices, less tree should be eradicated.
Therefore, this policy have a positive environmental effect in itself.
To put in a nutshell, any replacement between paper books and digital devices should be considered as a fruitful decision.
As I explained above, I fully support this idea.
In this regard, I discussed how this measure would make teaching more easy and learning more beneficial.
Moreover, I stated that this policy would have environmental impacts which is indispensable.
Consequently, in my personal point of view, books should be replaced with new tablets and computers.
