There is no debate on the utmost importance of practical knowledge in different languages.
Almost all persons believe that nowadays, the ability to commiunicate in at least on language other than the native language is indispensable.
From my personal perspective, I agree with this statement.
This is my firm belief based on two plausible reasons.
Speaking foreign lanuages is essential to find a prestigious job; and also, it is a useful mean to converse with people all around the world.
These aforementioned justifications will be elaborated more in the subsequent paragraphs.
First and foremost, the world business is an inter-related phenomenon and should you thought to have a world-class market, you would have to interact with foreigners.
In addition, no one can dismiss the fact that the current level of import or export, in an international sphere, requies actos to command multi-languages.
On the other hand, when it comes to individuals, the same is true.
It has been shown by the scietific statistics that those who know more than two languages, have a significant opportunity to find jobs with higher wages.
Hence, ability to speak different languages seems to be inevitable.
Secondly, there are numerous langnguages in the world.
Should you knew more, you would be able to make more bond and friendships.
Besides, knowing various languages, other than a maternal tongue, contributes to your ability to travell all around the world and discover things and gain unbelievable unprecedented experiences.
Therefore, by speaking to a second or third language, you will be able to discover many new places by your own.
Otherwise, if one does not consider it as an impossible, it would be so hard to travel abroad.
To put in a nutshell, language has become a necessary instrument to make relations, to find a better job, and even enjoy your life.
With the current trajectory in international relations among States and nations, capability to have a high degree of proficiency in different languages, such as English, is vital.
In this essay, I delineated two explainations in which the necessity of foreign languages are proven.
Not only job prospects makes it as a prerequisite for a professional career, but also, ordinary communication with people around the world, through social networks for instance, will not be possible without.
