There is no shortage of opinion on prosperity or happiness.
In this regard, there is a famous delimma on whether health or wealth has a priority over the other.
From my personal perspective, I invariebly opt for health.
This is my firm belief based on two plausible reasons.
In this essay I will explain how health is important; and also, I will draw attentions to drawbacks of wealth.
These justifications will be elaborated in the subsequent paragraphs.
First and foremost, health, either mental or physical, is the most valuable gift in a life.
Without having a healthy body, no one can enjoy his or her life.
In addition, to the extent that you benefit from health, you can flourish other aspects of your life.
Should you had a healthy life, then you would be able to foster your talents, including in sport or even in your academic career.
Therefore, health has a great contribution in life and will be resulted in a better performance in any other field.
Without health, you probably have to consume a considerable amount of energy, financially or mentally, to regain your favourable condition.
Secondly, wealth is important but there is always a limit.
Money has its own negative and positive consequences.
Although its positive impacts are prevailing the cons, still there are some disadvantages.
For instance, a great amount of money will lead to anxiety.
The scientists have been scrutinizing the repercussions of wealth on mental health.
The result of their survey was significant and unbelievable.
It has been observed by the psychological experts that money has ramifications on mental health as it contribute to higher degree of distress.
Thus, money or financial independence is something that everyone try to reach at.
Nevertheless, it is not impeccable and may raise unintended problems.
To put in a nutshell, Health is more important than wealth.
If you have money without a healthy mond or body, you will have no choice but to spend your money to recuperate yourself.
In this essay, I tried to demonstrate certain issues that prove the significance of health vis-a-vis wealth.
I discussed the effects of health, as a general, to enjoy a happy life and to flourish a vast range of traits.
Moreover, I delineated some remificiations of wealth on human's health.
For sake of a conclusion, I would like to emphasize that health is the vital to benefit from life.
