Its is of the utmost importance to be a trustful person.
Majority of people believe that on no account should someone tell a lie.
From my personal perspective, I confirm the aforementioned statement.
This is my firm belief, based on two plausible reasons.
In this essay, I will explore the main advantages of telling truth.
Furthermore, I will denote how a lie could ruin credibility of an individual.
These justifications will be elaborated in the subsequent paragraphs.
First and foremost, honestness is one of the significant traits.
In all cultures, religious and cults, being honest is robustly recommended.
Furthermore, all poets, social thinkers, as well as philosophers highlights the necessity of telling truth.
Importantly, they delineate that this general rule has no exception.
In other words, under no circumstances, should the truth be dismissed.
If someone had concealed a turth, they would have continued to add lies in order to prove the primary fallacious statement.
Therefore, as it has been mentioned in Quran, the holy book of Muslims. salvation is nothing but in truth.
Hence, by telling truth, you may help yourself to go through difficult situations.
Secondly, lies can destroy the reliability of a person.
It is highly accepted as a social norm that decent people, who are eagerly believe in their integrity, avoid to tell something unbasis.
To make it less grandly, if an individual deliberately made an erroneous claim or distorted a fact, or intentionally tried to cover an act up, whaterver it could be, his or her authenticity would be damaged, as the truth will finally reveal itself.
If it is the case, on the similar situations, even with insisting on truth, barely it will be feasible for audiences to confind on an infamous lier.
Thus, never do we have to invoke to misinformation.
To conclude, truth will invariably prevail in all possible conditions.
It is like a shed light which eradicate the darkness of lies.
Accordingly, no one can hide a lie for a long period.
Consequently, we will always adhere to truth in order to be an honest person and to keep ourselves credible in the eyes of our relatives.
