There is no shortage of opinion on negative lifestyles.
Many people believe that due to the harmful impacts of sedentary on mankind well-beings, all educational institutions, including universities and schools, must make physical exercise compulsory.
The proponents of this idea recommend that these sportive actitivies should be taken on every other day.
From a personal point of view, I agree with the above-mentioned statements.
In fact, this is my firm belief, which I will provide two plausible reasons to prove my perspective.
Firstly, I will address the negative ramifications of inactive lifestyles on health from a scientific context.
Secondly, I will explore the benefits of an active lifestyle on mental robustness.
All the aforementioneds will be eloborated in the subsequent paragraphs.
To begin with, undoubtably, there are severe consequences on health which are driven from a sedentary lifestyle.
In other words, our methods of living will directly affect our medical conditions.
It has been established through certain empirical researchs that people who are not active during day, are at stake of chronical physical conditions.
For instance, if exercaise has been eleminated from your daily schedule, you would plague with heart diseases.
These medical disorders are in negative correlation with the extent of physical activites.
Thus, if someone had been seated for a long time, in a long run, he would have gotten physical abnormalities.
Therefore, doing sport and dedication to have an active lifestyle is associated with health-strenght.
Secondly, on no account should we consider the impacts of sedentary limited to medical health.
Its effect and consequences are beyond.
Apparently, sedentary lifestyle has siginifacnt effects on mental health.
The statistic foundings delineate that those who benefit from vacancies in which they have to be active, for example police officers or doctors who should invariebly be rush on their foot, feel happier than others with sitting jobs.
In other words, you will feel more enthusiasim in your life if you allocate more time on physical activities, regardless of the purpose and nature of the activity.
In this regard, one may accentuate on the relations between physical and mental health and well-beings.
It should be noted, however, we do not know a great deal about the exact interaction between body and mental health.
Nevertheless, their importance and their mutual effects are undeniable.
In conclusion, having a healthy life is rooted in our approach towards our life.
One of the prodominant examples is the effect of sport, physical activities and exercise on both mental robustness and medical condition.
According to this fact and based on the presented justifications, which has been explained in the paragraphs above, relevant authorities should take all necessary measure in order to mitigate severe outcomes of an hectic but inactive lifestyle.
In this regard, educational complexes, such as universities, could provide certain measures to adequately address this problem.
