In my view, requiring volunteers as mandatory work that student have to complete to graduate is a great idea and must be carried out in high schools.
I will give three reasons to prove my opinion.
First, volunteer work suits with student.
Almost student have a lot of free time, and volunteering can make this free time into a meaningful time so they can dedicate their time and work for the community.
The next reason, student can gain plenty of soft skills during doing as a volunteer.
Because volunteer work requires the volunteer to work with people to make something for other people, student can prove some skills in teamwork, communication, time-management, planning, event organizing, and so on.
And the last one, doing volunteer help student aware of life more clearly.
During volunteer work, meeting miserable people make them feel sympathetic with the unlucky, so they will regard of what they have and want to give more for the social.
In conclusion, it is good for students if their high school turn volunteering into compulsory work for graduation because it benefits to both community and student.
