Because I am currently unemployed, I have a lot of free time.
I often daydream in my free time.
Besides that, what I've recently been doing with my free time is reading on social sciences and self-help books.
I might read up to three times a day and each time up to half an hour.
I like reading because it satisfies my sense of curiosity.
Moreover, it's the only way I know to help myself with my shitty life, though it hasn't been much helpful so far.
Last night, I started a new book on economics.
Yes, I do.
Unfortunately, I have dysthymia and I have a very difficult time finding the motivation.
I can only tell you about what I wish I could do: I wish I could exercise two or three times a week, two to six hours in total.
I prefer execising outdoors, but the gym is OK too.
I like badminton, hiking, horseback riding, swimming, archery, shooting, biking, and so on.
Some of these are dual sports or else more fun when you're part of a group.
Unfortunately, I have social phobia.
