Dear town council, I am currently writing to you concerning your thought about banning the use of mobile phones on public transport and in other facilities.
As far as I am concerned, removing the right to use phones during a trip or from a direction to another is a bit tough.
As a matter of fact, everyone feel the need to go checking their notifications on social medias, looking at the actual news on the Internet or even sending messages to a relative.
Phones are now common in our society, banning the use of them would be seen as constraints.
However, you could reconsider other possibilities to, at least, decrease the issue of always using phones on public places.
On the one hand, I truly agree with you with the idea of reducing the use of phones but not completely.
For example, I advise you to set up an accurate schedule in order to show animations in shops or restaurants to catch people' eyes: and they may not be on their phones aigain.
On the other hand, you cannot oblige people not to use their phones.
So, let them use it when they need them.
To sum up, reducing the use of phones, and not banning them is the best option, according to me.
It would finally let people free from their screens and make them realise in which wonderful and gorgeous society they are living in.
