Dear Sir/Madam, I read your announcement about banning the use of mobile phones on public transport and in shop and restaurants at the government website yesterday.
I have some opinions want to share to you.
First, the mobile phone is a great envention of mankind, we use it to contact with other people around the world, search the information in the internet, play games, have a character like a camera which help taking and storage nice memories by pictures.
The mobile phone is very popular, most of people around the world have one of it in the present.
You want to ban it that mean you refuse the development of mankind from the past to the present.
Second, mobile phones become a part of people life in now, people use it to read newspaper online when they come back home by public transport, they use it to take some photos with friend or just theirselves when they come a new store or new restaurant.
People can not use mobile phones on public transport and in shops and restaurants mean that they put a part of their life in home when they come here.
I think they can do that instead of they will leave there.
It will make a big damage for the economy of our city.
Thirdly, people use mobile phones to contact each other like friends, member of their family, company staffs.
If they can not use it, it will become a big problem for daily life.
For example, when you are coming back home, your wife want you to buy meat and vegetable in a convenient store, then she will call you by mobile phone.
However, the government promulgate a law about banning use mobile phone in public, she just talk to you when you stay at home.
So you waste a lot of time for buying food.
I think banning mobile phones are impossible in the present.
