Everybody lies and that's okay When we are children, our parents always say that lie is wrong, however one common strategy for convice kids in not lie, is saying phrases like: "if you lie your nose will grow up" and show the cartoon of Pinochio, a story about a doll made of wood by a carpenter, this doll has life and they like to lie a lot, and always he does that his nose grow more and more.
The adults always says lies, for example: Santa exists and in the reality is the father in a costumer of santa to give gifts in the Christmas.
One other problem as the adults teach for children not to lie, but lying to them and even worse, asking for kids lie.
As an example: say to answer in the telephone that there are not in house.
The reality is everybody lies, and gives bad example of it for the kids don't help in nothing.
There are white lies that sometimes is necessary to not hurt the people that we like.
Or just not to be a bad mood person, like it's not okay someone ask " are you fine?"
and the other reply with every problem that has in the life.
Sometimes you need to lie for thiefs not stole you, just give the things that he could find.
If you have a secret safe you don't need to say the truth to him
I had a dicussion with my parents about people must always tell the truth or people is sometimes acceptable to tell a lie.
In my opinions, I think people is sometimes acceptable to tell a lie.
When you tell the true to some one, it make them hurting or shame so we use the white lie in situations.
White lie is a term which use to tell some thing not true but useless and harmless to anyone.
In the medical area, when patients have incurable disease, doctor, who take care of patients, often don't tell the truth about medical condition for them.
In contrast, doctor will say their medical condition is very good and they are recovering to normal, they just say the truth for patients' family.
If doctor tell the truth about medical condition for patients, they could feel nervous, anxiety about it.
It have bad affective for treatment or make sicknes is more worst.
In addition, the truth is sometimes unacceptable for some one, people usually want to hear something good about themselves instead of bad.
For example, when your staff, who work together with you in a company, asked you about how do you feel about her new dress which is weared on her body today.
In your mind, you feel it so urgly, terrible and unsuit for her.
However, if you tell the truth about your emotion about her dress to her, she could feel uncomfortable, shameful, or angry.
It can make a broken in bond between you and her in working and comunication.
Instead of you will say it is so beautiful and suitable for her.
In the present, if you say the truth, you would have enemy.
If you say the lie, you have friends.
In my opinion, replacing paper books with tablets and computers in schools and universities has its pros and cons.
One of the pros is certainly that there would be no risk of deforestation and therefore the non-cutting of trees.
Another pro is that it would greatly reduce the weight of the backpack which is a problem for students who are far from school.
One of the cons, however, is that, in my opinion, those who cannot afford a tablet or computer will not be able to attend school lessons.
Another cons is that, in my opinion, electronic devices will never be able to replace paper books because even from the point of view of touch it would change badly.
In the end, if the books are really replaced by tablets and computers, we will make a decision.
