Nowadays, most of the people seem to be obsessed with their mobile phones, and it is crucially awful.
And that will be outstanding to make people less immersed into their social lives.
And I appreciate any town council's attempts to prompt it, but the idea of banning the use of mobile phone on public transport and in shops and restaurants altogether seems to me too bad decision.
And that type of measures needs to be rethought and replaced by less strong and more pleasure.
And for that, there are a couple of reasons.
The first one is that some people do need to use mobile phones due to the important messages or calls, and they just couldn't wait until a receiver would go out and answer to it.
The second reason why people might need to use a mobile phone in that cases is that they might need to look something up on the internet or write a note.
However, in multitude ways, people just use their phones to entertain themselves during the boring parts when they are at that places.
And I think that the best that the council may do is that they will redesign the council's banning.
The council should place a rule at that places that will declare that people must just turn off the volume of the phones and use it in a way that don't interrupt others.
And in addition to the rule, the council should create an environment at these places that will get visitors immersed and make them forget about phones.
That will be a gorgeous action from the council's side for most of the people.
