Books have been important since the paper was invented.
Knowledge, feelings, ideas was transferred with books along ages.
With computers and tablets becoming popular, recently use of books has been reducing.
Computers have taken the place of books in many fields.
In my opinion, computers and tablets should completely replace books in schools and universities due to ease of use, easier portability, and envorimental reasons.
First of all, tablets provide an easy access to information.
We can find any information that we want with one click of a button.
Studunets buy their textbooks on the internet, and they can read them on the tablets.
Most of my classmates use tablets instead of books.
Another reason is that tablets are more portable than books.
We can fit billions of books in a tablet.
A tablet weighs approximately 500 grams while an average book weighs about one kilograms.
When we consider that a student carries more than three books a day, this makes a huge difference.
Lastly, millions of trees are cut down in order to make books every year.
On the other hand, tablets and computer never use trees.
So they don't cause any damage to forests.
