The program that is Write and Improve is helpful because of these main reasons: The first reasoning is that it gives learners at every skill level the ability to improve their writing skills with practice.
After practicing, you can test your writing with official tests to see if you are at the skill level you think.
Also, you can change your writing and it does not just permanently stay there.
There is one hundred lessons which is a lot of lessons for learning at any skill level.
It also gives feedback for wrong words, forgotten words and whole sentences.
You can even make your own tests in the program.
There are classes you can make and join and view results of the students' lessons.
You can track your own writing, your activity and awards.
You have a personal progress graph and a writing timer to keep track of your writing.
There is feedback, which is automatic, to say: "You have done great" or if you are wrong than it will say to look back at your writing.
You can also just write for fun in the program as well.
There are all kinds of writings: essays, reviews, articles and emails to learn for the test in real life.
The things that are bad about this program are: If you pass a word threshold by almost any means, it will just add some points even if your phrasing is worse and your sentences end with a gap.
The only difficulty with this tool is the scores are not very accurate.
I will highly suggest this program, Write and Improve to any English learners.
There are a lot of great things but sometimes things are a bit bad but it is very good for learning writing.
