The straight forward anwser for your question is yes, Television can also educate people, especially if we're talking about children.
Furthermore, Television isn't the best way to educate, because it compromises your concentration capabilities.
Also, is very limited, it could be use as one resource to search, and absorb content, but you can't do much more than that.
In my opinion, Television could be a smart way to educate your children, as it can be funny, and could focus the kid's attention to the Television programs.
Today, there's many education channels for children, and if they're not used in exaggerated way, I guess, it can helps in the education.
For adults in another hand, I can't find very useful for education purposes, maybe when you are studying languages, it's nice to get used to the accent, and some more real world vocabulary.
In resume, Television is just a tool, like internet, books, etc.
The secret for a good education is a dedicated mentor, who analysed, and reflects about what kind of information, is being consumed.
The mentor, in case of adults, can be yourself.
